<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LXXIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Apostasia.  Apostate religionis quandoque
corporaliter puniuntur.</FOREIGN></HEAD> 

<P> We rede how &thorn;er was offer&dtail; vnto Damyanus, in an abbay
&thorn;at Saynt Gregur byggi&dtail; with-in &thorn;e wallis of
&thorn;e cetie of Rome, a childe be his fader &amp; his moder; and
whe&ntail; he come vnto mans age, he

<PB N="56">

forsut&hbar; forsuke &thorn;is Abbay, &amp; went into &thorn;e werlde,
&amp; tuke hy&mtail; a wyfe.  So afterwar&dtail; hy&mtail; happend for
to fa&llbar; seke, and he garte bere hy&mtail; vnto &thorn;is abbay,
&amp; &thorn;er he lay; &amp; o&ntail; a tyme, sodanlie, befo&rtail;
his wyfe &amp; a&llbar; &thorn;at was aboute, he bega&ntail; to cry
faste, &amp; sai&dtail; &thorn;at Saynt Andrew &amp; Saynt Gregur had
bett hy&mtail; grevuslie; and whe&ntail; he had ligy&ntail; a while,
he sai&dtail; at &thorn;ai had donge&ntail; hy&mtail; becauce he went
oute of &thorn;e abbay &amp; tuke hy&mtail; a wyfe.  And a while after
he say&dtail; &thorn;ai bett hy&mtail; agay&ntail; becauce he
skorny&dtail; pure me&ntail;, &amp; wulde giff &thorn;aim noght;
"&amp; now," he said, "&thorn;ai bete me becauce I tuke wronguslie vi
&dtail; of a ma&ntail; &amp; wulde not giff hy&mtail; &thorn;aim
agay&ntail;; &amp; now I hafe for ilk peny a lass&hbar;" and within
ane how&rtail; or ij after, he rase oute of his bed, &amp; did
o&ntail; hy&mtail; a hayr &amp; a scapularie &thorn;at lay by
hy&mtail;, and ra&ntail; vnto &thorn;e kur&ktee;, and sai&dtail;
&thorn;at, be &thorn;e grace of Go&dtail;, he was delyver&dtail; of
a&llbar; &thorn;is betyng.  &amp; he garte make his bed in &thorn;e
same kur&ktee;, &amp; garte a monke go vnto mes; and evy&ntail;
onone, as &thorn;e gospe&llbar; was re&dtail;, he endi&dtail; his
life.  And &thorn;e monkis had his bodie to wass&hbar; it, &amp;
&thorn;ai fand vppo&ntail; his bodie wowndis &amp; yedders of &thorn;e
betyng &thorn;at he sai&dtail; he was bett with &thorn;ase halie
Saynttis for &thorn;e trispas at he had done. et c&curl;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> LXXIV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Apostata red[i]ens ad religionem pacienter debet
ferre quamcumque penitenciam.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Vitis Patrum,' how &thorn;at &thorn;er was ij fadurs
&thorn;at war tempid with &thorn;e spiritt of fornicacio&ntail;, &amp;
&thorn;ai went into &thorn;e werl&dtail; &amp; tuke &thorn;aim wyfis.
So o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;e tone of &thorn;aim sai&dtail; vnto
&thorn;e toder; "whatt hafe we wo&ntail; in &thorn;is our vnclennes,
se&ntail; we consayfe &thorn;at euerlastand pay&ntail; mo&ntail; folow
itt, &amp; we hafe forsake&ntail; &thorn;e life of angels?  And
&thorn;erfo&rtail; latt us tur&ntail; agay&ntail;, &amp; be as we wer
in wilde[r]ness."  And &thorn;ai went agay&ntail; vnto &thorn;er
cellis, and was reclusis a fu&llbar; yere, and had nothyng bod a
porcio&ntail; of bread &amp; watir evurilk day.  And whe&ntail;
&thorn;e yere was done, &thorn;e tone of &thorn;aim had a pale face,
&amp; &thorn;e toder a fayr face; &amp; his brethir askid hy&mtail;
whi his face was so pale, &amp; he ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail; and
sai&dtail;; "I hafe a pale face for I had myn&dtail; of &thorn;e
paynys of he&llbar;, whil&ktee; &thorn;at

<PB N="57">

I mon&dtail; hafe bod if I did penance for my sy&ntail;."  And
&thorn;e toder sai&dtail; his face was so fayr for he thoght of
&thorn;e gudenes of allmightti Go&dtail;, &amp; had a grete
comfurt&hbar; &amp; a ioy &thorn;at he was delyver&dtail; oute of
&thorn;e paynys of he&llbar;; &amp; &thorn;erfo&rtail; he sai&dtail;,
he had grete comfurt&hbar; whe&ntail; he purseyvi&dtail; &thorn;at he
was delyver&dtail; of so grete a pere&llbar;, &amp; &thorn;a&ntail;
put agay&ntail; in so grete wurthines.  And whe&ntail; &thorn;er
brethir har&dtail; &thorn;is, &thorn;ai vnderstude att &thorn;ai wer
of evy&ntail; penance. et c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Apostate reuertentes frequenter deuocius se
habent.  Infra de penitencia, ij<HI REND="sup">o</HI>.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>
</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> LXXV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Apostate aliquando eciam mali peiores
efficiuntur.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how &thorn;er was so&mtail; tyme a yong ma&ntail;
&thorn;at made [hym] of a mon&ktee; of Ceustos ordur, and &thorn;uff
<NOTE ID="P57.N1">MS. if.</NOTE> a&llbar; he was gretelie movi&dtail; be a
bissho&ptail; at was his Cussy&ntail; to co&mtail; oute of &thorn;e
place, yit neuer-&thorn;e-les he wolde nott, bod abade sti&llbar; &amp;
was professi&dtail;, &amp; efterwar&dtail; made a preste.  So
afterwar&dtail; be temptacio&ntail; of &thorn;e devu&llbar;, he gatt
oute of his place &amp; went vnto a grete company of thevis; &amp; he,
&thorn;at was gude emang his brethir, was &thorn;er &thorn;e warste of
a&llbar;.  So o&ntail; a tyme, at &thorn;e sege of a Caste&llbar;,
hy&mtail; happen&dtail; to be hurte with ane arow, &amp; was
bow&ntail; to dye.  And me&ntail; abowte cowncel&dtail; hy&mtail; to
shryfe hy&mtail;, an&dtail; he ansswer&dtail; &amp; say&dtail;; "What
may shrifte profett me, &thorn;at hase done so many grete trispasis?"
And &thorn;e preste tol&dtail; hy&mtail; &thorn;at &thorn;e mercie of
God was more &thorn;a&ntail; was a&llbar; hys sy&ntail;.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; he bega&ntail; to shryfe hy&mtail;, &amp; sett
hy&mtail; dow&ntail; o&ntail; his kneis befo&rtail; &thorn;e preste;
and God sent hy&mtail; swilk contricio&ntail; &thorn;at euer
whe&ntail; he bega&ntail; to shryfe hy&mtail;, he sighe&dtail; &amp;
wepi&dtail; so sore &thorn;at he mott not speke a wur&dtail;.  So at
&thorn;e laste he tuke his spiritt vnto hy&mtail; &amp; say&dtail;;
"Sur, I hafe synny&dtail; ofter &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;er is
grave&llbar; in &thorn;e see, and I hafe gane oute of myne ordur and
felashippi&dtail; me with thevis &amp; lurdans, &amp; slay&ntail; many
a ma&ntail;.  And if &thorn;ai be savi&dtail; I mo&ntail; nott, ffor I
hafe violatt &amp; fyli&dtail; many mens wyvis, &amp; &thorn;er
chuldre, &amp; burnyd &thorn;er howsis, &amp; done many other infenyte
illis."  And &thorn;e preste was bod a fule &amp; sai&dtail;; "
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Maior est iniquitas tua quam veniam
mercaris:</FOREIGN>



<PB N="58">

&thorn;i sy&ntail; &amp; &thorn;i wikkednes is more &thorn;a&ntail;
evur &thorn;ou may gett forgiffnes off."  And he ansswer&dtail;
agay&ntail; &amp; sai&dtail;; " Sur, I a&mtail; a clar&ktee;, &amp; I
hafe sene &thorn;is written, ' <FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Quacumque hora
ingemiscerit peccator, et cetera:</FOREIGN> Whatt how&rtail; som euer
&thorn;at a synner forthynkis his sy&ntail;, &amp; shryvis hy&mtail;
clene &thorn;erof, almighti God wi&llbar; forgiff hy&mtail;.'  And
&thorn;erfo&rtail; I beseke you for Goddis sake to enioy&ntail; me
so&mtail; penance for my sy&ntail;."  And &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e
preste sai&dtail;; "I wate nevur what penance I sulde enioyne
&thorn;e, for &thorn;ou arte bod a loste ma&ntail;."  Tha&ntail; he
ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail; &amp; sai&dtail;; "Sur, se&ntail; &thorn;ou
wi&llbar; not enioy&ntail; me penance, I sa&llbar; enioy&ntail; my
selfe penance; And &thorn;erfo&rtail; I byn&dtail; my selfe to be ij M&lbar;
.  <NOTE ID="P58.N1">M&lbar;. <HI REND="i">omitted, and added above the line</HI>.</NOTE> yere in purgatorie; &amp; after &thorn;at at
I may hafe forgifnes of my sy&ntail; of a&llbar;myghti Go&dtail;."
And &thorn;a&ntail; he askid &thorn;at he myght be howsel&dtail;, and
&thorn;is fon&dtail; preste wolde not howse&llbar; hy&mtail;.
Tha&ntail; at &thorn;e laste, he praye&dtail; hy&mtail; write his
confessio&ntail; in a scrow, and at he wol&dtail; giff it vnto
&thorn;e bisshop&ptail; &thorn;at was his cussy&ntail;; and &thorn;e
preste hight hy&mtail; &thorn;at he sul&dtail; do so.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; he dyed &amp; his sawle went vnto purgatorie, as he
had bo&ntail; it to do.  And &thorn;e preste offer&dtail; &thorn;is
cedu&llbar; vnto &thorn;is bisshop&ptail;; and whe&ntail; &thorn;e
bisshop&ptail; redd itt he was passan&dtail; hevie &amp; wepud, &amp;
sai&dtail; &thorn;us vnto &thorn;e preste; "&thorn;er was neuer
ma&ntail; &thorn;at I luffi&dtail; so wele whik&ktee;, &amp;
&thorn;erfo&rtail; I sa&llbar; luff hy&mtail; deade."  And in
&thorn;at yere he sente &thorn;urg&hbar; a&llbar; his bisshoppryke,
&amp; garte do message &amp; oders prayers &amp; suffrage of halie
kur&ktee; for hy&mtail;.  And at &thorn;e yere en&dtail; he
aperi&dtail; vnto hy&mtail; with a pale &amp; a lene face, &amp; tolde
hy&mtail; &thorn;at be his suffrage &thorn;at he garte do &thorn;at
yere for hy&mtail;, &amp; did hy&mtail; selfe, he was remytt of a M
&lbar; yere &thorn;at he sulde hafe suffre&dtail; in &thorn;e
pay&ntail; of purgatorie; &amp; if he wol&dtail; do als meku&llbar;
for hy&mtail; &thorn;e nexte yere, he sai&dtail; he sulde be clene
delyver&dtail; &thorn;eroff for evur.  And &thorn;is bissho&ptail;
garte do for hy&mtail; &thorn;e secund yere as he did &thorn;e furste.
And whe&ntail; &thorn;is was done, as &thorn;e bissho&ptail; was
syngan&dtail; a mes for hy&mtail;, he apperi&dtail; vnto hy&mtail; in
a white cowle, &amp; with a passan&dtail; fayr face, &amp; say&dtail;;
"Almi&yogh;tti God rewar&dtail; &thorn;e at &thorn;ou hase done for
me; for be &thorn;i besynes I a&mtail; delyver&dtail; in &thorn;ies ij
yere of &thorn;e paynys of ij M &lbar; yere in purgatorie.  And
&thorn;erfo&rtail; I thanke the, for now I go vnto paridice vnto
evurlastan&dtail; blis." et c&curl;.



<PB N="59">
</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Apostate habentes firmum propositum redeundi si sic moriantur
saluat eos, et reddit eis habitum monachalem.  Infra de voluntate que
pro facto reputatur.</FOREIGN></ITEM> <ITEM><FOREIGN>Apostata a fide aliquando a deo eciam
corporaliter punitur.  Infra de benedicta.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> LXXVI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Apostolus.  Apostolorum memoria et deuocio est
utilis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how som tyme in &thorn;e cetie of Colay&ntail;
&thorn;er was so grete a fyre, &thorn;at a grete parte of &thorn;e
cetie was brente.  So &thorn;er was a certay&ntail; womma&ntail; in
&thorn;e cetie, &thorn;at wasshi&dtail; &amp; amendi&dtail; for hur
hyre a&llbar; &thorn;e clothis &thorn;at belonge&dtail; vnto &thorn;e
kur&ktee; of &thorn;e apostels.  And sho had a howse a&llbar; of
wu&dtail;, harde be &thorn;e kur&ktee;, and whe&ntail; &thorn;e
wykkid fyre was in howsis nere-han&dtail; hur, hur doghter bega&ntail;
to bere oute hir howsshol&dtail;; &amp; hur moder bad hur lefe, &amp;
wolde nott latt hur, bod garte hur bere in a&llbar; agay&ntail;.  And
sho lokki&dtail; &thorn;e dure faste, &amp; wente in-to &thorn;e
kur&ktee;, &amp; had grete faythe in &thorn;e apostels, &amp; sett
hur downe afo&rtail; &thorn;aim &amp; prayed in &thorn;is maner of
wise; "O! ye holie apostels!  &amp; euer I di&dtail; you any trew or
gude serves, kepe my howse &amp; my gudis &thorn;at is &thorn;erin."
Lo! &thorn;is was a mervalos fayt&hbar; of a womma&ntail;!  And
&thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e fyre &thorn;at burny&dtail;, sti&llbar;
ow&rtail;-hippi&dtail; &thorn;is lawnderer howse, so &thorn;at nowder
it nor hur gudis &thorn;at was &thorn;er-in was byrny&dtail;,
&thorn;uf a&llbar; &thorn;ai wer in myddeste &thorn;e fyre; &amp;
&thorn;us hur howse was savi&dtail; &thorn;urg&hbar; fayt&hbar;, &amp;
belefe &thorn;at sho had vnto &thorn;e apostels.  et c&curl;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> LXXVII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Aqua quasi solida stetit non fluens.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Gregorie tellis, how at &thorn;e Cetie of Terenence <NOTE ID="P59.N1">Latin MSS., apud Verenensem urbem, = Verona.</NOTE> , &thorn;e flude &thorn;at is calli&dtail; Artose
bolnyd up so, &thorn;at it come vnto &thorn;e kurk of Saynt
Zeno&ntail; &thorn;e martyr; and yit, &thorn;uf a&llbar; &thorn;e
duris wer oppy&ntail;, it come not

<PB N="60">

in; and it sparri&dtail; vp &thorn;e kurk-duris &amp; &thorn;e
wyndows, as it had bene turny&dtail; into a thyng &thorn;at had bene
faste as &thorn;e stone wa&llbar;, vnto so meku&llbar; &thorn;at mekle
peple &thorn;at was in &thorn;e kur&ktee; wa&rtail; sparri&dtail; in
with &thorn;e watir, &amp; myghte not wy&ntail; oute.  And yitt
whe&ntail; &thorn;ai come vnto &thorn;e kurk-dure, &thorn;ai might
take &thorn;aim water &amp; dryn&ktee; &thorn;eroff.  And &thorn;us,
&thorn;urg&hbar; &thorn;e gude prayers of &thorn;is holie martir,
&thorn;e watir was many day as a wa&llbar; vnto &thorn;aim, &amp;
myght nott entir in-to &thorn;at holie place.  et c&curl;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> LXXVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Archidiaconus ad episcopatum aspirans perpetrauit
homicidium.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Libro de Dono Timoris,' how so&mtail; tyme &thorn;er
was in Duchelan&dtail; ane archdeky&ntail; &thorn;at desiri&dtail;
gretelie to be a bisshop&ptail;, &amp; contyrfeti&dtail;
he&rtail;-fo&rtail; &thorn;e bisshoppis deade; &amp; he garte lay a
grete stane abow&ntail; &thorn;e yate at &thorn;e bisshop&ptail;
vsi&dtail; to go in att &thorn;e kurk att; and &thorn;er was ow&rtail;
&thorn;e yate ane ymage of our ladie.  And o&ntail; a tyme, as
&thorn;e bissho&ptail; went befo&rtail; a&llbar; his felashi&ptail;,
&amp; sett hy&mtail; dow&ntail; to wurshu&ptail; &thorn;is ymage
o&ntail; his kneis, &thorn;is stane was put dow&ntail;, &amp; smate
oute his hernys.  And onone aftre, &thorn;is archedeky&ntail; was made
bisshop&ptail;, &amp; made a grete feste at his stallyng.  So at
&thorn;is ffeste &thorn;er was a grete prince &thorn;at servi&dtail;
hy&mtail;, &amp; sodanlie he was ravisschi&dtail; into a visio&ntail;,
&amp; &thorn;er he saw our ladie with a grete multitude of aungels
&amp; Sayntis, berand &thorn;e bisshop&ptail; hea&dtail; at &thorn;e
harnys was streky&ntail; oute off, and present it vnto Almi&yogh;tti
God, sayan&dtail; o&ntail; &thorn;is maner of wise; "dere Son! yit
&thorn;is my servan&dtail; hede bledis; &amp; yit his succidur
&thorn;e homycide, at garte sla hy&mtail;, ioyes of his dignytie at he
hase after hy&mtail;."  And &thorn;a&ntail; our Lor&dtail; aski&dtail;
hur whome he sulde send vnto hy&mtail;.  And sho sai&dtail;; "Lo!
yonder is his server."  And &thorn;a&ntail; ou&rtail; Lorde
commanddi&dtail; hy&mtail; in pay&ntail; of dethe, &thorn;at he sulde
with-oute contynnance te&llbar; &thorn;e bisshop&ptail; a&llbar;
&thorn;at evur he had bothe har&dtail; &amp; sene.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; he come vnto hy&mtail; selfe &amp; wepu&dtail;, &amp;
went in &amp; tol&dtail; opynlie vnto &thorn;e bissho[p], befo&rtail;
a&llbar; at &thorn;er was, a&llbar; &thorn;at he had bothe har&dtail;
&amp; sene.  And whe&ntail; &thorn;is bisshop&ptail; had har&dtail;
hy&mtail; oppynlie befo&rtail; a&llbar; me&ntail;, he wex wude &amp;
swelte. et c&curl;.

<PB N="61">
</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Archiepiscopus a demonibus <NOTE ID="P61.N1">MS. demonijs.  Latin MSS. have, de demonibus deportatur.</NOTE> portatur.  Infra
de demone.</FOREIGN></ITEM> <ITEM><FOREIGN>Arma religiosorum sunt vestes eorum.  Infra de
Religione.</FOREIGN></ITEM> <ITEM><FOREIGN>Arma monachi possunt tempore et loco ex causa <NOTE ID="P61.N2">MS. leaves a space here. Harl. MS. Arma monachi possunt tempore et loco.  Infra de bello. Arund.  MS. Arma monachi possunt tempore et loco ex causa.  Infra de bello.</NOTE> ...  Infra de bello.</FOREIGN></ITEM> <ITEM><FOREIGN>Arnulphi Metensis.  Infra
de Remissione.</FOREIGN></ITEM> <ITEM><FOREIGN>Arsenij senatoris et heremite.  Infra de odore
et de peccato, de solitudine et vigilia. et c&curl;.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>

</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> LXXIX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Aspectus debet esse compositus.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Tullius tellis how &thorn;at Pericles <NOTE ID="P61.N3">MS. paricles.</NOTE> &amp;
Sophocles war made dukis at Athenys.  And o&ntail; a tyme, whe&ntail;
&thorn;ai went to speke to-gedur in a cowncelhows of suche thyngis as
was necessarie vnto &thorn;e cetie, &thorn;er happen&dtail; a fayr
yong ma&ntail; to go be a wyndow at &thorn;ai sett enence.  And
&thorn;is Sophocles spak vnto Pericles <NOTE ID="P61.N4">MS. peric&hbar;.</NOTE> &amp;
say&dtail;; "Se! yonder gois a fayr yong ma&ntail;!" And he
ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail; agay&ntail; &amp; sai&dtail;; "Sur, it semys
a ma&ntail; of cownce&llbar;, not alonelie to kepe sti&llbar; his
handis &amp; his tong, bod also for to kepe his ee&ntail; contynent
fro&mtail; a&llbar; maner of ydi&llbar; sightis in tyme &thorn;at he
is at conce&llbar;."


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> LXXX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Assenec&hbar; historia.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> As we rede in &thorn;e furste yere of &thorn;e vij plentyfu&llbar;
yeris &thorn;at was in Egipte, Kyng Pharao sent Josep&hbar; to
gad&rtail; samen cornys &thorn;at he cuthe gett in &thorn;e bowndis of
Cleopilas, of whilk regio&ntail; Pytaphar <NOTE ID="P61.N5">MS. Pyckaphar.</NOTE>
&thorn;e preste was prince.  &amp; he was a wise ma&ntail; &amp; grete
of cownce&llbar; with Pharao; and he had a doghter &thorn;at hight
Assenec&hbar;, and sho













<PB N="62">

was a passan&dtail; fayr mayde&ntail; emang a&llbar; o&thorn;er; &amp;
with &thorn;at sho was passan&dtail; statelie &amp; prowde, &amp;
thoght skor&ntail; be evur-ilk commo&ntail; ma&ntail;.  And sho was
kepi&dtail; so at no ma&ntail; saw hur.  And &thorn;er was
ioyny&dtail; uppo&ntail; &thorn;is Putyphar howse a tow&rtail;, at was
grete &amp; hy, &amp; in &thorn;e top &thorn;erof was a cenacle,
&thorn;at had in it x chawmers; of &thorn;e whilk &thorn;e furst was
grete &amp; fayr, &amp; dight with-in with precious stonys; and in
&thorn;at was &thorn;e goddis of Egipte, of golde &amp; of syluer, at
&thorn;is Assenec&hbar; did sacryfice vnto.  &amp; evur-ilk day sho
offer&dtail; vnto &thorn;aim.  And &thorn;e secun&dtail; chawmer lay
hur clothyng in, &amp; hur gold &amp; hur sylver &amp; hur precious
stonys; and in &thorn;e iij chawmer war a&llbar; &thorn;e gudis of
&thorn;e lande, &amp; &thorn;er was hur buttrie; and in &thorn;e toder
wa&rtail; vij maydyns &thorn;at servi&dtail; &thorn;is Assenec&hbar;,
with whame spak nowder childe nor ma&ntail;; and in Assenec&hbar;
chawmer was &thorn;er iij wyndows, ane at &thorn;e suthe, a noder at
&thorn;e este, &amp; &thorn;e iij at &thorn;e weste: &amp; at &thorn;e
northe was hur be&dtail;, onowrny&dtail; with gol&dtail; &amp; syluer,
precious stonys, &amp; gay clothis of purpur &amp; sylk at sho
slepi&dtail; in, &amp; &thorn;er sat neuer ma&ntail; o&ntail; &thorn;at
be&dtail;.  And aboute &thorn;is towre was &thorn;er ane entre with a
hy wa&llbar;, with-in &thorn;e whilk &thorn;er was fayre treis &amp;
frutefu&llbar; of dyvers kyndis; &amp; &thorn;er was a fayr spryng
&amp; a we&llbar;.  And &thorn;is Assenec&hbar; was a meku&llbar;
large womma&ntail; as Sarra was, &amp; als wise as Rebecca, &amp; als
fayr as Rache&llbar;.  So &thorn;is Joseph sent vnto &thorn;is
Putiphar &amp; lete hy&mtail; witt at he wal&dtail; co&mtail; vnto hys
place &amp; se itt; &amp; he was fay&ntail; &thorn;erof, &amp; lete
his doghter hafe knowlege, &amp; sai&dtail; he wolde marie hur vnto
hy&mtail;.  And sho was wrothe &thorn;er-with, &amp; sai&dtail; scho
wol&dtail; be giffe&ntail; vnto no ma&ntail; at was in thraldo&mtail;
as Josep&hbar; was, bod rather vnto a kyngis so&ntail;.  So as
&thorn;ai war spekan&dtail; samen, one come &amp; tolde &thorn;aim at
Josep&hbar; come.  And &thorn;is Assenec&hbar; fle&dtail; in-to hur
cenacle, vp into &thorn;e top&ptail; of &thorn;e towre.  And Joseph
come rydand in Pharao carte, &thorn;at was a&llbar; of gol&dtail;,
&amp; iiij white hors drew it, &amp; &thorn;ai had brydyls a&llbar; of
gol&dtail;; &amp; Josep&hbar; was cle&dtail; in a white cote &amp; in
pa&llbar; &amp; purpur wovy&ntail; with golde, &amp; a crow&ntail; of
precious gol&dtail; opo&ntail; his hea&dtail;, &amp; aboute it was
xij precious stonys, &amp; he had in his han&dtail; a golde&ntail;
wan&dtail; of &thorn;e kynges, &amp; a branc&hbar; of oliff fu&llbar;
off fatt frute.  And &thorn;is Putipha&rtail; &amp; his wife come
&amp; mett hy&mtail;, and wurschippi&dtail; hy&mtail;, and Josep&hbar;
went in-to &thorn;is entrie, &amp; &thorn;ai sparri&dtail; &thorn;e
duris after hy&mtail;.  &amp; at &thorn;e laste he was war of Assenech
oute at a wyndow, and sho saw

<PB N="63">

hy&mtail;.  And &thorn;a&ntail; sho was gretelie truble&dtail; with
wurd at sho had har&dtail; o&ntail; hy&mtail;, and &thorn;a&ntail; sho
sai&dtail;; "Beholde! &thorn;e so&ntail; is comme&ntail; fro
hevy&ntail; to shyne vppo&ntail; vs in his cowrs; and I wiste not,"
sho sai&dtail;, "at Josep&hbar; was &thorn;e so&ntail; off God&dtail;.
What ma&ntail; myght hafe so grete fayrnes, &amp; what wommans wambe
myght bere so grete a light?"  And &thorn;a&ntail; Josep&hbar; went
vnto Putiphar hows, &amp; &thorn;ai wasshi&dtail; his fete.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; Josep&hbar; aske&dtail; what womman &thorn;at was
&thorn;at he saw in &thorn;e cenacle oute at &thorn;e wyndow, &amp;
&thorn;ai tolde hy&mtail;.  &amp; he was afer&dtail; &thorn;at sho was
hevye vnto hy&mtail;, as sho was vnto other &thorn;at sent vnto hur
messangers with grete giftys; &amp; euer sho keste &thorn;aim
agay&ntail; att &thorn;aim with grete <NOTE ID="P63.N1"><HI REND="i">After</HI> grete, giftis, <HI REND="i">erased</HI>.</NOTE>
skor&ntail; &amp; dedyne.  And &thorn;a&ntail; sai&dtail; Putiphar;
"Sur, my doghter is a mayde&ntail;, &amp; hatis evur-ilk ma&ntail;,
for sho saw neuer ma&ntail; bod me &amp; the at sho saw &thorn;is day.
And if &thorn;ou wi&llbar;, sho sa&llbar; co&mtail; &amp; speke with
the."  And &thorn;a&ntail; Josep&hbar; thoght &thorn;at &amp; sho
hati&dtail; euer-ilk a ma&ntail;, sho sulde not be vnbehuvable vnto
hy&mtail;.  And &thorn;a&ntail; he sai&dtail; vnto hur fadur; "and
your doghter be a mayde&ntail;, I luff hur as my sustre."  And hur
moder went &amp; fechi&dtail; hur dow&ntail; &amp; broght hur befor
hy&mtail;, and hur fadur bad hur hals hur bruther, &thorn;at
hati&dtail; a&llbar; wome&ntail; as sho di&dtail; a&llbar; men.  And
sho halsi&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp; sayde; " <FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Ave
benedicte a deo excelso!</FOREIGN> hayle &thorn;ou blissi&dtail;,
comme&ntail; fro Almyghti Go&dtail;!" and &thorn;a&ntail; he
sai&dtail; agay&ntail;; " <FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Benedicat te deus qui
viuificat omnes;</FOREIGN> God blis &thorn;e &thorn;at whikkens
a&llbar; creaturs."  And Putiphar bad his doghter kys Josep&hbar;; and
sho wolde hafe done so, &amp; he lett hur with his han&dtail; &amp;
sai&dtail;; "It semys nott a ma&ntail; &thorn;at wurschuppis Almyghti
Go&dtail; to kys a womma&ntail; &thorn;at wurshuppis mawmettis
&thorn;at er defe &amp; do&mtail;."  And whe&ntail; sho har&dtail;
hy&mtail; say so, sho was passan&dtail; hevye &amp; wepi&dtail;.  And
Josep&hbar; was sorowfu&llbar; for hur, &amp; lai&dtail; his
han&dtail; o&ntail; hur heade &amp; blissi&dtail; hur.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; sho was merie &amp; parti&dtail; with hy&mtail; &amp;
went vnto hur be&dtail;.  And what for ioy &amp; what for drede, sho
fe&llbar; seke, &amp; did penans for &thorn;ase fals goddis at sho had
wurshuppi&dtail;, and forsuke &thorn;aim.  And whe&ntail; Josep&hbar;
had ety&ntail;, he tuke his lefe &amp; went his way, &amp; sai&dtail;
he sulde co&mtail; agay&ntail; &thorn;at day viij dayes.  And
whe&ntail; he was gone, &thorn;is Assenec&hbar; did o&ntail; blak
clothyng in toke&ntail; of hevynes &amp; sparri&dtail; hur dure, &amp;
keste dow&ntail; a&llbar; hur ydolsis, &amp; keste hur supper vnto



<PB N="64">

hundis, &amp; putt ass&hbar; opo&ntail; hur hea&dtail;, &amp;
lai&dtail; hur dow&ntail; on &thorn;e payment &amp; wepi&dtail;
bitterlie vij dayes.  And o&ntail; &thorn;e viij day come Josep&hbar;
&amp; tuke hur vnto wyfe &amp; wed hur. et c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
