<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> LXXXI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Avaricia.  Auarus quanto plus congregat, tanto
deus aliquando ei occasionaliter subtrahit.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Vitis Patrum' how &thorn;at so&mtail; tyme &thorn;er
was a garthener, &amp; a&llbar; &thorn;at evur he gatt off his labur,
he gaff it in almos, so &thorn;at vnnethis he kepi&dtail; vnto
hy&mtail; selfe to fyn&dtail; hy&mtail; mete &amp; clothe.  So
afterwar&dtail; be intysyng of &thorn;e devu&llbar;, he lefte his
almos-giffyng, &amp; gader&dtail; samen a grete some of money
&thorn;at he myght liff with in his age.  So afterwar&dtail; &thorn;er
happen&dtail; a surans for to fa&llbar; in hys lymbe, &thorn;at his
fute roti&dtail; off.  And he spendi&dtail; a&llbar; his money in
lechecrafte, &amp; was neuer &thorn;e better; and att &thorn;e laste,
be cownce&llbar; of a gude leche, he garte cutt it off.  And
opo&ntail; &thorn;e same nyght at it was cutt off, as he lay in his
bed sorowan&dtail; &amp; mornan&dtail;, &thorn;er apperi&dtail; vnto
hy&mtail; ane ange&llbar; &amp; sai&dtail;; "Whar is now &thorn;e
money att &thorn;ou gader&dtail; samen to liff with in &thorn;ine
elde?  What may &thorn;at now helpe the att &thorn;ou had hope in?"
And he ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail; &amp; sai&dtail;, "I hafe
synny&dtail;, &amp; I wi&llbar; now no mo&rtail; do soo."  And
&thorn;is aunge&llbar; tuchy&dtail; his fute, &amp; it was
restori&dtail; agay&ntail;.  And &thorn;e leche come to hy&mtail;
agay&ntail; o&ntail; &thorn;e mor&ntail;, &amp; fan&dtail; his fute
hale, &amp; hy&mtail; gravan&dtail; as he was wunt to do in &thorn;e
felde.  Lo! Surs, &thorn;us he was restori&dtail; for his gude dede,
&thorn;uff a&llbar; he lefte it, and &thorn;erfor ye may see at
Go&dtail; wi&llbar; hafe no gude dede vnrewardi&dtail;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> LXXXII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Avaricia a temporali promocione impedit.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Grego&rtail; tellis how one &thorn;at hight Constancius, at
was cussy&ntail; vnto Bonyface, o&ntail; a tyme selli&dtail; his hors
for xij &dtail; of gol&dtail;, &amp; he

<PB N="65">

putt &thorn;aim in his kiste; &amp; in &thorn;e mene while he <NOTE ID="P65.N1"><HI REND="i">After</HI> he, dyed, <HI REND="i">erased</HI>.</NOTE> went his way.  So o&ntail; a tyme pure me&ntail; come
vnto &thorn;is pope Bonyface, &amp; aski&dtail; hy&mtail; almos
passan&dtail; faste; &amp; he was in &thorn;e kur&ktee; &amp; had
nothyng to giff &thorn;aim.  So he trusti&dtail; gretelie in his
cussy&ntail;, at he had gude, &amp; went vnto his kiste &amp;
bra&ktee; it, &amp; tuke oute &thorn;ies xij golde penys &amp; gaff
&thorn;aim vnto pure folke.  So &thorn;is Constancius come agay&ntail;
&amp; fan&dtail; his kyste breke&ntail;, &amp; with a grete
rumo&rtail; &amp; a cry he come vnto the pope, &amp; bad hy&mtail;
giff hy&mtail; his xij &dtail; agay&ntail;.  &amp; with his crying
&thorn;is pope wente into the kur&ktee; &amp; was gretlie
steri&dtail;, &amp; evy&ntail; standan&dtail; he lifti&dtail;
up&ptail; his handis vnto a&llbar;myghti Go&dtail;, &amp; made his
prayer.  &amp; sodandlie he grapi&dtail; in his boso&mtail; &amp;
fan&dtail; xij &dtail; of gol&dtail;, &amp; he keste &thorn;aim in
&thorn;is wude preste skyrte, &amp; sai&dtail;; "Behol&dtail;! now
&thorn;ou hase &thorn;e xij &dtail; of gol&dtail; at &thorn;ou
aski&dtail; me; Bod &thorn;ou sa&llbar; vnderstan&dtail;, &thorn;at
after my decese &thorn;ou sa&llbar; neuer be pope nor byssho&ptail; of
&thorn;is kurk, as &thorn;ou trowis to be; and a&llbar; becauce off
&thorn;i covatusnes, at &thorn;ou wi&llbar; giff God no &thorn;ing of
&thorn;at at he sendis the."


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> LXXXIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Avaricia est quandoque causa amissionis temporalium,
et vnius avaricia toti vni congregacioni nocet.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how &thorn;at a monk som tyme of Ceustus ordur,
&thorn;at was Celerer, was tempi&dtail; with covatice.  So o&ntail; a
tyme in barganyng he begyli&dtail; a pure wedow.  So it happen&dtail;
&thorn;at same yere our Lor&dtail; sent suc&hbar; weddur &thorn;at
stroye&dtail; a&llbar; &thorn;e vynys &thorn;at langed vnto &thorn;e
abbay, so at &thorn;er wyne had nowder colour nor savor.  And &thorn;e
abbott, seyng &thorn;is, trowe&dtail; &thorn;at it come for somwhatt
at God was displesi&dtail; with &thorn;aim fore.  And he went vnto a
holie mayde&ntail; &thorn;at hight Acelina, &amp; besoght hur mekely
at sho wol&dtail; aske in hur prayers of almyghti Go&dtail;, at sho
mot know be reuelacio&ntail; what was &thorn;e cauce here-off; and so
sho di&dtail;.  &amp; it was ansswer&dtail; hur be allmyghti
Go&dtail;, &thorn;at it was for &thorn;e fraude &amp; &thorn;e gyle
&thorn;at &thorn;is celerer did vnto &thorn;is pure wedow.  And yit it
was sai&dtail; mo&rtail; vnto &thorn;aim be almyghti Go&dtail; in
&thorn;is wise; "Yit I sa&llbar; tuche hy&mtail; with a plage."  &amp;
so it happen[d] &thorn;at a knyght &thorn;at wonnyd beside &thorn;aim



<PB N="66">

in &thorn;att yere, sodanlie of i&llbar; wi&llbar;, opo&ntail; a night
sett fyre in &thorn;er lathis, &amp; burny&dtail; up a&llbar;
&thorn;er warn-store at &thorn;ai had of cor&ntail;.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e plage cesi&dtail;, &amp; &thorn;e monke
shrafe hy&mtail; clenelie of a&llbar; hys synnys, &amp; come vnto
amendment.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> LXXXIV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Auaricia retrahit ab elemosinis
faciendis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Jacobus tellis how at &thorn;er was a womma&ntail;, &amp; hur
husban&dtail; gaff hur keys &amp; kepyng of a&llbar; at evur &thorn;ai
had.  And sho was so sparan&dtail;, at sho wolde giff nothyng for
Goddis sake vnto pure folke, nor vnto &thorn;aim at myster&dtail;.  So
at &thorn;e laste hur happend to dye, &amp; hur neghburs
cowncelli&dtail; hur husban&dtail; to dele so&mtail; almos to pure
folke for hur saule.  And he ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail; &amp; sayde;
"Whils scho liffi&dtail; hur selfe, sho wolde nothyng dele nowder for
hur selfe, nor for me; &amp; &thorn;erfo&rtail; I wi&llbar; now
nothyng dele for hur."

</P>
<P>
