<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CXXXVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Castitatem viri periclitari faciunt tempus, locus, et
mulier alliciens.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Jero&mtail; tellis in &thorn;e 'Legent of Saynt [Paul <NOTE ID="P96.N1">So in the Latin MSS.</NOTE> ] &thorn;e Hermett,' how Decius, at som tyme was
Emperour, tuke a yong christen-ma&ntail; &amp; garte lay hy&mtail; in
a softe bed, wha&rtail; &thorn;er was temperans of &thorn;e ay&rtail;
&amp; sown&dtail; of watir rynyng, &amp; syngyng of burdis, and gude
sme&llbar; of flowris, &amp; he garte byn&dtail; hy&mtail; &thorn;er
so with rapis, &thorn;at he myght nowder stur han&dtail; nor fute, nor
helpe hy&mtail; selfe.  So as he lay, &thorn;er come vnto hy&mtail; a
yong wenche &amp; a fayre, bod scho was not clene of hur bodie, &amp;
lai&dtail; hur done be &thorn;is yong ma&ntail; &amp; made hy&mtail;
dalyans.  And whe&ntail; he feli&dtail; at sho had movi&dtail; his
fless&hbar; vnto



<PB N="97">

sy&ntail; &amp; he mot not helpe hy&mtail; selfe, nor no maner of
wapy&ntail; had to fen&dtail; hy&mtail; with fro hur, he bate in
sonder his tong &amp; spitt it in hur face.  And with &thorn;e wark
&thorn;erof his temptacio&ntail; recedid away. et c&curl;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CXXXIX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Cautela.  Cautela bona frequenter est
necessaria.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Valerius tellis how ij men &thorn;at was samen at hoste with a
womma&ntail; &thorn;at hel&dtail; hostre, lefte o&ntail; a tyme with
hur a grete sowme of money, vndernethe &thorn;is condicio&ntail;, at
sho suld not delyver it bod if &thorn;ai bothe come vnto hur samen
&thorn;erfo&rtail;.  So with-in a little while after, &thorn;e tane
come &thorn;erfo&rtail;, &amp; sayi&dtail; his felow was dea&dtail;,
&amp; begyli&dtail; hur &amp; made hur to delyvur hy&mtail; &thorn;e
mony; and he went &thorn;erwith our se into a noder contre.  And onone
fro he was gone, &thorn;e toder come vnto hur &amp; aski&dtail; hur
&thorn;is money, and sho ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail; &amp; say&dtail;
sho was redie to giff &thorn;is money, bod sho wol&dtail; not delyver
it or he &amp; his felow bothe samen come &thorn;erfor, as &thorn;ai
had bothe bedy&ntail; hur do; &amp; &thorn;us sho excusi&dtail; hur.

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Cautela fraudulenta reprehensibilis est.  Supra de

