<PB N="107"></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLIV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Cogitacio de morte multum est vtilis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede ex 'Dictis Patrum,' how a yong ma&ntail; sayd o&ntail; a
tyme vnto ane ol&dtail; ma&ntail;; "what sa&llbar; I do? for I
a&mtail; like to be slay&ntail; with fowle &thorn;oghtis."  And
&thorn;is al&dtail; ma&ntail; ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail; agay&ntail;
&amp; sai&dtail;; "So&ntail;, a womma&ntail; whe&ntail; sho wi&llbar;
spane hur chil&dtail;, sho wi&llbar; enoynt hur pappis with bitter
&thorn;ing, att hur childe, whe&ntail; he wolde sowke, sulde lett
whe&ntail; he feli&dtail; bytternes.  And &thorn;erfo&rtail; putt in
&thorn;i thoght &thorn;e bitternes of dede, &amp; of &thorn;e paynys
&thorn;at er ordan&dtail; in he&llbar; &amp; in purgatorie for
sy&ntail; in tyme to co&mtail;, and onone &thorn;ies evi&llbar;
&thorn;oghtis sa&llbar; recede away fro the." et c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
