<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXIV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Communionem aliquando impedit pollucio nocturna,
et aliquando non.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cassianus tellis how he knew som tyme a ma&ntail; of
religio&ntail;, &thorn;at gaff hy&mtail; gretelie vnto chastitie bothe
of his harte &amp; of his body, with grete mekenes; noghtwithstondyng
he was tempi&dtail; with grete ludificacions o&ntail; &thorn;e nyght.
And evur whe&ntail; he ordan&dtail; hy&mtail; to ressayfe his
sacrament, o&ntail; &thorn;e nyght befo&rtail; evur he was pollutt in
his slepe.  And whe&ntail; he for ferdnes had lang time absteny&dtail;
hy&mtail; fro his mess-saying, for ferdnes hereoff he went vnto ane
olde bruther of his &amp; tol&dtail; hy&mtail; &thorn;e mate&rtail;
&amp; aski&dtail; hy&mtail; cownce&llbar; &thorn;erin.  An&dtail; he
vmthoght hy&mtail; &thorn;at &thorn;er was nowder in &thorn;is
ma&ntail; superfluitie, nor at his myn&dtail; was giffe&ntail; vnto
suche illusions, &amp; &thorn;erbie hy&mtail; thoght at it was nowder
sy&ntail; of his bodye nor of his mynde, he cowncel&dtail; hy&mtail;
baldlie to go vnto his mes &amp; reseyfe &thorn;e holie sacrament,
&thorn;at not be &thorn;is disseyte &thorn;e medcy&ntail; of &thorn;e
helefu&llbar; medcy&ntail; &amp; remedy sulde be lefte.  And be
&thorn;is cownce&llbar; he went vnto mes &amp; boldelie resayvi&dtail;
&thorn;e sacrament: and be &thorn;e vertu &thorn;eroff &thorn;e
custo&mtail; at he was wunte to hafe of &thorn;is illusio&ntail; fro
thens-furt sesy&dtail;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Communioni possunt adaptari multa que dicuntur

