</LIST></P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Comparaciones odiose sunt.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Agellius tellis how &thorn;at whe&ntail; Aresto[ti]le &thorn;e
philosophyr wexi&dtail; olde, a&llbar; his scolers &amp; &thorn;ai
&thorn;at vsi&dtail; his facultie come vnto hy&mtail;





<PB N="116">

&amp; prayed hy&mtail; to te&llbar; &thorn;aim &thorn;at, whe&ntail;
he was dea&dtail;, who sulde succede &amp; be &thorn;er maister in his
steade.  And &thorn;er was in his scole ij principallis, Thofrastus
and Memedemus.  And &thorn;a&ntail; Arestotile garte bryng hy&mtail;
bere &amp; mea&dtail; &thorn;att he myght dryn&ktee; of &thorn;aim
bothe befo&rtail; a&llbar; his scolars.  And whe&ntail; he had
tasti&dtail; of bathe, he commendi&dtail; ather of &thorn;aim.
Neuer-&thorn;e-les he say&dtail; &thorn;at bere was &thorn;e bettyr,
becauce it was &thorn;e elder.  And &thorn;us priualie
with-oute&ntail; lakkyng or commendacio&ntail; of owder partie
(&thorn;ai purseyvid) &thorn;at Thofrastus sulde be &thorn;er maister
after hy&mtail; whe&ntail; he was dea&dtail;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXVI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Compassio naturaliter inest mulieribus. et
c&curl;.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P>Valerius tellis how o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;er was a womma&ntail;
&thorn;at had done a grete trespas agayns &thorn;e law, &amp; sho was
broght &thorn;erfo&rtail; befo&rtail; &thorn;e justice, &amp;
&thorn;er sho was demy&dtail; &thorn;at o&ntail; a certa&ntail; day
afte&rtail; hur hea&dtail; sulde be smyten of.  And sho was
commandi&dtail; to priso&ntail;, &amp; he &thorn;at had hur in kepyng
had petie o&ntail; hur and gaff a doghter of hurs, at was a
womma&ntail;, lefe ilk day to co&mtail; vnto hur; &amp; ay whe&ntail;
sho come in he serchi&dtail; hur &thorn;at sho broght nothyng with
hur, &amp; it was commandi&dtail; hy&mtail; &thorn;at sho sul&dtail;
neuer hafe meate afo&rtail; scho sulde dy.  So whe&ntail; he
fan&dtail; sho abade on life many dayes with-owte&ntail; meate,
o&ntail; a tyme whe&ntail; hur doghter come, he serchi&dtail; hur
&amp; he fan&dtail; &thorn;at sho had susteny&dtail; hur moder life
with hur mylk of hur pap; &amp; he thoght &thorn;is a grete mervayle
&amp; went &amp; tol&dtail; &thorn;e iustice.  And &thorn;e iustis
he[r]fo&rtail; had compassio&ntail; o&ntail; hur &amp; forgaff hur hur
tryspas for hur doghter sake.

</P>
