</LIST></P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Compaciendum est amplius peccatis hominum
quam rebus temporalibus proprijs.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Grego&rtail; tellis; "we rede of a gude holie ma&ntail;
&thorn;at had no &thorn;ing to lif o&ntail; a&llbar; yere bod a little
cor&ntail; &thorn;at he had gravy&ntail; &thorn;e er&dtail; of, &amp;
sawe&ntail; hy&mtail; selfe.  So o&ntail; a tyme whe&ntail; he had
shor&ntail; it &amp; broght it home, ane i&llbar; ma&ntail; &thorn;at
luffi&dtail; hy&mtail; nott sett fyre in his lathe, &amp; burny&dtail;
v&ptail; &thorn;e cor&ntail; and a&llbar;.  So a ma&ntail; har&dtail;
te&llbar; &thorn;eroff &amp; come vnto hy&mtail; &amp; sai&dtail;;
'allas! fadur, what is happen&dtail; vnto &thorn;e? wo is me for
&thorn;e.'  And he ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail; with a chere as he had
bene nothyng grevi&dtail; &amp; sai&dtail;; 'wo is me for &thorn;at at
sa&llbar; happy&ntail; vnto hy&mtail; &thorn;att di&dtail; &thorn;is
dede!' as he had not sett be hys aw&ntail; her&mtail;, bod rather be
&thorn;e toder mans sy&ntail;."  et c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Compositus debet esse homo in sensibus exterioribus,

vt habetur supra de Aspectu.</FOREIGN></ITEM>


</LIST></P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXIX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Concordia multum est necessaria habitantibus
ad inuicem.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Vitis Patrum' how som tyme &thorn;er was ij brether
&thorn;at dwelte samen many yeris, &amp; &thorn;ai vari&dtail; neuer
nor neuer was wrothe.  So o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;e tone sai&dtail;
vnto &thorn;e toder; "latt vs make debate betwix vs as other me&ntail;
of &thorn;is werl&dtail; dois."  And &thorn;e toder ansswer&dtail;

<PB N="119">

&amp; say&dtail; &thorn;at he wuste neuer what debate was; &amp;
&thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e toder say&dtail; vnto hy&mtail;; "lay
dow&ntail; &thorn;i hude betwixt vs two and I sa&llbar; say it is
myne, &amp; &thorn;ou sa&llbar; say, 'nay! it is myne.'  An&dtail;
here-of sa&llbar; a debate brede betwix vs."  And &thorn;ai lai&dtail;
dow&ntail; &thorn;is hude betwyx &thorn;aim, and &thorn;e tone
sai&dtail;; "it is myne"; &amp; &thorn;e to&thorn;er sai&dtail;; "nay!
it is myne."  &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e tother say&dtail;; "it is
&thorn;yne; &amp; &thorn;erfo&rtail; take it v&ptail; &amp; do&ntail;
it o&ntail; &thorn;i hede &amp; go &thorn;i ways."  And &thorn;us
&thorn;ai parti&dtail; &amp; nowder of &thorn;aim mott nor cuthe
discorde with o&thorn;er.

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Concubina sacerdotis punitur.  Infra de
