</LIST></P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Concupicencia carnalis naturaliter ad mulierem
inclinatur.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P>We rede in &thorn;e storie of Barlaa&mtail; how &thorn;er was a
kyng &thorn;at had a so&ntail;; an&dtail; whe&ntail; he was new
bor&ntail;, wyse lechis &thorn;at saw it tol&dtail; hy&mtail; &thorn;at
hy&mtail; burde gar kepe it to it war x yere olde, &thorn;at it saw no
&thorn;ing bod meate &amp; dryn&ktee; &amp; clothis &amp; a
womma&ntail; to kepe it, &amp; els it sul&dtail; dye.  And so he
dy&dtail;; &amp; at x yere en&dtail; he garte bryng befo&rtail; it
a&llbar; maner of &thorn;ingis, &thorn;at it mott se &thorn;aim &amp;
know what att &thorn;ai war; &amp; &thorn;er was b[r]oght befo&rtail;
hy&mtail; gol&dtail; &amp; syluer, &amp; hors &amp; cate&llbar;, &amp;
evur as he aski&dtail; what &thorn;ai war me&ntail; tolde hy&mtail;.
And whe&ntail; yong womme&ntail; &amp; maydyns come befo&rtail;
hy&mtail; &amp; he saw &thorn;aim, he aski&dtail; beselie what at
&thorn;ai hight, &amp; what &thorn;ingis &thorn;ai we&rtail;.  And
&thorn;ai &thorn;at wer aboute ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp;
sai&dtail;; "yone er devils &thorn;at begylis me&ntail;."  And whe&ntail;
he had sene a&llbar; maner of &thorn;ingis, &thorn;ai broght hy&mtail;
vnto &thorn;e kyng his fadur; and he aski&dtail; hy&mtail; of a&llbar;
thyngis &thorn;at he had sene, whilk he luffi&dtail; beste.  And he
ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail; &amp; say&dtail;: "Fadur, forsuthe nothyng
els bod devuls &thorn;at disseyvis me&ntail;, ffor of &thorn;aim
alonelie befo&rtail; a&llbar; o&thorn;er is my harte sett."

</P>
