<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio delet peccata de Sciencia
Diaboli.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in &thorn;e 'Meracles of Saynt Constanty&ntail; <NOTE ID="P120.N1">Arundel MS. Ex miraculis sancti Constantini Cantuaris; celebrante sancto Lanfranco Cantuaris archiepiscopo missam.  The Harleian MS.  <HI REND="i">has</HI>; Ex miraculis sancti Dunstani Cantuaris; celebrante sancto Lanfranco Cantuaris Archiepiscopo missam.</NOTE> ,' how o&ntail; a tyme whe&ntail; Saynt Lamfranke at
was bissho&ptail; of Ca[n]turberie sayde mes &thorn;er, sodonlie a
yong monke, &thorn;at sul&dtail; hafe re&dtail; &thorn;e gospe&llbar;
at &thorn;e same mes, was afore &thorn;e gospe&llbar; take&ntail; with
a fen&dtail;; vnto so meku&llbar; at &thorn;ai &thorn;at come before,
what at evur &thorn;ai had done &amp; had not bene shrevy&ntail;
&thorn;erof, he wol&dtail; hafe tel&dtail; &thorn;aim it.  And
so&mtail; &thorn;at shamy&dtail; with &thorn;er sy&ntail;, went &amp;
shrafe &thorn;aim clene &thorn;erof for fer&dtail; of hy&mtail;.  And
whe&ntail; &thorn;ai come agay&ntail; before hy&mtail; he
spirri&dtail; whatt &thorn;ai war &amp; whar-fo&rtail; &thorn;ai come;
&amp; had no knowlege &thorn;at &thorn;ai had bene at hy&mtail;
befo&rtail;. et c&curl;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio nocet Demoni.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how &thorn;er was a doctur of Dyvinitie &thorn;at
was a gay prechur, &amp; he hight Thomas.  And whe&ntail; he was seke
&amp; bow&ntail; to dye, he was war of &thorn;e devu&llbar;
standdan&dtail; in a noke of &thorn;e chawmbre &thorn;er he lay, and
he coniuri&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp; spirri&dtail; hy&mtail; many
thyngis.  And emang a&llbar; o&thorn;er thyngis he aski&dtail;
hy&mtail; what noye&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp; his felos moste.  And he
sai&dtail; att no &thorn;ing noyed nor hurte &thorn;aim so i&llbar; as
di&dtail; confessio&ntail;; ffor whe&ntail; a ma&ntail; is in deadlie
sy&ntail;, a&llbar; his membres is bo&ntail;, &amp; he may not mofe
hy&mtail;; and onone as he is shrevy&ntail;, &thorn;a&ntail; is he
lowse, and redie vnto a&llbar; gudenes.  And whe&ntail; &thorn;is
holie doctur had har&dtail; hy&mtail; say &thorn;us, he thanki&dtail;
Go&dtail; &amp; gaff vp&ptail; his sawle in-to hevy&ntail;.

</P>
