<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio pura celat peccatum et recidiuum
manifestat.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how so&mtail; tyme in &thorn;e Dioces of Traiecte,
&thorn;er was a fysscher &thorn;at was a fornicatur.  &amp; o&ntail; a
tyme he was fer&dtail; to be putt vp at &thorn;e sene <NOTE ID="P121.N1">Latin MSS. timens in synodo accusari.</NOTE> ; &amp; he went vnto a preste &amp; shrafe hy&mtail;
of a&llbar; his sy&ntail;, and whe&ntail; he had done &thorn;at, if he
war accusi&dtail; he mot sekurlie deny it, &amp; suffer &thorn;e
burnyng of a hate yr&ntail; as &thorn;er was vse to &thorn;aim at
denyed it.  And so he di&dtail;, and &thorn;is hate yr&ntail;
&thorn;at he bare noye&dtail; hy&mtail; no &thorn;ing.  So afterward
he fell &thorn;erto agay&ntail;.  And o&ntail; a tyme he feri&dtail;
ouer a watir with a ma&ntail; &thorn;att had knawlege of his
mysgouernans; &amp; &thorn;is ma&ntail; spak vnto hy&mtail; &amp;
sai&dtail;; "I merve&llbar;, &amp; so duse many mo, &thorn;at &thorn;e
hate yr&ntail; byrnyd &thorn;e noght; for we knew wele enoghe at
&thorn;ou was giltie, &amp; hase occupyed it syne."  &amp; he
ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail;, &amp; say&dtail; &thorn;e hate yr&ntail;
noyed hy&mtail; no more &thorn;a&ntail; did puttyng of his han&dtail; in-to
&thorn;e watir; &amp; with &thorn;at he putt his han&dtail; into &thorn;e
watir.  And onone <NOTE ID="P121.N2">Latin MSS. mira dei iustitia, qui misericorditer penitentem custodiuit iuste, et iuste recidiuantem punivit.</NOTE> , be &thorn;e rightwusnes of
a&llbar;-myghti Go&dtail;, &thorn;at hy&mtail; hy schameles whe&ntail;
he was a penytent, becauce of turnyng agay&ntail; vnto his sy&ntail;,
&thorn;er he was punysshi&dtail;; &amp; onone as he tuchi&dtail;
&thorn;e watir it was vnto hy&mtail; as byrnan&dtail; fyre.  For als
sone as his han&dtail; was in &thorn;e watir he gaff a grete cry &amp;
tuke vp his han&dtail;; and a&llbar; &thorn;e sky&ntail; lefte
behyn&dtail; in &thorn;e watir.  And &thorn;a&ntail; he tol&dtail;
&thorn;aim a&llbar; how it happend hy&mtail;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXIV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio pura delet peccata a memoria confessoris
quandoque.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how &thorn;at <NOTE ID="P121.N3">MS. &thorn;an.</NOTE> o&ntail; a
tyme, as a grete meneyay of pylgrams sayli&dtail; to-gedur ou&rtail;
&thorn;e se, &thorn;er fe&llbar; suche a tempeste in &thorn;e









<PB N="122">

se, at &thorn;e shipme&ntail; war fer&dtail; at &thorn;ai sulde
a&llbar; dye.  And &thorn;a&ntail; spak one att was emang &thorn;aim
att was a grete synner &amp; sayde; "&thorn;is tempest is fally&ntail;
o&ntail; vs becauce I a&mtail; a grete synner; and I pray you a&llbar;
att ye wi&llbar; here my confessio&ntail;."  And &thorn;ai a&llbar;
hel&dtail; &thorn;er tong; &amp; he tol&dtail; so meku&llbar; horrible
veno&mtail; of sy&ntail; at &thorn;aim irki&dtail; to here hy&mtail;.
And onone as he had done, &thorn;ur&hbar; &thorn;e mercie of almighti
Go&dtail; &thorn;er fe&llbar; a grete calme in &thorn;e see, &amp;
&thorn;e stor&mtail; sesy&dtail; so sone at euere ma&ntail; had
merva&llbar; &thorn;eroff.  And whe&ntail; &thorn;ai come vnto
&thorn;e havy&ntail;, almyg&hbar;ti God tuke oute of &thorn;er aller
myndis a&llbar; &thorn;ase synys &thorn;at he had shrevy&ntail;
hy&mtail; off als verelie as &thorn;ai had neuer harde te&llbar; of
one of &thorn;aim.

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio pura a confusione temporali liberat.  Infra

de famulo.  v.</FOREIGN></ITEM>


</LIST></P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio eciam a morte corporali
liberat.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede how som tyme in &thorn;e cetie of Arthebatencis <NOTE ID="P122.N1">MS. Harl. In ciuitate Attrabanense.  MS. Arund.  In civitate Atrabacesi.</NOTE> , a yong pure clerk say&dtail; vnto a goldsmyt&hbar;
&thorn;at &thorn;er sulde co&mtail; vnto his howse a merchan&dtail;,
&thorn;at wal&dtail; by of hy&mtail; syluer vesse&llbar; of dyvers
for&mtail;.  And whe&ntail; he had tol&dtail; hy&mtail; &thorn;is,
&thorn;is goldsmyt&hbar; wol&dtail; fay&ntail; hafe solde his chaffer,
&amp; commawndi&dtail; one of his me&ntail; to go home &amp; feche
suche vesse&llbar; &amp; bryng &thorn;aim vnto suche a clerke howse.
And a sister of &thorn;is goldsmyt&hbar; broght &thorn;aim &thorn;edur
&thorn;is clerk lay in wayte of hy&mtail; &amp; his suster as
&thorn;ai come in at &thorn;e dure, &amp; slew &thorn;aim bothe, &amp;
cut &thorn;aim in pecis &amp; keste &thorn;aim in a sege.  And
whe&ntail; &thorn;is goldsmyt&hbar; meneya saw he tarid long &amp;
come not home, &thorn;ai went vnto &thorn;is clerkis howse &amp;
spirri&dtail; after &thorn;er maister &amp; his suster.  And &thorn;is
cler&ktee; denye&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp; say&dtail; he come nott
&thorn;er; &amp; &thorn;ai areste hy&mtail; &amp; a bruder &amp; a
sister &thorn;at he had, &amp; broght &thorn;aim befo&rtail; &thorn;e
<NOTE ID="P122.N2">MS. <HI REND="i">repeats</HI>, &thorn;e.</NOTE> iustice of &thorn;er law, &amp; &thorn;er
&thorn;ai cuthe not agaynsay &thorn;er gilde, for &thorn;e ma&ntail;
was fo&ntail; with &thorn;aim, &amp; &thorn;e syluer vesse&llbar;
bothe; and &thorn;ai war demy&dtail; a&llbar; to be brent.
&thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;is suster sai&dtail; vnto hur <NOTE ID="P122.N3"><HI REND="i">After</HI>, hur, h, <HI REND="i">erased</HI>.</NOTE> brother &thorn;e clerke;








<PB N="123">

"Bruther, I suffer &thorn;is fo[r] &thorn;e.  And se&ntail; we may
nott esshew &thorn;e pay&ntail; of dea&dtail; at we er demy&dtail;
vnto, lat vs shryfe vs of ow&rtail; sy&ntail;, at we may so esshew
&thorn;e euerlastan&dtail; pay&ntail; of he&llbar;."  And bothe
&thorn;e brethir wul&dtail; nott.  Noght-with-stondyng sho sh afe hur
of hur sy&ntail; vnto a preste with grete wepyng &amp; hertlie
contricio&ntail;; and &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;ai wer a&llbar;
taky&ntail; &amp; boun vnto a stokk, and a grete fyre made abowte
&thorn;aim.  And &thorn;e clerk &amp; his bruther fe&llbar; in a
dispayr &amp; war burnyd v&ptail;; &amp; &thorn;is damyse&llbar;
&thorn;urg&hbar; hur trew confessio&ntail; was kepy&dtail; harmeles.
&amp; yit &thorn;e bandis at sho was boun with wer burny&dtail;, &amp;
sho feli&dtail; no more of &thorn;e hete of &thorn;e fyre,
&thorn;a&ntail; it had&dtail; bene &thorn;e blaste of a dew
wyn&dtail;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXVI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio simulata vel tamen furtiua
<NOTE ID="P123.N1">MS. fulcina.  Latin MSS. <HI REND="i">as above</HI>.</NOTE> non delet
peccata de sciencia diaboli, sed tantum vera
confessio illa delet.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis &thorn;at o&ntail; a tyme in Braba&ntail;
&thorn;er was a ma&ntail; boun in a howse &thorn;at ha&dtail; a
fen&dtail; in hy&mtail;, whilk fen&dtail; cawsi&dtail; &thorn;is
ma&ntail; to vpbray&dtail; ilkone at come in with syns at &thorn;ai
had done &amp; war nott shrevy&ntail; off.  So &thorn;er was a
ma&ntail; in &thorn;e tow&ntail; &thorn;at gretelie desyri&dtail; to
se hy&mtail; &amp; here hy&mtail; speke, bod he was fer&dtail;
&thorn;at he sul&dtail; vpbrayde hy&mtail; with his sy&ntail;.  And
for fer&dtail; here-of he went &amp; shrafe hy&mtail; of a&llbar; his
synys vnto a preste, bod he kepi&dtail; with-in hy&mtail; a wi&llbar;
to fa&llbar; vnto sy&ntail; agay&ntail;; and he trowi&dtail; &thorn;at
he was sekur enog&hbar; &amp; wente boldelie into &thorn;e howse vnto
&thorn;is ma&ntail;.  And onone as he come in, &thorn;is ma&ntail; at
was bu&ntail; crye&dtail; &amp; sai&dtail;; "A! welco&mtail;,
fren&dtail;! co&mtail; ner!  for &thorn;ou hase wele whitten&dtail;
&thorn;e."  &amp; onone, &thorn;uf a&llbar; he war shrevy&ntail;, yit
he tol&dtail; a&llbar; his synnys oppynlie vnto a&llbar; &thorn;at
stude abowte; &amp; &thorn;e ma&ntail; &thorn;oght he was gretlie
confusi&dtail; becauce his syns wer so fowle, and he was passan&dtail;
hevye &amp; turny&dtail; agay&ntail; vnto &thorn;e preste, &amp; tolde
hy&mtail; a&llbar; how it happen&dtail;.  And he shrafe hy&mtail;
agay&ntail; with a fu&llbar; wy&llbar; neuer to sy&ntail; agay&ntail;.
And &thorn;an &thorn;e preste bad hy&mtail; go baldlie agay&ntail; and
he sulde no more shame hy&mtail;; and



<PB N="124">

he did so.  And whe&ntail; he come into &thorn;e howse, one at was
&thorn;er sai&dtail; vnto &thorn;is ma&ntail; at was bu&ntail;; "lo!
&thorn;i fren&dtail; is comme&ntail; agay&ntail;."  And he aski&dtail;
whilk was he.  And &thorn;ai sai&dtail;; "he &thorn;is att &thorn;ou
vpbraydi&dtail; right now with so fowle synys at &thorn;ou say&dtail;
at he had done."  And he ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail; agay&ntail; &amp;
sai&dtail;; "I vpbraydi&dtail; hy&mtail; noght, nor I knaw none
i&llbar; of hy&mtail;."  And fro thens furthe euerilk ma&ntail; trowed
att he was bod a lyer, &amp; wolde truste no thyng at he
say&dtail;. et c&curl;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXVII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio ex corde facta celat
peccata.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede how o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;er dwelte in a tow&ntail; a
knyght, &amp; he had a fayr wyfe; &amp; &thorn;e preste of &thorn;e
tow&ntail; hel&dtail; hur.  And it was tolde &thorn;e knyght, &amp;
he wolde nott onone giff faythe &thorn;erto; notwithstondyng he had
&thorn;aim evur in suspecio&ntail;, &amp; he wol&dtail; nowder latt
&thorn;e preste nor his wyfe witt at he had &thorn;aim so.  So
o&ntail; a tyme he prayed &thorn;e preste at he wolde go with
hy&mtail; to speke with a ma&ntail; a myle or ij thens.  And he
sai&dtail; yis, and went with hy&mtail; vnto a noder tow&ntail;,
wha&rtail; &thorn;er was a devu&llbar; in a ma&ntail; at wolde
te&llbar; euerilk ma&ntail; of a&llbar; &thorn;e synys at evur
&thorn;ai had dow&ntail; &thorn;at &thorn;ai wer not wele
shrevy&ntail; of.  And &thorn;is preste was afer&dtail; &thorn;at
&thorn;e knight broght hy&mtail; &thorn;edur for to aske &thorn;is
devu&llbar; of his dedis, &amp; he went &amp; soght a preste and
&thorn;er was nane in &thorn;e tow&ntail;.  And &thorn;a&ntail; he
went privalie into &thorn;e staby&llbar; &thorn;er &thorn;e knightis
man&ntail; had sett vp &thorn;er hors, &amp; he fe&llbar; o&ntail; his
kneis befo&rtail; &thorn;e knyghtis ma&ntail;, &amp; praye&dtail;
hy&mtail; &thorn;at he wol&dtail; here his confessio&ntail;, for he
was so seke he was bow&ntail; to dye.  And &thorn;er, with grete
contricio&ntail; he made a fu&llbar; confessio&ntail; vnto &thorn;is
ma&ntail;, &amp; besoght hy&mtail; to enione hy&mtail; penance: and
&thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;is servand say&dtail;; "Sur, I a&mtail; no preste; I
know nott whatt penance I sulde enione you, bod &thorn;at penance at
ye wolde enione a noder prest and he war shrevy&ntail; at you of a
like sy&ntail;, &thorn;at sa&llbar; be your penance."  And &thorn;is
done he went o&ntail; boldlie with &thorn;e knight vnto &thorn;is
ma&ntail; at ha&dtail; &thorn;is devu&llbar; in hy&mtail;.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;is knight aski&dtail; hy&mtail; if he
ken&dtail; oght with hy&mtail; selfe; and he sayd, Nay, he knew no
&thorn;ing with hy&mtail;. &thorn;a&ntail; he aski&dtail; hy&mtail;
what he cuthe say of &thorn;e preste, &
<PB N="125">

he say&dtail; &thorn;at he cuthe say nothyng of hy&mtail;.  And whe&ntail; he
had say&dtail; so, he turny&dtail; his tong oute of &thorn;e language at
&thorn;e knyght vnderstude, &amp; spak Laty&ntail; &amp; sai&dtail;;
"<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">In stabulo mundatus est;</FOREIGN> he was
clensi&dtail; in &thorn;e staby&llbar;."  &amp; &thorn;e preste vnderstude
what he say&dtail;, &amp; so di&dtail; none o&thorn;er att was &thorn;er.
&amp; he was fay&ntail; &amp; thanki&dtail; God &amp; went home with
&thorn;e knight agay&ntail;, &amp; lefte &thorn;is werl&dtail; &amp; went
&amp; made hy&mtail; a monke in Ceustus ordur &amp; become evur after a
gude ma&ntail;.
</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio facta diabolo in loco sacerdotis aliquid
prodest.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Jacobus de Vetriaco tellis how at &thorn;er was a ma&ntail;
&thorn;at had done many grete synys at he was neuer shrevy&ntail; of,
&amp; so hy&mtail; happen&dtail; fa&llbar; seke &amp; was like to dye.
And &thorn;e devu&llbar; was fer&dtail; at he sul&dtail; shryfe
hy&mtail; vnto so&mtail; preste, &amp; come vnto hy&mtail; hy&mtail;
selfe in liknes of a preste, &amp; cowncel&dtail; hy&mtail; to shrife
hy&mtail;.  And &thorn;is ma&ntail; trowe&dtail; at he had bene a
preste, &amp; shrafe hy&mtail; to hy&mtail; with gude wi&llbar; of
a&llbar; his synys with grete contricio&ntail;.  An&dtail; &thorn;is
done, &thorn;e devu&llbar; say&dtail; vnto hy&mtail;; "Bruther,
&thorn;ies synnes er grevus, and &thorn;erfo&rtail; I enione &thorn;e
to penance at &thorn;ou schryfe &thorn;e noght of &thorn;aim vnto no
noder ma&ntail;, for &thorn;ai may gretlie sklander &thorn;e"; and
&thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e devu&llbar; went his wayes.  And onone
&thorn;is ma&ntail; dye&dtail;; and &thorn;er come aungels &amp; fendys
vnto his sawle, &amp; &thorn;e fendis sayde; "he is owres, for he was
neuer schrevy&ntail; vnto no preste."  And &thorn;e aungels say&dtail;
&thorn;at he had made a confessio&ntail;, for he was contrite;
an&dtail; &thorn;uf a&llbar; it was &thorn;e devu&llbar; at he was
shrevy&ntail;, yitt he trowe&dtail; &thorn;at he ha&dtail; bene a
preste.  And &thorn;is sawle was broght befo&rtail; &thorn;e hie
iugement of almyghtti Go&dtail;; &amp; he demy&dtail; it for to be
putt agay&ntail; in &thorn;e body, at &thorn;e bodi eft mot be
shrevy&ntail; vnto a preste, and so it was. et c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio pura reddit sacerdotem dignum sacramento

misse.  Infra de sacerdote.  vj.</FOREIGN></ITEM>

<ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio cum 
<NOTE ID="P125.N1">MS. sine.</NOTE>  proposito recidiuandi non valet.

Infra de contricione.  j.</FOREIGN></ITEM>

<PB N="126">


<ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessionem impedit demon quantum potest.  Infra

de demone.  xj.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio penam corporalem inflictam delet.  Infra

de hereticis. i. et de Maria.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessio amissa a viuo, fit quandoque a mortuo

resussitato precibus sanctorum.  Infra de

Francisco et oracione.</FOREIGN></ITEM>


</LIST></P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXIX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessor in aliquo casu non tenetur confessionem
celare.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how &thorn;er was a monke of Ceustus ordur, &amp;
he confessi&dtail; hy&mtail; vnto his Abbott, how &thorn;at &thorn;uff
a&llbar; he war no preste, yit he sai&dtail; mes; and he wol&dtail;
not lefe nowdur be prayer, nor charge, nor comman&dtail; of his
abbott.  And &thorn;is abbott tol&dtail; &thorn;is case vnto a
certa&ntail; perso&ntail; and sent it vnto pope; and he ansswer&dtail;
agay&ntail; &amp; sai&dtail; it was no confessio&ntail;, it was bod a
blasfemyng, and "a confessur," he say&dtail;, "aw not be &thorn;e law
to lay&ntail; suc&hbar; a blasfeme, whar-&thorn;urg&hbar; grete
pere&llbar; myght fa&llbar; vnto a&llbar; holie kur&ktee;."  And
&thorn;us he was dischargi&dtail; of mes-saying. et c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessor non celans confessionem est causa

multorum malorum.  Infra vbi agitur de Maria

Dei genitrice.</FOREIGN></ITEM>


</LIST></P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessor incontinens multociens potest esse occasio
dampnacionis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how &thorn;er was a riche huswyfe &thorn;at had
done many horrible synnys; &amp; sho had grete sorow for &thorn;aim in
hur harte, and yit sho wol&dtail; nevur shryfe hur of &thorn;aim.  So
&thorn;er was a yong preste &thorn;at sho had broght v&ptail; of
bar&ntail; little hur self; &amp; sho tuke suertie of hy&mtail; &amp;
shrafe hur unto hy&mtail; of a&llbar; hur synnys.  And whe&ntail; he
had har&dtail; hur confessio&ntail; he was lathe to displease hur,
&amp; cowncel&dtail;

<PB N="127">

hur to fulfy&llbar; &thorn;e luste &amp; &thorn;e likyng of hur bodie;
&amp; scho wol&dtail; nott, bod abade in parfite contricio&ntail;.
And when he saw &thorn;at, he discuri&dtail; hur synys to ilk
ma&ntail; &amp; diffamyd hur.  And sho was so gude a womma&ntail; at
no ma&ntail; trowid hy&mtail; bod hel&dtail; hur a gude womma&ntail;
&amp; cownti&dtail; hy&mtail; bod for a fule.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXXI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessor eciam in cautela et in interrogando
<NOTE ID="P127.N1">Harl. MS. incautus in interrogando.  Arun. MS. as above.</NOTE>
multis est occasio peccati.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede how o&ntail; a tyme a maydy&ntail; come &amp; shrafe hur
vnto a preste; and he as ane vnwyse confessur bega&ntail; to tempe
<NOTE ID="P127.N2"><HI REND="i">After</HI> tempe, hym, <HI REND="i">erased</HI>.</NOTE> hur vnto sy&ntail;, &amp; gaf hur comfurthe
&thorn;erin &thorn;at sho sulde contynue.  And so sho contynue&dtail;
it so lang at sho cuthe neuer lefe it <NOTE ID="P127.N3">Latin MSS.  Virgo quedam cuidam sacerdoti confitebatur.  Ille sicut imprudens cepit de peccatis sibi ignotis interrogare.  Que mox de eis in tantum cepit temptari quod, sicut postea retulit alteri sacerdoti, vix de illis peccatis continuit.</NOTE> .


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXXII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessor discretus eciam nolentes per discrecionem
suam ad penitenciam inducit.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius [tellis] how &thorn;er was a ma&ntail; &thorn;at had done
many horrible synnys, and whe&ntail; he had shrevy&ntail; hy&mtail;
&thorn;erof vnto a preste, he wolde resayfe no penance, bod sai&dtail;
he myght do none; to so meku&llbar;, &amp; &thorn;e preste enionyd
hy&mtail; neuer so lity&llbar; penance, yit he wolde nott graunte
&thorn;erto.  So his confessur aski&dtail; hy&mtail; if he myght say
euer-ilk day his pater noster.  &amp; he tuke hy&mtail; &thorn;erto
&amp; did itt.  And almighti God sent hy&mtail; suche grace, &thorn;at
he come agay&ntail; oft-sithes &amp; asked evur more penans, vnto
&thorn;e preste had eniony&dtail; hy&mtail; sufficient penance for his
sy&ntail;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessor discretus debet esse compaciens et

condescendens peccatoribus.  Supra de Abbate.</FOREIGN></ITEM>

<PB N="128">

</LIST></P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXXIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confessor dure loquens confitentibus aliquando
contra se ipsum prouocat eos.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Libro de Dono Timoris' how &thorn;at a ma&ntail;
&thorn;at was in sy&ntail; happend o&ntail; a tyme to be in
pere&llbar; of his dea&dtail;; and he made a vow &thorn;at, &amp; he
mot esskape, he sulde shrife hy&mtail;.  And so hy&mtail;
happen&dtail; be delyver&dtail;; &amp; &thorn;e maister of his
felowshi&ptail; went &amp; shrafe hy&mtail; vnto a preste hermett,
&amp; he shrafe hy&mtail; vnto &thorn;e same.  And &thorn;is preste
gretlie blamy&dtail; hy&mtail; for his sy&ntail;, &amp; sent hy&mtail;
vnto &thorn;e pope; &amp; &thorn;is ma&ntail; wexi&dtail; hy&mtail;
gretlie and slew hy&mtail;, and di&dtail; &thorn;e same with ane
o&thorn;er confessur.  And &thorn;e thri&dtail; confessur har&dtail;
hy&mtail; mekelie &amp; spak frendlie vnto hy&mtail;, &amp;
treti&dtail; hy&mtail;, and enionyd hy&mtail; to penance one thyng
alonelie, &amp; &thorn;at was; &thorn;at whe&ntail; so&mtail;evur he
saw any ma&ntail; dea&dtail;, he sul&dtail; helpe to berie hy&mtail;
&amp; he myght, &amp; putt hy&mtail; in &thorn;e ert&hbar;, and at he
sulde &thorn;inke of deade.  And so he did oft-sythis; &amp; att
&thorn;e laste he bega&ntail; devowtelie to &thorn;inke o&ntail; his
estate, &amp; went in-to wyldernes, &amp; &thorn;er he liffi&dtail;
&amp; dyed in grete penance. et c&curl;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXXIV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confidencia.  Confidendum non est in senectute vt
propter hoc magis homo periculis se exponat.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Vitis Patrum' how &thorn;at ane olde ma&ntail; of
religio&ntail; was seke in Egipte, and he wol&dtail; algattis go home
vnto his frendis at he mot be with &thorn;aim to he wer seke, &amp;
not emang his <NOTE ID="P128.N1"><HI REND="i">After</HI> his, breke, <HI REND="i">erased</HI>.</NOTE> brether to noy &thorn;aim.  And
&thorn;e abbot Moyses bad hy&mtail; go noght, &thorn;at he fe&llbar;
not into fornicacio&ntail;.  And he was hevy &thorn;erwith &amp;
say&dtail; his bodie was dea&dtail; fro a&llbar; maner of swilk luste.
And he went o&ntail; his ways to his frendis; &amp; a damyse&llbar; of
hur devocio&ntail; kepi&dtail; hy&mtail;.  An&dtail; whe&ntail; he was
cover&dtail; of his sekenes, he lay by hur &amp; gatt hur with
chil&dtail;.  And whe&ntail; &thorn;is chil&dtail; was bor&ntail;,
&thorn;is olde ma&ntail; tuke it in his



<PB N="129">

armys opo&ntail; a grete festiua&llbar; day, &amp; come into &thorn;e
kur&ktee; &thorn;erwith befo&rtail; a&llbar; his brether &amp;
a&llbar; o&thorn;er &thorn;at &thorn;er was; and his brethir
wepi&dtail; &amp; made sorow for hy&mtail;.  An&dtail; &thorn;a&ntail;
he sai&dtail; vnto &thorn;aim; "See ye &thorn;is childe?  Lo!
&thorn;is is &thorn;e so&ntail; of inobediens; be war!" he sai&dtail;,
"&thorn;erfo&rtail;, ye brether, &amp; take ensample be me, for
&thorn;is I dyd in myne elde.  And &thorn;erfo&rtail; I pray you
hertelie pray for me."  And he went into his ce&llbar;; &amp; &thorn;er
he abade a&llbar; his life-days in grete penaunce &amp; prayer.

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confidencia est habenda in sanctis

<NOTE ID="P129.N1">So the Latin MSS.  The English version <HI REND="i">has</HI>, in sanctis temporalibus.</NOTE>  de rebus temporalibus.  Infra de Sancto Nicholao.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confidendum non est in quolibet.  Infra de gula.
iiij.</FOREIGN></ITEM> </LIST></P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXXV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confusio orta de peccato perpetrato aliquando est
occasio boni.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how o&ntail; a tyme a yong ma&ntail; gatt a
no&ntail; with chil&dtail;; an&dtail; he was so confusi&dtail;
&thorn;er-with, &amp; so fer&dtail; at he sulde be descrie&dtail;
&thorn;at he had done suche a truspas, &amp; no ma&ntail; had
hy&mtail; in suspecio&ntail;, &thorn;at he went vnto ane abbay of a
strayte ordur &amp; made hy&mtail; a ma&ntail; of religion, &amp;
&thorn;er abade in grete devocio&ntail; &amp; prayer a&llbar; his
life. et c&curl;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXXVI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Confusio aliquando est causa mortis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Helinandus tellis how &thorn;at shipme&ntail; o&ntail; a tyme come
vnto a philosophur &thorn;at hight Omerus, &amp; spirri&dtail;
hy&mtail; a questio&ntail; &amp; he cuthe not in no wise essoyne it.
And becauce he cuthe not, &thorn;ai sai&dtail; he was bo&dtail; a
fule, &amp; cuthe no wisdo&mtail;.  And he was so confusi&dtail; &amp;
esshamy&dtail; &thorn;at with-in a little while after he dye&dtail;
for sorow.



<PB N="130">

</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXXVII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Congregacio aliquando dirigitur per aliquem
bonum.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Isidorus tellis how [when] &thorn;at Phili&ptail; &thorn;at was
king of Macedonie was at Athenys, he askid of &thorn;e cetie at
&thorn;ai sulde delyvir hy&mtail; x wyse men <NOTE ID="P130.N1"><HI REND="i">After</HI> men, at, <HI REND="i">erased</HI>.</NOTE> ,
and he sulde breke vp his sege.  And whe&ntail; a ma&ntail; &thorn;at
hight Demonstrues <NOTE ID="P130.N2">Latin MSS. Demostrues.</NOTE> harde te&llbar; &thorn;is, he
feny&dtail; &thorn;is fable &amp; tol&dtail; it emang &thorn;e
cetisyns of Athenys; how &thorn;at, o&ntail; a tyme, wulfis
desyri&dtail; of sheperdis at &thorn;ai &amp; &thorn;ai myght be made
frendis.  And &thorn;e sheperdis &thorn;oght none i&llbar; &amp;
grawnti&dtail; &amp; was made frendis with &thorn;aim.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e wulfis aski&dtail; of &thorn;ies sheperdis at
&thorn;ai mott hafe &thorn;er doggis at kepi&dtail; &thorn;er
shepefal&dtail; delyver&dtail;; ffor as &thorn;ai say&dtail;, &thorn;ai
wol&dtail; be occasio&ntail; and cauce to gar &thorn;aim fa&llbar; att
debate agay&ntail;.  And &thorn;e sheperdis agreid &thorn;erto, &amp;
delyver&dtail; &thorn;aim &thorn;er doggis &thorn;at war wunte for to
kepe &thorn;er faldis.  And &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e wulvis
killi&dtail; &thorn;ies howndis; &amp; whe&ntail; &thorn;ai had so
done, &thorn;ai come &amp; weri&dtail; vp a&llbar; &thorn;e shepe att
was in &thorn;e flok&ktee;.  "And &thorn;us," he say&dtail;,
"wi&llbar; Philip&ptail; &thorn;e kyng do with vs, &thorn;at is to
say, take away our wise me&ntail; &amp; ow&rtail; oraturs; and
whe&ntail; he hase so done, &thorn;a&ntail; he wy&llbar;
mys-chefe vs &amp; sla vs, &amp; a&llbar; &thorn;at er in &thorn;e
cetie of Athenys."


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXXVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Consanguinitas.  Consanguinei non sunt a viris
sanctis sustentandi nisi in iure suo proprio.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in &thorn;e life of Abbott Pastur, how &thorn;er was a
Iustice of &thorn;e contre, &amp; he desyri&dtail; to se &thorn;is
Abbott, and he mot nevur com to at se hy&mtail;.  And &thorn;is iustis
saw &thorn;at, &amp; he garte take &thorn;e sister so&ntail; of
&thorn;is abbott, &amp; sai&dtail; he was a thiefe &amp; putt
hy&mtail; in priso&ntail;, &amp; say&dtail; &amp; &thorn;is abbott
Pastor wol&dtail; co&mtail; vnto hy&mtail; &amp; pray hy&mtail; for
hy&mtail;, he sul&dtail; delyver hy&mtail; hy&mtail;.  And pa&ntail;
&thorn;e moder of &thorn;is childe come vnto &thorn;is abbott
ce&llbar; dure, an&dtail; calli&dtail; &thorn;er-att &amp; besoght
hy&mtail; to speke with hur, &amp; he wolde no wur&dtail; ansswer.
And whe&ntail; sho saw &thorn;att, sho wepi&dtail; &amp; made
meku&llbar; sorow, &amp; say&dtail;; "And &thorn;ou ha&dtail;





<PB N="131">

a harte &amp; bowels of yr&ntail; &amp; mott not be movi&dtail; with
no compassio&ntail;, yit at &thorn;e leste marke, &thorn;ou sul&dtail;
hafe compassio&ntail; of &thorn;ine aw&ntail; blude, &thorn;i sister
so&ntail;."  And &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;is abbott sent wur&dtail; vnto
&thorn;is iustis &amp; say&dtail;; " <FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Pastor filios
non generauit;</FOREIGN> Abbott Pastor gatt nevur chil&dtail;."  And
whe&ntail; &thorn;is iustis saw at &thorn;e abbott wol&dtail; not
co&mtail; hy&mtail; selfe &amp; pray for hy&mtail;, he sai&dtail; &amp; he
wol&dtail; send wur&dtail; for hy&mtail; be mowthe he sul&dtail;
sen&dtail; hy&mtail; hy&mtail;.  And &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;is Abbott
sent hy&mtail; wur&dtail; &amp; say&dtail;; "Examy&ntail; &thorn;e
cauce as &thorn;e law wy&llbar;, &amp; if he be wurthi to dye lat
hy&mtail; dy; or els do with hy&mtail; as &thorn;ou plesis."  et
c&curl;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CLXXXIX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Consciencia bona frequenter timet
<NOTE ID="P131.N1">The Latin MSS. <HI REND="i">conclude</HI>, vbi non est timendum.</NOTE>.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Historia Tripartita,' &thorn;at o&ntail; a tyme
whe&ntail; Iulianus Apostata at a grete ffeste tyme, in maner as
emperours dose, garte encens be sett befor hy&mtail;, he made
cryste&ntail; me&ntail; to co&mtail; knelyng afor&ntail; hy&mtail;
&amp; serve hy&mtail; &thorn;er-of.  &amp; he gart hide fals mawmettis
vnder-nethe a clothe befo&rtail; hy&mtail;, at &thorn;e criste&ntail;
men sul&dtail; not se &thorn;aim; &amp; &thorn;e cristenme&ntail;
wiste nothyng &thorn;erof.  And whe&ntail; &thorn;is was done, he
garte bare &thorn;ies &amp; told &thorn;e criste&ntail; me&ntail;,
&amp; threpi&dtail; of &thorn;aim at &thorn;ai ha&dtail; done
sacrifice vnto his goddis, &amp; offred &thorn;aim encence.  And
whe&ntail; &thorn;ai harde &thorn;is, &thorn;ai cryed &amp; made
meku&llbar; sorow, and desyri&dtail; at &thorn;er right handis at
&thorn;ai broght it v&ptail; with sulde be cutt off for penance et
c&curl;; &thorn;uff a&llbar; &thorn;ai &thorn;oght not of no sacrifice
vnto fals goddis.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CXC.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Consciencia peccati
<NOTE ID="P131.N2">So Latin MSS. The English version <HI REND="i">has</HI>, peccato.</NOTE> non potest quiescere.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Libro de Dono Timoris,' how o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;er
was a riche ma&ntail;, &amp; he luffid wele to go to sportis &amp; to
grete festis.  So o&ntail; a tyme, as he was be hys ane, hy&mtail;
happen&dtail; to vmthynk hy&mtail; of his synnys, &amp; so he
contynue&dtail;; and his consciens was so gretlie







<PB N="132">

turment &thorn;er-with at he mott hafe no reste.  And
&thorn;erfo&rtail; evur whe&ntail; suche a thoght come in his
myn&dtail;, he wal&dtail; evur ca&llbar; vnto hy&mtail; one of his
neghburs to hal&dtail; a talk with hy&mtail;, &amp; for to putt suche
thoghtis oute of hys mynde.

</P>
<P> <LIST><ITEM> <FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Consecracio ecclesie.  Infra de
dedicacione.</FOREIGN></ITEM>


</LIST></P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CXCI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Consilio bono est acquiescendum.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede how o&ntail; a tyme ane archer gatt a little bur&dtail;
&thorn;at is calli&dtail; a nightgale, &amp; he gatt oute his knyfe
&amp; wol&dtail; hafe slane hur.  &amp; &thorn;a&ntail; sho spakk vnto
hy&mtail; &amp; say&dtail;; "&thorn;ou ma&ntail;! whatt may my dede profett
&thorn;e?  For &thorn;ou may not fy&llbar; &thorn;i body with me, bod
&amp; &thorn;ou wi&llbar; latt me go, I sa&llbar; gif &thorn;e for my
rawnso&ntail; iij wisdoms, whilk &amp; &thorn;ou kepe, sa&llbar; be
grete profett vnto &thorn;e."  And whe&ntail; he har&dtail; hur speke
he was gretelie astony&dtail;, &amp; say&dtail; &thorn;at &amp; sho
cuthe te&llbar; hy&mtail; any new &thorn;ingis at mot profett
hy&mtail;, he sul&dtail; latt hur go a&llbar; redie; &amp; sho
essuri&dtail; hy&mtail; at sho sul&dtail;.  And as for &thorn;e furste,
sho bad hy&mtail; neuer to desyre to gett &thorn;at &thorn;ing at the
myght not gett; and make not sorow for &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at
is verely loste &amp; ca&ntail; neuer be requover&dtail;; and as for
&thorn;e thri&dtail;, "Gyff not truste vnto euerilk wur&dtail; at
&thorn;ou heris."  And &thorn;is done he lete hur fle &thorn;er sho
wol&dtail;; and sho gatt hur vp into a tre &amp; &thorn;oght sho
wal&dtail; witt whe&thorn;er &thorn;ies wisdoms sulde tur&ntail;
hy&mtail; vnto any profett or nay.  And sho sai&dtail; vnto hy&mtail;;
"A! wo be vnto &thorn;e! for &thorn;ou hase ha&dtail; &thorn;is day
ane i&llbar; cownce&llbar;; for &thorn;er is with-in my body a precious
stone calli&dtail; a Margarite, &thorn;at is of grete vertue,
an&dtail; it is more &thorn;a&ntail; ane egg."  And whe&ntail; he
har&dtail; &thorn;is, he made meku&llbar; sorow at he had latty&ntail;
hur go, &amp; desyri&dtail; hur to co&mtail; agay&ntail;, &amp; made
a&llbar; &thorn;e crafte att he cuthe to gett hur.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; sho sayd vnto hy&mtail;; "Now I know &thorn;at
&thorn;ou erte bod a fule.  I bod &thorn;ou sul&dtail; not make sorow
for &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at was loste and irrecouerable, &amp;
I bad &thorn;ou sul&dtail; not be besy to labur for &thorn;at
&thorn;ing at &thorn;ou may nott gett, &amp; &thorn;ou makis mekil
<NOTE ID="P132.N1">MS. mekis.</NOTE> sorow at &thorn;ou hase loste me, &amp; laburs
to gett me agay&ntail;, &amp; I wi&llbar; not co&mtail; att &thorn;e.
And I bad &thorn;ou sulde not trow euer-ilk wur&dtail; att



<PB N="133">

&thorn;ou har&dtail;, &amp; &thorn;ou trowis at &thorn;er be in my bodye a
precious stone mo&rtail; &thorn;a&ntail; ane egg; &amp; a&llbar; my
bodie is nott so meku&llbar; as halfe ane egg.  And &thorn;erfo&rtail;
as I fan&dtail; &thorn;e a fule, so wi&llbar; I lefe &thorn;e."  &amp;
with &thorn;at sho flow away syngan&dtail; &thorn;ies ij versys; "
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Non nimis amissis doleas, nec omne quod audis
credas, nec cupias id quod habere nequis.</FOREIGN>"


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CXCII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Consilio inhonesto eciam si sit vtile, non est
adquiescendum.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Tullius tellis how som tyme &thorn;er was a ma&ntail; &thorn;at
hight Themistenes, &amp; o&ntail; a tyme he tol&dtail; vnto &thorn;e
me&ntail; at dwelte in Athens &thorn;at he cuthe te&llbar; &thorn;aim
a cownce&llbar; &thorn;at war for &thorn;er commo&ntail; profett.  Bod
he sai&dtail; &thorn;at it was noght necessarie &thorn;at a&llbar;
me&ntail; sul&dtail; witt it, &amp; &thorn;erfo&rtail; he
desyri&dtail; &thorn;aim at he myght hafe ane to te&llbar; it to.  And
&thorn;ai assigne&dtail; hy&mtail; a ma&ntail; &thorn;at hight
Aristes, and he tol&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp; say&dtail;: "A grete
shy&ptail; of Lacedonye is comme&ntail; vnto &thorn;e have&ntail;; and
it wer ane ethe &thorn;ing &amp; a profitable to men of &thorn;e cetie
to go &amp; take oute a&llbar; &thorn;e riches &thorn;er-of."  And
whe&ntail; &thorn;is Aristes har&dtail; &thorn;is, he went to &thorn;e
cownce&llbar; in-to &thorn;e cetie &amp; tol&dtail; &thorn;aim
&thorn;at he had har&dtail; a profitable cownce&llbar;, bod it was
nowder treut&hbar; nor honestie; and &thorn;erfo&rtail; he say&dtail; he 
wol&dtail; not concent &thorn;erto.

</P>
<P>
