<PB N="134">

</LIST></P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CXCIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Consolacio diuina cor ad se totum attrahit et
replet dulcedine.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Jacobus de Vetriaco tellis of <NOTE ID="P134.N1">Harl. MS. de sancta Maria de Ogniez.  Arund. MS. de sancta Maria de Origine.  This English version is entirely corrupt.</NOTE> our ladie
Saynt Marie, &thorn;at whe&ntail; sho norisshi&dtail; hy&mtail; in his
youthe&dtail; and sho had lige&ntail; with hy&mtail; iij dayes in bed
laykan&dtail;, hur wol&dtail; hafe &thorn;oght it bod ane hour; &amp;
sho wol&dtail; layke so long with hy&mtail; at he wol&dtail; be bathe
hon[g]rie and threstie.  And ay &thorn;e hongreer &amp; &thorn;e
thristier at he was, &thorn;e more sho desyri&dtail; to hal&dtail;
hy&mtail; in hur armys; and if he wol&dtail; hafe bene furt&hbar;, sho
wol&dtail; cry &amp; hol&dtail; hy&mtail; sti&llbar; betwix hur armys.
And so&mtail; tyme sho wol&dtail; bere hy&mtail; in hur armys iij
dayes, &amp; kis hy&mtail; &amp; play with hy&mtail; in dyvers placis,
becauce sho had so meku&llbar; comfort&hbar; of hy&mtail; in hur
harte; for als meku&llbar; as sho knew &thorn;at he was bothe verray
God &amp; ma&ntail;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CXCIV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Consolacio diuina debet precibus
impetrari.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Libro de Dono Timoris' of a womma&ntail; &thorn;at was
devowte; &amp; o&ntail; a tyme whe&ntail; sho wanty&dtail;
comfurt&hbar; at sho was wunte vnto, &amp; was fer&dtail; at it
sul&dtail; tary lang or it come, &amp; whe&ntail; at it war
comme&ntail; at it sul&dtail; sone pas away, and sho spakk vnto hur
aw&ntail; vertues at was with-in hur &amp; say&dtail;; "My faythe! go
&thorn;ou vnto my Lor&dtail; Go&dtail;, &amp; charge Hy&mtail;
be a&llbar; &thorn;e articles &thorn;at er trowe&dtail; in Hy&mtail;
&thorn;at He co&mtail; vnto me &amp; comfurt&hbar; me.  &amp; my
mynde!  Be &thorn;ou His hoste, &amp; orda&ntail; for his herberie.
And my luff!  Luke &thorn;ou make Hy&mtail; gude chere.  And my
charitie!  It acordis to &thorn;e to hol&dtail; Hy&mtail; sti&llbar;,
at He pas not away."  And whe&ntail; sho had &thorn;us chargi&dtail;
a&llbar; hur vertues, onone sho was putt in a mervalos grete
comfurt&hbar;, at contynued with hur lang &amp; recedi&dtail; noght
away fro&mtail; hur.

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Consolatur Deus <NOTE ID="P134.N2">So the Latin MSS.  The English MS. <HI REND="i">has</HI>, Consolatur Deus in aliquo in aliquo sacramento, &amp;c.</NOTE> aliquos in
sacramento altaris.  Infra de sacramento. j.</FOREIGN></ITEM>


<PB N="135">


<ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Consolacionem recipiunt aliquando sancti creaturis

vel factis.  Supra abbatis vi <NOTE ID="P135.N1">MS. ij.</NOTE> et infra de

