<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CXCVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Consuetudo peccandi minuit timorem.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Gregur tellis how &thorn;er was o&ntail; a tyme a ma&ntail;
&thorn;at opo&ntail; &thorn;e Pasc&hbar;-evy&ntail; corrupte a
maydy&ntail;.  So opo&ntail; &thorn;e mor&ntail; he was fer&dtail; for
to go into &thorn;e kur&ktee;, att &thorn;e devu&llbar; sul&dtail;
hafe no power of hy&mtail;.  Not-withstondyng, at &thorn;e laste he
went in for shame with a grete ferdnes.  And so he di&dtail; o&ntail;
&thorn;e secun&dtail; day, &amp; was les fer&dtail;; &amp; o&ntail;
&thorn;e iij day he was leste fer&dtail; of a&llbar;.  And &thorn;us
he di&dtail; vnto vij dayes was passid, and &thorn;a&ntail; he was
nothyng fer&dtail;, &amp; wol&dtail; not shryfe hy&mtail; &thorn;erof.
&amp; onone after he dye&dtail; a sodan dea&dtail;.  And whe&ntail; he
was lai&dtail; in his grafe, &thorn;er come sodanlie a grete low into
his grafe &amp; burny&dtail; ewhils &thorn;er was lefte a morce&llbar;
of hys bodie to bur&ntail; opo&ntail;, &amp; to it was clene
wasti&dtail;.

</P>
