<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Continens debet [motus]
<NOTE ID="P141.N1">Latin and English MSS. <HI REND="i">have</HI> homo <HI REND="i">instead of</HI> motus.</NOTE> sensualitatis et complexionis
naturalis reprimere.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cassianus tellis &thorn;at whe&ntail; Socrates &thorn;e
philosophur be complexio&ntail; off his bodye was disposi&dtail; vnto
many synys, so o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;er was a ma&ntail; &thorn;at
behel&dtail; hy&mtail; ons, &amp; say&dtail; he had &thorn;e ee&ntail;
of child&rtail; body.  And Socrates disciples &thorn;oght &thorn;ai
wol&dtail; bete hy&mtail; for &thorn;e skor&ntail; he gaff &thorn;er
maister; and &thorn;er maister wulde not latt &thorn;aim, bod garte
&thorn;aim lefe &amp; do hy&mtail; no skat&hbar;; "for it is with me
as he sai&dtail;, bod I with-draw me fro &thorn;at at I a&mtail;
desposi&dtail; to."

</P>
<P>
