<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Conuercio.  Conuerti facit peccatorem aliquando
consideracio perpetuitatis pene infernalis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Fulco <NOTE ID="P147.N1">Arund. MS. Fulco Marsilensis: episcopus Tholosamus.  Harl. MS.  Fulco Marsilione: episcopus Tholosanus.</NOTE> telles how &thorn;at Marciliensis
&thorn;at was bisshopp of Tholosa&ntail; tol&dtail; of hy&mtail;
selfe; "whe&ntail; I was yong &amp; giffe&ntail; vnto vanyties of
&thorn;is werl&dtail;, I bega&ntail; ans sodanlie [to think] of
&thorn;e evurlastyngnes of &thorn;e pay&ntail; of he&llbar;, an&dtail;
I sai&dtail; in my harte; `and it war putt vnto &thorn;e to lig alway
in a softe be&dtail; &amp; a delicatt, so &thorn;at in no maner of
wise &thorn;ou sulde pas oute &thorn;erof, and &thorn;ou might not
suffer &thorn;att, how may &thorn;ou &thorn;erfo&rtail; sustene in
&thorn;e euerlastan&dtail; bitter pay&ntail; of he&llbar;, if it
happe&ntail; &thorn;e to be dampny&dtail; thedur?'  And be &thorn;is
occasio&ntail; I lefte a&llbar; &thorn;ingis and made me a monke."


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCXI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Conuerti eciam facit peccatorem consideracio
acerbitatis pene inferni.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in `Libro de Dono Timoris,' how &thorn;at &thorn;er was a
yong ma&ntail; &thorn;at was riche and delicate, and he made hy&mtail;
a freer prechur.  And his frendis come vnto hy&mtail; &amp; wol&dtail;
hafe had hy&mtail; oute of his ordur; and &thorn;ai sai&dtail; vnto
hy&mtail; &thorn;at he myght not suffer &thorn;e austeritie of his
ordur. &thorn;a&ntail; he vmthoght hy&mtail; &amp; sai&dtail; vnto
hy&mtail; selfe; "The bitter pay&ntail; of he&llbar;, &thorn;at is
vntollerable vnto me, and &thorn;erfo&rtail; I hafe chosy&ntail; me
rather to suffyr &thorn;is pay&ntail; &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;att."

</P>
<P>
<LIST><ITEM>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Conuersus ad[d]iscens litteras efficitur peruersus.

