<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCXII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Conuerti eciam facit aliquando peccatorem
consideracio mortis subite.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in `Libro de Dono Timoris,' how som tyme &thorn;er was a
noble clar&ktee; &thorn;at was a grete baro&ntail; so&ntail;; and he
went &amp; made




<PB N="148">

hy&mtail; a freer prechur.  And whe&ntail; his fadur har&dtail;
te&llbar; of &thorn;is, he vmthoght hy&mtail; &thorn;at he wol&dtail;
dryfe &thorn;ase freers oute of &thorn;e lan&dtail;, &amp; take his
so&ntail; fro emang &thorn;aim.  And whe&ntail; &thorn;e freers
har&dtail; te&llbar; of &thorn;is, &thorn;ai a&llbar; samen went vnto
&thorn;is baro&ntail; with a&llbar; &thorn;e mekenes att &thorn;ai
cuthe, and tol&dtail; hy&mtail; &thorn;at &thorn;ai tuke not his
so&ntail; &amp; made hy&mtail; freer in violent, bo&dtail; he
offer&dtail; hy&mtail; &thorn;erto o&ntail; his aw&ntail; gude
wi&llbar;.  And he sai&dtail; &thorn;ai sai&dtail; wrang, &amp;
&thorn;at he sulde prufe &amp; evur he myght mete with his so&ntail;.
And so &thorn;ai lete his fadur &amp; hy&mtail; speke samen, &amp; he
trowe&dtail; &thorn;at onone with a wur&dtail; he sulde averte his
purpos.  And he sai&dtail; vnto hy&mtail; o&ntail; &thorn;is maner of
wise; "So&ntail;, &thorn;ou hase husely trubled me becauce &thorn;ou
hase made &thorn;e a freer.  Bod not forthi, &amp; &thorn;ou wi&llbar;
lefe &thorn;ine ordur &amp; go home with me, I sa&llbar; forgiff
&thorn;e a&llbar;."  And &thorn;is yong freer ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail;
agay&ntail; &amp; say&dtail;; "Fadur, I wu&llbar; nott go home with
you bod if ye wu&llbar; beheste me &thorn;at ye sa&llbar; fordo ane
i&llbar; custo&mtail; &thorn;at is within your
lor&dtail;-schu&ptail;."  And his fadir sai&dtail; he sul&dtail; do
what att evur hy&mtail; plesi&dtail; to by&dtail; hy&mtail; do, and
bad hy&mtail; te&llbar; hy&mtail; what &thorn;is custo&mtail; was.
And &thorn;is yong freer sai&dtail; it was &thorn;is, thatt als sone
dyes a yong ma&ntail; as ane olde ma&ntail;.  And whe&ntail; his fadur
har&dtail; &thorn;is, he tuke a grete compunccio&ntail; in his harte
&amp; lete hy&mtail; alone with &thorn;e freers, and went home
agay&ntail;, and nevur desiri&dtail; hy&mtail; after.  et c&curl;.

</P>
