<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCXXXII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Cruce signatam vestem inter flammas illesam
deus custodit.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how att &thorn;e cetie of Susas &thorn;er was a
cetysy&ntail; at was merki&dtail; with &thorn;e cros.  And in &thorn;e
mene-while, or he went



<PB N="162">

furt&hbar;, happen&dtail; his howse to be burny&dtail;, &amp; a&llbar;
his other gudis safeyng onelie als meku&llbar; of a garment of his as
&thorn;e cros &thorn;at he ha&dtail; take&ntail; was sewi&dtail;
opo&ntail;, &amp; &thorn;at was fo&ntail; vnbyrny&dtail; emang
&thorn;e hate colis.  And a&llbar; &thorn;at saw it had grete mervayle
&thorn;eroff, at &thorn;e cros had so meku&llbar; mervayle &amp;
vertue &thorn;erin. et c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Culpa.  Culpe respondet pena.  Supra de agro,

primo et ij.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Curatus male intrans ecclesiam punitur.  Supra de

blasfemia.  ij.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Curato ecclesie possunt coadaptari multa que dicuntur

infra de prelato et sacerdote.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Custodia.  Custodire debet homo sensus suos.

Supra de aspectu.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Custodiri non potest mulier.  Infra de muliere.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dampnacio.  Dampnatur homo qui toto tempore vite

sue sancte vixit, quia finaliter peccauit.  Supra

de carnis temptacione.   3.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dampnati non iuuantur orationibus viuorum.  Infra

