<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dampnatis non prosunt suffragia.  Infra de

suffragijs.   3.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dampnatus ab inferis ex speciali gratia reuocatur.

Infra de oratione ij. et viij.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dampnatis aliquando beata dei genitrix vitam

inpetrauit.  Infra de Maria.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dampnum.  Dampnificare proximum nemo debet

rebus suis.  Supra de columbis.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dampnum debet restitui dampnificato.  Infra de

restitucione.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dari non debet hostia non consecrata loco eukaristie.

Infra de eukaristia et infra de oratione.  ij.</FOREIGN>


<PB N="163">
</ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dacio siue donum.  Dare non debet vxor sine licencia

viri.  Infra de muliere.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dare debent principes liberaliter.  Infra de

liber[ali]tate.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCXXXIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Dant sancti res et corpus suum pro deo.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Gestis Serapionis Abbatis' how &thorn;at &thorn;is
Serapio&ntail; apo&ntail; a day gaff his amett vnto a pure ma&ntail;,
and it was cal&dtail; weddur; &amp; he mett a noder pure ma&ntail;,
&amp; he gaff his cote.  And &thorn;a&ntail; he was nere-han&dtail;
naki&dtail;; and he sett hy&mtail; dow&ntail; and ane evangi&llbar; in
his han&dtail;.  And &thorn;a&ntail; one of his brether come vnto
hy&mtail; &amp; say&dtail;; "Abba, who hase robbe&dtail; you?"  And he
shewi&dtail; &thorn;e euaungy&llbar; &amp; say&dtail;; "this hase
robbi&dtail; me."  And with-in a while after he sol&dtail; &thorn;is
euaungi&llbar;, &amp; gaff &thorn;e price &thorn;er-of vnto pure
me&ntail;.  So o&ntail; a tyme his disciple aski&dtail; hy&mtail; whar
it was, and he say&dtail;; "I hafe sol&dtail; it &amp; giffe&ntail; it
vnto pure men, becauce it says: <FOREIGN LANG="LAT">'vende que habes
et da pauperibus.'</FOREIGN>" So o&ntail; a tyme afterwar&dtail;
&thorn;er come a wedow vnto hy&mtail; &amp; aski&dtail; hy&mtail;
so&mtail; almos, for sho sai&dtail; sho had nowder meate nor
dryn&ktee; to hur nor hur childer.  And becauce he had no thyng to
giff hur, he gaff hur his aw&ntail; selfe, &amp; bad hur se&llbar;
hy&mtail;; &amp; so sho did vnto a lorde of Grece lan&dtail;.  And
with-in a while fro he had bene &thorn;er, he conuerti&dtail; a&llbar;
&thorn;at contret&hbar; &amp; made it cristen&dtail;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dari semper debet elemosina.  Infra de Elemosina.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Data pauperi elemosina datur deo.  Infra de

elemosina, et de Gregorio ij, et supra de Abbate.  iiij.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dona excecant oculos iudicum.  Supra de balliuo.  iiij.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>
</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>CCXXXIV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Debitum cito debet solui alioquin debitor dampnum
incurrit.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Petrus Alphonsus <NOTE ID="P163.N1">MS. Alphensus.</NOTE> tellis how &thorn;er was a
porter of a cetie, and he had be a gifte of &thorn;e kyng of &thorn;at
lan&dtail; &thorn;at ilk ma&ntail; or womma&ntail;



<PB N="164">

&thorn;at come in att his yate, &thorn;at was owder
cruky&dtail;-bakki&dtail;, or skabbi&dtail;, or &thorn;at ha&dtail;
bod one ey, or war in &thorn;e parlesie, or a crepy&llbar;, he sulde
hafe of &thorn;aim a peny.  So o&ntail; a day &thorn;er come in at
&thorn;e yate a ma&ntail; with a crukid ba&ktee;, &amp; he was wele
cle&dtail; &amp; war&mtail;.  And &thorn;e porter aresti&dtail;
hy&mtail; and bad hy&mtail; pay hy&mtail; a peny; &amp; he wol&dtail;
nott.  &amp; &thorn;e porter gatt hy&mtail; be &thorn;e cloke &amp;
lifte vp his hude, &amp; he fan&dtail; &thorn;at he had bod one eye,
and &thorn;a&ntail; he sai&dtail;; "Now &thorn;ou awis me ij d."
&amp; he wol&dtail; hafe bene away, &amp; &thorn;e porter gatt
hal&dtail; o&ntail; hys hude, &amp; it went off, &amp; &thorn;a&ntail;
his hede was skalli&dtail;.  And &thorn;e porter sai&dtail;; "Now
&thorn;ou awis me iij &dtail;."  And &thorn;is ma&ntail; saw at he
mott nott gett away, &amp; bega&ntail; to defen&dtail; hy&mtail;;
&amp; his armys happyn&dtail; bare, &amp; &thorn;ai wer skabbi&dtail;.
And &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e porter say&dtail;; "Now &thorn;ou awis me
iiij &dtail;."  And &thorn;us &thorn;ai wrastel&dtail; to-gedyr, &amp;
&thorn;is ma&ntail; fe&llbar;, &amp; &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;ai mott se
he had a croke&dtail; fute.  And &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e porter
sai&dtail;; "Now &thorn;ou awis me v &dtail;"; and garte hy&mtail; pay
itt.  And so it happen&dtail; hy&mtail; &thorn;at wol&dtail; not pay a
peny with his gude wi&llbar;, to pay v &dtail; ageyns his
wi&llbar;. et c&curl;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCXXXV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Debitum debet solui a debitore non petente vel
mortuo.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Seneca tellis of a philosophur &thorn;at hight Pictagoricus <NOTE ID="P164.N1">Arund. MS. Pictagorus.</NOTE> , &thorn;at boght a payr of shone o&ntail; a tyme of
a sho-maker, bod he had not money enog&hbar; to pay for &thorn;aim;
&amp; so he frustid hy&mtail;, &amp; with-in a few dayes, he come
agay&ntail; &amp; calli&dtail; at &thorn;e shomaker dure.  And one
ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail; with-in &amp; sayd; "Wharto losis &thorn;ou
&thorn;i labur?  &thorn;is sho-maker is dede."  &thorn;a&ntail;
&thorn;is philosophur, fro he hard &thorn;is, went home with his
syluer.  So o&ntail; a tyme, whe&ntail; he was be hy&mtail; selfe
&amp; &thorn;oght of &thorn;is syluer, hy&mtail; thoght his conciens
say&dtail; vnto hy&mtail;; "&thorn;ou aw yone ma&ntail; syluer.  Ga
pay hy&mtail; &thorn;at att &thorn;ou aw hy&mtail;."  And he went
agay&ntail; &thorn;erwith, &amp; in at a hole in &thorn;e dure he putt
ma penys &thorn;a&ntail; he aght, and putt away fro hy&mtail; &thorn;e
pere&llbar; of his wi&llbar;, &thorn;att gruchi&dtail; to pay itt.



<PB N="165">

</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCXXXVI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Decepcio.  Decepiuntur aliqui sub simulacione
boni.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in &thorn;e 'Cronicles of Rome,' how &thorn;er was som
tyme in &thorn;e cowrte at Rome a famos cler&ktee; &thorn;at hight
Machomett, and he desyri&dtail; to hafe bene made pope <NOTE ID="P165.N1">Latin MSS. in Romana curia honorem quem cupiebat assequi non potuisset.</NOTE> , &amp; myght not co&mtail; &thorn;erto.  And
herefo&rtail; he wex wrot&hbar;, &amp; went fer &thorn;ens ou&rtail;
&thorn;e se; and &thorn;er, with a symulacio&ntail;, he gadur&dtail;
samen a grete multitude of yong fol&ktee; vnto hy&mtail;, &amp;
tol&dtail; &thorn;aim &thorn;at &thorn;aim bur&dtail; hafe emangis
&thorn;aim a ma&ntail; to gover&ntail; &thorn;aim.  And in &thorn;e
mene-while he vsi&dtail; to putt whete-cornys in his ere, &amp; he
lerny&dtail; a white dowffe to stand opo&ntail; his shulder &amp; take
&thorn;aim oute.  So o&ntail; a day he calli&dtail; his pepu&llbar;
to-geder, &amp; say&dtail; &thorn;aim &thorn;at it was Goddis
wi&llbar; &thorn;at he sul&dtail; be made rewler of &thorn;aim, whame
&thorn;at God shewi&dtail; for be &thorn;e Holie Gaste.  And privalie
&thorn;is dowfe was latty&ntail; go; &amp; onone sho light o&ntail;
Machomett shulder &thorn;er he was emang &thorn;e prese of peple;
&amp; putt hur by&llbar; in his ere, &amp; tuke oute &thorn;e cornys.
And a&llbar; &thorn;e peple at was aboute went at it had bene &thorn;e
Holie Gaste &thorn;at had comme&ntail; fro heve&ntail; and
descende&dtail; o&ntail; hy&mtail;, &amp; tol&dtail; hy&mtail;
&thorn;e wur&dtail; of Go&dtail; in his ere, &amp; what at God wolde
hafe done; &amp; &thorn;us he was made rewler of a&llbar; &thorn;e
Sarracens, &amp; desayvi&dtail; &thorn;aim; &amp; he made &thorn;aim a
law att &thorn;ai kepe yit, whilk &thorn;at is calli&dtail; Machomett
law.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Decipit demon bonos sub specie boni.  Infra de

demone.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Decipitur iudex frequenter si iudicet secundum

apparenciam exteriorem.  Infra de Iudicio

humano.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Decipit vicinus vicinum.  Supra de Adulterio.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Decipiuntur tam boni quam mali per demones

multipliciter.  Infra de demone 
<NOTE ID="P165.N2">MSS. de decem.</NOTE> , et alijs locis.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


<PB N="166">

</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCXXXVII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Decipiuntur aliqui per artem
magicam.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Heraclides tellis how &thorn;at a ma&ntail; of Egipte was
stryke&ntail; in-to a luste with his neghbur wyfe; and he mot neuer
gett hur wi&llbar;.  And he sayd vnto a nygramansyer to make hur to
loff hy&mtail;, &amp; to hate hur aw&ntail; husban&dtail;.  And he
with hys crafte made hur a mere, so &thorn;at hur husban&dtail;,
whe&ntail; he waken&dtail; in his be&dtail;, he fan&dtail; hur a mere
lygan&dtail; by hy&mtail;.  And whe&ntail; he spak vnto hur sho
wol&dtail; giff hy&mtail; none ansswer.  And he fechi&dtail; prestis
&amp; lete &thorn;aim se, &amp; ledd hur vnto &thorn;e wu&dtail; as
sho ha&dtail; bene a beste.  And he went vnto &thorn;e ce&llbar; of
Saynt Machari with hur; and &thorn;e monkis blamy&dtail; hy&mtail;
becauce he come vnto &thorn;er monasteri with a mere.  And he
tol&dtail; &thorn;aim at sho was his wife, &amp; at sho was
forshapy&ntail; in his bed vnto a mere, &amp; how att &thorn;at iij
dayes he had ety&ntail; no meat.  And Saynt Macharie wiste
&thorn;er-of wele enog&hbar; be a reuelacio&ntail;; &amp; his
bretherin went &amp; tol&dtail; hy&mtail;.  And he come vnto
&thorn;aim &amp; say&dtail;; "Ye er bathe as hors, &amp; hase hors
ee&ntail;.  And hur &thorn;is is a womma&ntail;, &amp; sho is not
transfigur&dtail; into &thorn;e lyknes of a hors bod vnto &thorn;er
sightis &thorn;at may be begyli&dtail; with vanyte syght."  And he
made his prayers &amp; kest hali watir o&ntail; hur &amp; onone sho
was a womma&ntail; agay&ntail;. &amp; &thorn;a&ntail; he garte
refress&hbar; hur with meatt &amp; dryn&ktee;, &amp; bad hur go home
with hur husban&dtail;; and at sho sulde euer whils sho liffi&dtail;
say hur prayers &amp; daylie here mes.  For he sai&dtail; sho
suffer&dtail; all &thorn;is becauce &thorn;e space of v wekis sho
nowder har&dtail; dyvyne serves nor mes.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Decipiens prius aliquem 
<NOTE ID="P166.N1">MS. aliquando, Harl. MS. aliquem.</NOTE>  postea quandoque ab eo

decipitur.  Infra de vindicta et de muliere.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCXXXVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Deceptor aliquando in actu decepcionis decipitur et
forte ab eo quem decipere volebat.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Petrus Alphonsus <NOTE ID="P166.N2">MS. Alphensus.</NOTE> tellis how o&ntail; a tyme
ij burges went o&ntail; a fer pylgramege, and &thorn;er went with
&thorn;aim a husband-ma&ntail;;





<PB N="167">

and &thorn;ai made &thorn;aim felows in &thorn;er vitals.  And
whe&ntail; &thorn;er vita&llbar; was nerehan&dtail; gane so at
&thorn;aim was left bod a little flow&rtail;, &thorn;e burges
say&dtail;, tone of &thorn;aim vnto &thorn;e toder; "we hafe bod litle
brea&dtail;, &amp; ou&rtail; felow etis myki&llbar;."  And &thorn;ai
ij tuke in cownce&llbar; to-gedur at &thorn;ai sulde take &thorn;is
flow&rtail; &amp; make it a&llbar; in a lafe &amp; sethe itt; and
ewhils it wer in sethyng &thorn;ai sulde lay &thorn;aim dow&ntail;
&amp; slepe.  And whilk of &thorn;aim iij dremy&dtail; &thorn;e
mervolest dreme sul&dtail; hafe &thorn;is lafe &amp; ete it a&llbar;
be his one.  And &thorn;us &thorn;ai feny&dtail; to begyle &thorn;is
husband-ma&ntail;.  And &thorn;ai made &thorn;er counan&dtail;, &amp;
&thorn;is husban&dtail; consenti&dtail;; &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;ai
made &thorn;is lafe &amp; put it to sethyng, &amp; lay&dtail;
&thorn;aim to slepe.  And &thorn;is husban&dtail; purseyvi&dtail;
&thorn;er suteltie, &amp; ewhils &thorn;ai wer slepan&dtail; he tuke
&thorn;is lafe halfe-sode&ntail; &amp; eete it &amp; lai&dtail;
hy&mtail; dow&ntail; agay&ntail;.  Tha&ntail; &thorn;ies burges
waken&dtail;, and one of &thorn;aim say&dtail; at he had dremyd a
mervalus dreme; for hy&mtail; thoght at ij angels oppyn&dtail;
hevy&ntail; yatis, &amp; tuke hy&mtail; &amp; ledd hy&mtail;
befo&rtail; a&llbar;myghti Go&dtail;.  And &thorn;e toder say&dtail;
at hy&mtail; thoght &thorn;at ij angels cutt &thorn;e erthe evy&ntail;
in sonder, &amp; led hy&mtail; dow&ntail; vnto he&llbar;.  And
&thorn;is husband a&llbar; &thorn;is tyme lete as he slepi&dtail;
&amp; har&dtail; &thorn;aim we&llbar; enog&hbar;; and &thorn;a&ntail;
&thorn;ai wakken&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp; he starte vp as he had bene
flaye&dtail;, &amp; say&dtail;; "Who is &thorn;at att callis me?"  And
&thorn;ai say&dtail;; "We, &thorn;i felows."  And he ansswer&dtail;
&amp; say&dtail;; "Er ye comme&ntail; agay&ntail; now?"  &amp;
&thorn;ai say&dtail;; "Whethyr went we at we sulde co&mtail;
agay&ntail;?"  And &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e husban&dtail; tol&dtail;
his dreme, &amp; sayde; "Me thoght att ij angels led &thorn;e tane of
you vnto hevy&ntail; &amp; &thorn;e toder vnto he&llbar;.  And I
trowi&dtail; at ye sulde neuer co&mtail; agay&ntail;, &amp; rase &amp;
tuke &thorn;e lafe &amp; eet it."  &amp; &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;ai
luki&dtail; whar it was, &amp; it was gone, et c&curl;.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e tane of &thorn;aim was wrot&hbar; &amp;
say&dtail; &thorn;ai wer begilde; &amp; &thorn;e toder say&dtail; nay,
&amp; say&dtail; " <FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Fallere fallentem non est
fraus.</FOREIGN>" et c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Decipit aliquando discipulus magistrum.  Infra de
vindicta.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Decipit aliquando vxor virum.  Infra de muliere.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
