<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCXLVI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Demon non est incaute nominandus.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Gregorie tellis how a preste &thorn;at hight Stephan
o&ntail; a tyme was wate-shod&dtail;, and necligentlie he
commanddi&dtail; his servan&dtail; &
<PB N="173">

say&dtail;; "&thorn;ou devu&llbar;!  Co&mtail;, doff my shone!"  And
at &thorn;is biddyng onone &thorn;e thwangis of his shone lowsi&dtail;
passand tite.  And whe&ntail; &thorn;e prest feli&dtail; &thorn;is, he
was passan&dtail; fer&dtail; and cried with a grete voyce &amp;
say&dtail;; "&thorn;ou wriche! Go fro me! Go fro me! ffor I spakk not
vnto &thorn;e, bod vnto my servan&dtail;."  And so &thorn;e shone
lefte vndofte vnto his servan&dtail; did &thorn;aim off.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCXLVII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Demones in nocte apparent in formis virorum
et mulierum.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in &thorn;e 'Life of Saynt Germa&ntail;' how &thorn;at
o&ntail; a tyme he was lugi&dtail; o&ntail; a night in a howse vp of
lan&dtail;; and whe&ntail; a&llbar; had suppy&dtail; &thorn;ai sett
&thorn;e burde agay&ntail;.  And he had mervayle &thorn;erof and
aski&dtail; for wha&mtail; &thorn;ai did so.  &amp; &thorn;ai
tol&dtail; hy&mtail; &thorn;ai <NOTE ID="P173.N1">MS. &thorn;at.</NOTE> sett &thorn;e
bur&dtail; for &thorn;ase gude womme&ntail; &thorn;att gase o&ntail;
nyghtis.  And he thoght &thorn;at he wol&dtail; se whatt &thorn;ai
wer, &amp; awaki&dtail; a&llbar; &thorn;at nyght.  And aboute mydnyght
he saw a multitude of fendis co&mtail; to &thorn;is bur&dtail; in
for&mtail; &amp; liknes of me&ntail; &amp; womme&ntail;; and he
chargi&dtail; &thorn;aim remow &thorn;aim, &amp; he calli&dtail;
v&ptail; a&llbar; &thorn;e meneya in &thorn;e howse &amp; shewi&dtail;
&thorn;aim &thorn;ies me&ntail; and &thorn;ies womme&ntail;, &amp;
aski&dtail; &thorn;aim if &thorn;ai knew any of &thorn;aim.  And
&thorn;ai sai&dtail; at &thorn;ai knew &thorn;aim wele enog&hbar;,
&thorn;ai wer a&llbar; &thorn;er neghburghs, bothe me&ntail; &amp;
wyvis.  And he sent vnto &thorn;er howsis at &thorn;ai say&dtail; war
&thorn;er, &amp; &thorn;ai &thorn;at went fand &thorn;aim in &thorn;er
beddis.  And &thorn;a&ntail; he coniuri&dtail; &thorn;ies fendis,
&amp; &thorn;ai tol&dtail; how &thorn;ai war fendis &amp; come to
dissayfe &thorn;e peple.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Demon eciam religiosos retrahit ab oratione.  Supra

