</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCLXVI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Deuotos sibi eciam in celo sancti
remunerant.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how &thorn;er was so&mtail; tyme a chylde
&thorn;at kepi&dtail; shepe of a wedous, and he had a grete
deuocio&ntail; vnto Saynt Nicholas,



<PB N="186">

vnto so meku&llbar; at halfe &thorn;e meatt at he had euere day, he
wol&dtail; dele it vnto pure me&ntail; in wurshu&ptail; <NOTE ID="P186.N1">MS. <HI REND="i">repeats</HI>, in wurshu&ptail;.</NOTE> of Saynt Nicholas; &amp; euer he made his prayers
vnto hy&mtail;.  So o&ntail; a tyme Saynt Nycholas aperi&dtail; vnto
hy&mtail; in habett &amp; lyknes of a fayr olde ma&ntail;, and bad
hy&mtail; dryfe hys shepe hame.  And he sai&dtail; his huswyff
wol&dtail; be wrothe &thorn;a&ntail;, for it was ouer <NOTE ID="P186.N2">Harl. MS. quia nimis mane est.</NOTE> tymelie of &thorn;e day.  And &thorn;is Say[nt] <NOTE ID="P186.N3">MS. Say.</NOTE> comman&dtail; hy&mtail; to do as he bad hy&mtail;,
&amp; say&dtail;; "So&ntail;, &thorn;is day sa&llbar; &thorn;ou dye,
&amp; &thorn;erfo&rtail; make &thorn;e redie, &amp; go home &amp; take
&thorn;i sacramentis; ffor I a&mtail; Saynt Nicholas at &thorn;ou hase
bene devote to, &amp; I wi&llbar; rewarde the."  And he went home;
&amp; his dame was wrathe &amp; blamy&dtail; hy&mtail;.  And he
say&dtail; he had myster to co&mtail; home, ffor he mon&dtail; dye
&thorn;at same day And his huswyffe trowe&dtail; &thorn;at he had bene
fon&dtail; &amp; at he had sene so&mtail; &thorn;ing in &thorn;e
fel&dtail;, and praye&dtail; &thorn;e prest to inquere hy&mtail;
&thorn;eroff.  And he tolde &thorn;e preste of a&llbar; his
visio&ntail;, and he tuke his sacramentis of holy kur&ktee; and
dye&dtail;; an&dtail; his saule went vnto hevy&ntail;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Deuotos deus in sacramento altaris confortat.  Infra

de sacramento.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>
</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCLXVII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Deuocio ad Sanctos non debet
impediri.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in &thorn;e 'Meracles of Saynt Nicholas' how o&ntail; a
tyme in a kur&ktee; &thorn;at was of &thorn;e holie cros, &thorn;e
monkis of ane abbay desyri&dtail; &thorn;er priour att he wol&dtail;
suffre &thorn;aim go &thorn;eder o&ntail; Saynt Nicholas <NOTE ID="P186.N4">MS. <HI REND="i">repeats</HI>, o&ntail; Saynt Nicholas.</NOTE> day, at &thorn;ai myght syng &thorn;e storie of
Saynt Nicholas, for &thorn;a&ntail; it was new made; and he wolde not
latt &thorn;aim.  So o&ntail; a nyght after, as &thorn;e prior and
a&llbar; his brether was in &thorn;er beddis, Saynt Nicholas visible
apperi&dtail; vnto &thorn;e priour in a ferdfu&llbar; wyse, and he
drew hy&mtail; oute of his bed be &thorn;e hare, &amp; keste hy&mtail;
apo&ntail; &thorn;e dortur flure.  And he bega&ntail; to syng
&thorn;is ante&mtail;, ' O! pastor
eterne'; and sang it softlie vnto &thorn;e en&dtail;; &amp;
at euere wur&dtail; <NOTE ID="P186.N5">MS. euer ewur&dtail;.</NOTE> he gaff a lass&hbar;, &amp;
sang it with a grete tarying, to so meku&llbar; &thorn;at with his
holie crying he waken&dtail; a&llbar; &thorn;e monkis.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;ai tuke &thorn;er priour &










<PB N="187">

bare hy&mtail; vnto his be&dtail;, &amp; euere yere, fro thens
furt&hbar;, he ba&dtail; hys brether o&ntail; Saynt Nicholas day go
vnto &thorn;at kur&ktee; and syng &thorn;e storie off Saynt Nicholas.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCLXVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Deus omnia videt.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Petrus Damianus tellis how o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;er was a
ma&ntail; &thorn;at stale his neghbur sew; and &thorn;is ma&ntail; at
stale &thorn;is sew was a ma&ntail; &thorn;at luffi&dtail; wele to
herber pure folk.  So o&ntail; a tyme ou&rtail; Lor&dtail;
apperi&dtail; vnto hy&mtail; in lyknes of a pure ma&ntail;; &amp; he
was lang-hari&dtail;, &amp; he praye&dtail; hy&mtail; &thorn;at he
wol&dtail; for charite cutt it shorter.  And with gude wi&llbar; he
welcom&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp; say&dtail; he wol&dtail;, a&llbar; redie;
&amp; he garte hy&mtail; sett hy&mtail; dow&ntail;, &amp; tuke a payr
of sisurs and bega&ntail; to clypp hy&mtail; before.  And in &thorn;e
hynderparte of his hea&dtail; he fan&dtail; ij privay ee&ntail;
lurkan&dtail;; and he had grete merva&llbar; &thorn;erof &amp;
aski&dtail; hy&mtail; whi &thorn;ai war &thorn;er.  And he
ansswer&dtail; &amp; say&dtail;; "I a&mtail; Iesus, &thorn;at seis our
a&llbar; &thorn;is werl&dtail;, and &thorn;ies er &thorn;e ee&ntail;
wha&rtail;-with I saw &thorn;i neghbur sew at &thorn;ou stale, &amp;
slew it &amp; hy&dtail; it in a cafe."  And with &thorn;at he
vanysshi&dtail; away.  And &thorn;is ma&ntail; amendi&dtail; hy&mtail;
&amp; made restitucio&ntail; privalie for hur vnto hy&mtail; att aght
hur, be advice of his confessur.

</P>
<P>     
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Dileccio.  Supra, sicut de amicicia et amore.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>

</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCLXIX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Dionisius.  Dionisij martirium beato Regulo
nunciavit deus.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede how o&ntail; a tyme whe&ntail; bysshop&ptail; Regulus sang
mes, and in hys cano&ntail; he namy&dtail; &thorn;e apostels o-raw,
&amp; &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e martyrs, sodanly he say&dtail;; "
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Et beatis martiribus tuis <NOTE ID="P187.N1">Latin MSS. et beatis Martiribus tuis, Dyonisio, Rustico et Eletherio.</NOTE> ,
Rustico et Eleutherio.</FOREIGN>" And whe&ntail; he had say&dtail; so,
se&ntail; als meku&llbar; as he ken&dtail; &thorn;ies servandis of
Go&dtail; at &thorn;ai war olyfe, he had grete mervale how &thorn;er
namys happen&dtail; so sodanly in his mouthe, &amp; he wiste no
&thorn;ing of &thorn;aim.  And as he was in &thorn;is merva&llbar;,
&thorn;er apperi&dtail; vnto hy&mtail;



<PB N="188">

iij dowffes sittan&dtail; opo&ntail; &thorn;e cros of &thorn;e awter;
and &thorn;ai had &thorn;e namys of &thorn;ies holie martyrs
writty&ntail; with blude o&ntail; &thorn;er brestis.  And onone as he
saw &thorn;at, he vnderstude at &thorn;ies holie saynttis was
martyr&dtail; &amp; putt to dea&dtail;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Discrecio.  Discretus debet esse prelatus.  Supra

de Abbate.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Discretus est a cibo abstinendum.  Supra de Maria.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Disciplina.  Disciplinandi sunt iuuenes ne

