</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCXXXVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Gaudium quandoque nocet corpori.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in &thorn;e 'Storie of Aprocryfattis <NOTE ID="P234.N3">Lat. MSS. Historia Apocriphi.</NOTE> ' of Titus and Vespacya&ntail;, how &thorn;at when
Titus har&dtail; te&llbar; &thorn;at his fadur Vespacia&ntail; was
made Emperour, he was stryky&ntail; with such a ioy and a
comfurt&hbar;, &thorn;at he was shronke&ntail; a&llbar; his synowes
to-gedur in a lumpe, as it had bene with a crampe.  And Iosephus
har&dtail; te&llbar; how he was &thorn;us falle&ntail; seke, &amp;
serchi&dtail; &thorn;e cauce of his sekenes, &amp; &thorn;e tyme at it
tuke hy&mtail; in.  And he conseyvi&dtail; at he tuke it with a
hertelie ioy and a comfurt&hbar; &thorn;at he tuke whe&ntail; he
har&dtail; te&llbar; of &thorn;e sublimacio&ntail; of his fadur.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; he vmthoght how &thorn;at a sekenes may be curi&dtail;
with &thorn;e contrarie, &amp; he garte spur if &thorn;er wa&rtail;
any ma&ntail; &thorn;at Titus was wrothe with, or grevi&dtail;
agay&ntail;, or &thorn;at he wol&dtail; not suffer co&mtail; in his
sight.  And belyfe &thorn;ai tol&dtail; hy&mtail; of one <NOTE ID="P234.N4">Lat. MSS. et erat ibi seruus adeo Tito molestus, ut sine uehementi turbacione nulla tenus in ipsum respicere posset.</NOTE> .  And &thorn;a&ntail; he come to Titus &amp;
say&dtail;; "And &thorn;ou desyre to be hale, &thorn;ou bus
pardo&ntail; &amp; suffer a&llbar; &thorn;aim &thorn;at commys in-to
&thorn;i presens with me."  And Titus grawnti&dtail; at he sul&dtail;
so do.  And Iosephus garte sett a bur&dtail; in &thorn;e chawmer
anence his be&dtail;, and he garte Titus be sett att meatt at &thorn;e
bur&dtail;-end, in a chayr, &amp; he sett &thorn;is servan&dtail;, at
he was so wrothe with, o&ntail; his right han&dtail;, &amp; himselfe
o&ntail; his lefte han&dtail;.  And Titus saw at it was &thorn;is
ma&ntail; at he was wrothe with, &amp; remembre&dtail; hy&mtail;
how &thorn;at he mott say nothyng










<PB N="235">

vnto hy&mtail;; &amp; he was so angre&dtail; &amp; so trubbe&dtail; in
his mynde, vnto so meku&llbar;, &thorn;at he &thorn;at with a
cal&dtail; for ioy was shronke&ntail; to-gedur, &thorn;a&ntail; with a
hete of angrynes hys synos rache&dtail; &amp; lowsi&dtail;.  &amp;
&thorn;us he gatt vp o&ntail; his fete, and was curi&dtail;, &amp;
tuke hys <NOTE ID="P235.N1">MS. hy&mtail;.</NOTE> servan&dtail; vnto grace, &amp;
forgaff hy&mtail; his truspas; &amp; evur after, fro thens furt&hbar;,
he luffi&dtail; &thorn;is Iosephus specialli befo&rtail; a&llbar;
o&thorn;er.

</P>
<P>
