<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCXXXIX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Germani Antissiodorensis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in his Legen&dtail; how &thorn;is Germanus was Duke of
Normundye <NOTE ID="P235.N2"><HI REND="i">For</HI> Burgundye.</NOTE> ; &amp; after-war&dtail; his wyfe, be
&thorn;er bother consent, was made a no&ntail;, and he was made
bisshop&ptail; of Antissiodorensis; &amp; &thorn;ai delte a&llbar;
&thorn;er gudis vnto pure folk.  And he punysshi&dtail; so his bodi
xxx<HI REND="sup">ti</HI> yere to-gedu&rtail;, &thorn;at he neuer eate brea&dtail; of
whete, nor potage, nor salte; nor dranke neuer wyne bot twyce in
&thorn;e yere, att Yole &amp; att Pac&hbar;.  And a&llbar; o&thorn;er
tymys he dran&ktee; watir &amp; wyne to-gedur, and furste he
wol&dtail; eatt assis &amp; fyne barlie brea&dtail;.  An&dtail; nowder
wynter nor sommer he ware no clothe bod hare, &amp; aboue it a cote
&amp; a cowle; &amp; &thorn;ase wolde he neuer doff vnto &thorn;ai war
clene wor&ntail; away.  And his bed was bod of sek-clothe &amp; of
hare, &amp; he had no cod at his hede bod a stone, &amp; he ware bod
seldo&mtail; shone nor gyrde&llbar; aboute hy&mtail;.  And so &amp; he
do nott meracles it is a grete mervayle.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCXL.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Gloriari siue gloria.  Gloriandum non est de delicijs
naturalibus.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Austy&ntail; tellis how &thorn;at Alcibiades <NOTE ID="P235.N3">MS. Abibiades.</NOTE> , &thorn;at was Socrates discipy&llbar;, was a
passan&dtail; fay&rtail; ma&ntail; &amp; a riche, &amp; ane eloquent







<PB N="236">

speker; and here-in he had grete pride.  And whe&ntail; Socrates
purseyvi&dtail; &thorn;is, with his disputacions he provi&dtail;
hy&mtail; bod a wriche &amp; a natura&llbar; fule, so &thorn;at he
garte hy&mtail; wepe for tene.  And &thorn;a&ntail; Tullius sai&dtail;
&thorn;at &thorn;er sulde a myserie and a wrichidnes folow &thorn;e
ioy att he ha&dtail;, &amp; &thorn;at sulde be parti&dtail; in-to ij
fortuns.  And ane sulde be <NOTE ID="P236.N1">MS. <HI REND="i">repeats</HI>, &amp; ane sulde be.</NOTE> &thorn;at he had
riches, favour, and witt at his aw&ntail; wy&llbar;.  And a noder
fortun sulde folow hy&mtail; after-war&dtail;, and &thorn;at sulde be
outelawrie, myserie &amp; hatre&dtail; of &thorn;e contre; &amp; at
&thorn;e laste he sulde hafe a vylans dea&dtail;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Gloriandum non est de virtutibus.  Infra de iactantia.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCXLI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Gloriandum non est de dictis vel factis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Valerius tellis &thorn;at whe&ntail; Sophocles wex ane alde
ma&ntail;, he sent a ma&ntail; of his, at he luffi&dtail;
passan&dtail; wele, vnto a iustyng; and &thorn;er he wa&ntail;
&thorn;e victorie aboue a&llbar; o&thorn;er.  And whe&ntail; he
har&dtail; te&llbar; &thorn;eroff, he tuke so meku&llbar;
comfurt&hbar; &amp; ioy vnto hy&mtail;, &thorn;at evy&ntail; sodanlie
he fe&llbar; dow&ntail; &amp; dye&dtail;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Gloria vana semper est fugienda.  Infra de vanitate.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Gloria vana oritur aliquando ex bonis operibus.

Supra Barnardi.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCXLII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Gloria mundi parum durat.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Esopus in 'Fabulis' tellis how &thorn;er was a hors &thorn;at was
araye&dtail; with a brydy&llbar; of gol&dtail;, &amp; a gay
saddy&llbar;, &amp; he mett ane ass &thorn;at was lady&ntail;; &amp;
&thorn;is ass made hy&mtail; no reuerens, bod hel&dtail; evy&ntail;
furt&hbar; his way.  So &thorn;is prowde hors was wrothe
&thorn;er-with, &amp; sai&dtail;; "Bod at I will not vex my selfe, els
I sulde sla &thorn;e with my hynder fete, becauce &thorn;ou wolde not
voyde &thorn;e way, &amp; giff me row&mtail; to pass by &thorn;e."
And whe&ntail; &thorn;is ass har&dtail; hy&mtail;, sho made
meky&llbar; sorow.



<PB N="237">

So with-in a little while after, &thorn;is hors, &thorn;at was so
gaylie cle&dtail;, was wayke &amp; lene, &amp; had a sare galli&dtail;
bak&ktee;; &amp; &thorn;e ass mett hy&mtail; vndernet&hbar; a carte,
ledan&dtail; muke vnto &thorn;e felde: &amp; &thorn;e ass was fayr
&amp; fatt.  &amp; &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e ass sai&dtail; vnto
hy&mtail;; "Whar is now &thorn;i gay aray at &thorn;ou was so prowde
of?  Now blissi&dtail; be Go&dtail;, &thorn;ou erte put to &thorn;e
same occupacio&ntail; at I vse, &amp; yit my bak is haler
&thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;yne.  &amp; &thorn;erfo&rtail; now &thorn;i gay
gere helpis &thorn;e nott&curl;." et c&curl;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCXLIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Gracie agende sunt deo de omnibus que
videntur.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Helinandus <NOTE ID="P237.N1">MS. Heliandus.</NOTE> tellis how som tyme &thorn;er
was a freer, &amp; he said he saw neuer &thorn;at &thorn;ing bod he
tuke a comfurt&hbar; with &thorn;e sight &thorn;eroff.  And a noder
aski&dtail; hy&mtail; what comfurt&hbar; he ha&dtail; whe&ntail; he
saw a fowle tade?  An&dtail; he sai&dtail;; "yis, als oft sithes as I
se a tade, I vmbethynk me, &amp; thankis Go&dtail; &thorn;at gaf me so
fayr a for&mtail;, &amp; so fayr a liknes as I hafe, lyke His
aw&ntail; selfe, wha&rtail; &thorn;at He myght, and He had wal&dtail;,
hafe made me als fowle &amp; als vglie as a tode is."


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCXLIV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Gregorij Sancti.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede how o&ntail; a tyme, whe&ntail; Saynt Gregur was a
chyl&dtail;, our Lor&dtail; apperi&dtail; vnto hy&mtail;, at his moder
yate, in liknes of a pure shipma&ntail;, and aski&dtail; hy&mtail; his
almos.  &amp; he ha&dtail; bo&dtail; x&dtail; in his purs, &amp; he
gaff hy&mtail; vj&dtail; &thorn;eroff.  And belife after, &thorn;e
same day, he come agay&ntail;, &amp; aski&dtail; hy&mtail; mo&rtail;;
&amp; &thorn;a&ntail; he gaff hy&mtail; &thorn;e toder iiij&dtail;.
And agay&ntail; evy&ntail; he come agay&ntail;, &amp; aski&dtail;
mo&rtail;; &amp; he had no thyng at giff hy&mtail;, bo&dtail; a syluer
dissc&hbar; &thorn;att his moder had giffe&ntail; hy&mtail; potage in,
&amp; &thorn;at he gaff hy&mtail;.  And he was fay&ntail;
&thorn;er-of, &amp; went his wayes &thorn;erwith.  And
efterwar&dtail;, our Lor&dtail; lete hy&mtail; se be reuelacio&ntail;,
&thorn;at Hy&mtail; selfe was &thorn;at shipma&ntail; &thorn;at he
gaff &thorn;at syluer diss&hbar; vnto.

</P>
<P>
