</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCLXXI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Humilitas sola diabolum confundit.
&amacr;.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Vitis <NOTE ID="P255.N1">MS. Vitas.</NOTE> Patrum' how o&ntail; a
tyme whe&ntail; Macharius went furt&hbar; of his ce&llbar;, &thorn;e
devu&llbar; come o&ntail; hy&mtail; with a ley &amp; walde hafe
smety&ntail; hy&mtail;, &amp; he myght noght.  And &thorn;a&ntail; he
cried &amp; sai&dtail;; "Thow Macharie ! Thow fastis o&thorn;er-while,
&amp; I am refresshi&dtail; with no maner of meate; &amp; &thorn;ou
wakis oft-sithis, and I slepe neuer.  And yit &thorn;i mekenes
alonelie ouercommys me."  &amacr;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Humilis verus humilia de se sentit.  Infra de

timore.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Humiliandi sunt iuuenes per disciplinas.  Infra de

iactancia.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Humiliari debet homo ex consideracione sui.  Supra

