oratione et supra de cibo.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Ieronimi.  Infra de leone asini custode.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Ignacij 
<NOTE ID="P259.N2">MS. Ignasij.</NOTE>  martiris  Infra de nomine.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCLXXVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Ignorancia multa mala facit.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> As Helinandus tellis, whe&ntail; <NOTE ID="P259.N3">Harl. MS. Cum Homerus poeta aliquando in quadam insula uenisset, proposuerunt ei naute quamdam questionem facilem.</NOTE> &thorn;e
poett Omerus &amp; many other shypme&ntail; apo&ntail; a tyme war
purposi&dtail; for to co&mtail; in-to ane yle, &thorn;e shipme&ntail;
putt vnto hy&mtail; a light questio&ntail;. et c&curl;.







<PB N="260">
</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>vt supra de confusione. i.</FOREIGN></ITEM><ITEM><FOREIGN>Ignorans clericus aliquando
audacior est quam sciens.  Supra de ceco.</FOREIGN></ITEM><ITEM><FOREIGN>Impedimentum.
Impedit Deus aliquando malos aliquos ne impleant quod facere poterant
vel precogitabant.  Infra de signis.</FOREIGN></ITEM><ITEM><FOREIGN>Impeditur raptor oratione
et compellitur restituere.  Infra de Raptore nocturna.</FOREIGN></ITEM><ITEM><FOREIGN>Impedit
communionem <NOTE ID="P260.N1">MS. communione.</NOTE> pollucio nocturna aliquando.  Infra
de pollucione.</FOREIGN></ITEM><ITEM><FOREIGN>Imperator iudicium sine causa inferre non debet.
Infra de Iudice.  iiij.</FOREIGN></ITEM><ITEM><FOREIGN>Imperator obedire debet prelatis
ecclesie.  Supra de Ambrosio.</FOREIGN></ITEM><ITEM><FOREIGN>Imperator honorare debet personas
ecclesiasticas.  Supra de celare.  ij.</FOREIGN></ITEM><ITEM><FOREIGN>Imperator eciam proprio
filio in iudicio non parcit.  Infra de Iusticia.</FOREIGN></ITEM><ITEM><FOREIGN>Imperatrix per
