<PB N="312">

</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCLVIII. 
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Magdalene precibus filius procreatur et nutritur per

ipsam, et mater a morte eius meritis suscitatur.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede ex 'Legenda Lombardica' how &thorn;e Duke of Marsilie
&amp; his wife &thorn;urg&hbar; techyng and prechyng of Marie
Magdale&ntail; war turnyd vnto &thorn;e fait&hbar; and &thorn;ai had
no chil&dtail;, &amp; &thorn;ai praye&dtail; vnto hur at &thorn;ai
myght hafe a childe.  So his wife happend to be grete with childe, and
Mary Magdale&ntail; marki&dtail; &thorn;aim bothe with &thorn;e cros,
for &thorn;ai desyri&dtail; to see Saynt Petur &thorn;e
apposte&llbar;, &amp; to be enformy&dtail; of hy&mtail; and &thorn;e
wife was grete &amp; wolde nott lefe hur husban&dtail;.  So as
&thorn;ai wer vppo&ntail; &thorn;e se it fe&llbar; a grete storme of
wedur, so meku&llbar; at &thorn;ai a&llbar;, &amp; in specia&llbar;
&thorn;is womma&ntail; with childe, war passynglie trubble&dtail;
&amp; dissesi&dtail;, vnto so meku&llbar; &thorn;is womma&ntail; was
delyver of a childe &amp; dye&dtail;.  &amp; whe&ntail; &thorn;is
childe was bor&ntail; it layti&dtail; after &thorn;e moder pap&ptail;,
&amp; wepid and made grete murnyng.  And &thorn;e fader &thorn;erof
wepid &amp; sai&dtail; vnto hy&mtail; selfe; "Allas, wriche! &thorn;ou
desyri&dtail; a childe &amp; now &thorn;ou hase loste bathe &thorn;e
moder &thorn;erof and &thorn;e childe."  And &thorn;e shipme&ntail;
wolde hafe caste&ntail; hur bodie into &thorn;e see, and hur
husban&dtail; gatt grawnte of &thorn;aim at sho sulde be had to
lan&dtail;, &amp; so sho was; &amp; hur husban&dtail; lai&dtail;
&hbar;ur &thorn;er wappi&dtail; in a manty&llbar; dea&dtail;, &amp;
hur childe whik in hur ar&mtail;.  And &thorn;a&ntail; he sai&dtail;
with grete wepyng; "O &thorn;ou Magdalene!  Wol&dtail; God &thorn;ou
had neuer comme&ntail; vnto Marsilie, and wol&dtail; God my childe had
bene bor&ntail; &thorn;er.  Bod &thorn;at I purchasi&dtail; be the, I
beteche it to God &amp; &thorn;e to kepe."  And so he went vnto
&thorn;e shup&ptail; agay&ntail; &amp; come vnto Rome vnto Saynt
Petur, and tol&dtail; hy&mtail; a&llbar; &thorn;e case.  And Saynt
Petur comforthi&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp; sai&dtail; vnto hy&mtail;
&thorn;at God was of power to tur&ntail; his sorow into ioy.  And he
informyd [hym] in &thorn;e fait&hbar;, and shewi&dtail; hy&mtail;
a&llbar; &thorn;e conuersacio&ntail; of Criste, &amp; &thorn;e placis
of His passio&ntail;; &amp; he went agay&ntail; vnto ship&ptail;.  And
after &thorn;e space of ij yere afterwar&dtail; he landi&dtail; at
&thorn;e same place &thorn;er he lefte his wyfe, and he was war of a
little childe &thorn;er o&ntail; &thorn;e see-bank, playing hy&mtail;
with little stonys, and he had grete merva&llbar; what it was &amp;
went &thorn;erto.  &amp; onone as &thorn;e childe saw hy&mtail; &amp;
had neuer sene ma&ntail; befo&rtail;, he ra&ntail; vnto his moder
breste, &
<PB N="313">

crepi&dtail; vnder-nethe &thorn;e manty&llbar; &amp; hi&dtail;
hy&mtail;.  And whe&ntail; his fadur come at hy&mtail; a lifte
vp&ptail; &thorn;e manty&llbar; &amp; fan&dtail; it was a fayr,
whik&ktee; childe, "O &thorn;ou, Marie Magdale&ntail;!" he
sai&dtail;, "how happy war I if my wyfe war now o&ntail; life &amp;
myght go home with me into myne aw&ntail; contret&hbar;, ffor I knaw
wele enog&hbar; at &thorn;ou, whilk hase nurisshi&dtail; my childe, is
of power to rayse my wife fro dea&dtail; to life, &amp; &thorn;ou
wi&llbar;."  And at &thorn;is wur&dtail; &thorn;e womma&ntail; was
olife &amp; rase vp, and sai&dtail;; "O, &thorn;ou Magdale&ntail;!
&thorn;ou erte of grete merett, whilk &thorn;at in my childyng was
medwife vnto me, &amp; evur syne hase helpi&dtail; me in a&llbar; my
nedis!"  And whe&ntail; hur husban&dtail; har&dtail; hur speke, he was
fay&ntail; &amp; say&dtail;; "Womma&ntail;, liffis &thorn;ou?"  And
sho ansswer&dtail;; "Ya, &amp; I hafe [bene] with &thorn;e in euerilk
place &thorn;er &thorn;ou hase bene."  And sho telli&dtail; hy&mtail;
a&llbar; &amp; fayli&dtail; neuer a wur&dtail;.  And &thorn;a&ntail;
&thorn;ai a&llbar; samen wente hame vnto Marsulie, &thorn;er aw&ntail;
contrey.  And whe&ntail; &thorn;ai come at home &thorn;ai fe&llbar;
o&ntail; kneis befo&rtail; Marie Magdale&ntail; &amp; thanki&dtail;
hur hertelie, &amp; tolde hur a&llbar; how it had happen&dtail;
&thorn;aim.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCLIX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Magdalenam angeli ad celum eleuant.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Legenda Lombardica' how, o&ntail; a day, Marie
Magdaley&ntail; in &thorn;e vij cano&ntail; howris was lifti&dtail; vp
in-to &thorn;e ayre with angels, and with hur bodelie eris sho
har&dtail; glorios sangis of hevynlie companys, &thorn;u[r]g&hbar;
&thorn;e whilk euerilk day sho was fed, &amp; wyt&hbar; &thorn;e same
aungels had in-to &thorn;e ayr &amp; broght dow&ntail; agay&ntail;, so
&thorn;at sho myster&dtail; nor desyri&dtail; no bodelie meat.  So
opo&ntail; a day &thorn;er was a solitarie preste at dwelte bod a
little &thorn;ine, and with his bodelie ee&ntail; he saw how sho was
daylie lifti&dtail; v&ptail; into &thorn;e ayr with angels, &amp;
&thorn;er holde&ntail; ane how&rtail; space, &amp; how angels with
mery sang sett hur dow&ntail; agay&ntail; &thorn;er sho was.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCLX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Magdalena deuotos sibi ad pentitenciam
adducit.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Legenda Lombardica' how &thorn;er was in Flandres a
cler&ktee; &thorn;at hight Stephan, &amp; he fe&llbar; vnto so grete
sy&ntail; &amp; folie

<PB N="314">

so &thorn;at he vsi&dtail; to do a&llbar; maner of folie, bod he
wol&dtail; nowder do nor here nothyng &thorn;at was gude.
Neuer-&thorn;e-les he had grete deuocio&ntail; vnto Marie
Magdaley&ntail;, &amp; wurshuppi&dtail; hur day &amp; fasti&dtail; hur
evy&ntail;, and wol&dtail; go in pylgramege vnto hur grafe.  So
o&ntail; a tyme sho aperi&dtail; vnto hy&mtail; in lyknes of a fayr
womma&ntail;, bod sho had wepyng ee&ntail;, and sho sai&dtail; vnto
hy&mtail;; "Stephan, whi duse &thorn;ou i&llbar; dedis agay&ntail; my
gude merettis?  Whi ert &thorn;ou not movi&dtail; with no
compunccio&ntail; for &thorn;i sy&ntail;?  And I hafe prayed so
hartlie for &thorn;e se&ntail; &thorn;ou had deuocio&ntail; vnto me,
and &thorn;erfo&rtail; rise &amp; forthynke &thorn;e, for I wi&llbar;
not forsake &thorn;e to &thorn;ou be recowncel&dtail;."  And fro thens
furt&hbar; he feli&dtail; so meku&llbar; grace yett in hy&mtail;
&thorn;at he forsuke &thorn;is werl&dtail;, &amp; tuke hy&mtail; vnto
religio&ntail; &amp; shrafe hy&mtail; &amp; did penance, &amp;
lifi&dtail; a gude life &amp; die&dtail; a holie ma&ntail;.  And
whe&ntail; he dye&dtail; Mari Magdaley&ntail; was sene at his dying,
&amp; had his sawle vnto hevy&ntail; in ane ange&llbar; lyknes.

</P>
