</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCLXI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Mansuetus homo ab omnibus diligitur.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in &thorn;e Cronicles how Titus &thorn;e Emperour was
fu&llbar; of a&llbar; vertues, to so meku&llbar; he was calli&dtail;
&thorn;e delitis of a&llbar; mans kyn&dtail;; and &thorn;ai &thorn;att
war convicte of coniuracio&ntail;, he tuke &thorn;aim <NOTE ID="P314.N1"><HI REND="i">After</HI> &thorn;aim, toke, <HI REND="i">erased</HI>.</NOTE> to familiarite &amp; forgaff &thorn;aim, &amp; he
wolde deny nothyng to no ma&ntail; &thorn;at aski&dtail; hy&mtail;,
becauce he wolde at no ma&ntail; went hevylie fro hy&mtail;, &amp;
&thorn;at day hy&mtail; thoght was loste at he gaff no thyng o&ntail;.

</P>
