<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCXCII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Miles devotus reuerenciam facit deo et
sacramentis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how som tyme &thorn;er was a knyght of France.
And he was of suche devocio&ntail;, &thorn;er whare-somevur he saw
Goddis bodye he wolde fa&llbar; dow&ntail; and wurshu&ptail; it, and
it ha&dtail; bene evy&ntail; in &thorn;e myre.  So it happen&dtail;
o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;at he was cled in gude clothes, &amp; he went
into a cetie, and &thorn;e strete &thorn;at he rade in was
passan&dtail; myrye.  And sodanlye hy&mtail; happen&dtail; mete
&thorn;e preste with Goddis body, and onone as he saw itt, he
avysi&dtail; hy&mtail; a while &amp; sai&dtail; vnto hy&mtail; selfe;
"What wy&llbar; &thorn;ou do now?  And &thorn;ou knele dow&ntail; here
&thorn;ou losis a&llbar; &thorn;i gay clothyng.  And if &thorn;ou do
it nott, &thorn;ou erte breker of a helefu&llbar; condicio&ntail; at
&thorn;ou was wunt to vse."  And with &thorn;at, with-oute&ntail;
more, he lighti&dtail; of his hors and sett hy&mtail; dow&ntail; in
&thorn;e myre o&ntail; bothe his knethis, and hel&dtail; v&ptail; his
handis and wurshuppid &thorn;e sacrament.  And our Lor&dtail;,
&thorn;at wurshuppi&dtail; &thorn;aim at wurshuppis Hy&mtail;,
shewi&dtail; &thorn;is meracle &thorn;urg&hbar; his power, at
&thorn;er was not o&ntail; a&llbar; his clothis a drope of <NOTE ID="P335.N2">MS. <HI REND="i">repeats</HI>, of.</NOTE> myre nor a spott of clay.  And whe&ntail; he saw
&thorn;is, he had grete merve&llbar; &amp; lepi&dtail; v&ptail;
vppo&ntail; his hors agay&ntail;.  And evur fro thens furt&hbar;, he
was mo&rtail; comforthe&dtail; in &thorn;e fait&hbar; &thorn;a&ntail;
he was afo&rtail;, and thanky&dtail; Almighti Go&dtail;.

</P>
<P>
