<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCXCIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Miles debet esse constans in prelio et corpus
exponere periculo
<NOTE ID="P336.N1">MS. <HI REND="i">paradiso</HI>; Harl. MS. <HI REND="i">as above</HI>.</NOTE>.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Iustinus tellis of a knyght of Athenes &thorn;at hight Cinigrus
how o&ntail; a tyme whe&ntail; he saw hys enmys had done grete
slaghter, and &thorn;ai gader&dtail; meku&llbar; gude to-gedur &amp;
had it vnto a shi&ptail;, and whe&ntail; &thorn;ai wer a&llbar;
&thorn;erin, he gatt hol&dtail; o&ntail; &thorn;e shi&ptail; &amp;
hel&dtail; it with his right han&dtail; &amp; wol&dtail; not lat
&thorn;aim go.  And &thorn;ai saw &thorn;at, and smate it of.  And
whe&ntail; it was of, he gatt hol&dtail; &thorn;ero&ntail; agay&ntail;
with his lefte han&dtail;, and hel&dtail; it, &amp; &thorn;ai smate it
of.  And whe&ntail; he saw bothe his handis was of, he gatt hel&dtail;
it with his tethe.  And &thorn;us nowder for los of bothe his handis,
nor for no oder hurte at he had, he wolde not lefe, bod faght as he
had bene a wude beste, ty&llbar; att &thorn;e laste &thorn;ai smate
hy&mtail; dow&ntail; &amp; kylli&dtail; hy&mtail;.

</P>
<P>
