</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCXCIV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Minucio.  Minucione aliquando perditur sciencia
prius habita
<NOTE ID="P336.N2"><HI REND="i">Heading supplied from</HI> Harl. MS.</NOTE>.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how som tyme &thorn;er was a clerk &thorn;at was wele
and sufficientlie letter&dtail;.  And o&ntail; a tyme he garte latt
hy&mtail; blode, and





<PB N="337">

whe&ntail; he had ble&dtail; he loste a&llbar; his lettera&llbar;
connyng, right evy&ntail; as he <NOTE ID="P337.N1">MS. <HI REND="i">repeats</HI>, he.</NOTE> had loste
&thorn;aim be blode-lattyng <NOTE ID="P337.N2">MS. blode lastyng.</NOTE> , so &thorn;at he
knew not a lettre nor cuthe not vnderstan&dtail; a latty&ntail;
wur&dtail;; not-withstondyng he was refte no thyng els.  And &thorn;is
he tolde vnto many me&ntail;.  So &thorn;er was a ma&ntail; o&ntail; a
tyme cowncel&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp; sayde, "&thorn;e same day
twelmo[n]th at &thorn;ou was latty&ntail; blude o&ntail;, and &thorn;e
same howre," he sulde lat hy&mtail; blude agay&ntail;, and so
peraventur he sulde gytt agay&ntail; his connyng.  And so he did,
&amp; he requover&dtail; hys connyng agay&ntail; als wele as evur he
had it.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCXCV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Misericordia impenditur inimico crucifixi
amore.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how i&ntail; Duchelan&dtail; &thorn;er <NOTE ID="P337.N3">MS. &thorn;at.</NOTE> was a knyght &thorn;at happend sla &thorn;e fadur of
a noder knyght.  So be chawnce his so&ntail; att was slay&ntail;
happen&dtail; to take hy&mtail; at slew his fadur.  And he drew his
swerde and wol&dtail; hafe take&ntail; hy&mtail; and slay&ntail;
hy&mtail;.  And he fe&llbar; o&ntail; kneis befo&rtail; hy&mtail;
&amp; sai&dtail;; "Sur, I beseke you, ffor His luff &thorn;at dyed on
&thorn;e cross &amp; had mercy of a&llbar; &thorn;is werl&dtail;,
&thorn;at ye wold hafe mercie o&ntail; me now."  And with &thorn;ies
wurdis he was compuncte, &amp; tuke hy&mtail; vp&ptail; &amp; sayde
vnto hy&mtail;; "Loo, in wyrshu&ptail; of &thorn;e holie cros, &amp;
for His sake &thorn;at dye&dtail; &thorn;ero&ntail;, at He may forgyf
me my synnys I forgyff &thorn;e, not alonelie &thorn;e truspas at
&thorn;ou hase done vnto me, bod fro&mtail; hens furt&hbar; I
sha&llbar; be &thorn;i fren&dtail;."  And with &thorn;at he tuke
hy&mtail; abowte &thorn;e nek&ktee; &amp; kyssy&dtail; hy&mtail;.
And with-in a little while after, &thorn;is same knyght burny&dtail;
hy&mtail; with &thorn;e cros &amp; went vnto &thorn;e holie
lan&dtail;.  And whe&ntail; he come at &thorn;e kur&ktee; of &thorn;e
sepulcre of ou&rtail; Lor&dtail;, he went in-to it as other di&dtail;.
And, at a&llbar; folk saw, &thorn;e ymage of &thorn;e crucifix
bowe&dtail; evy&ntail; dow&ntail; &amp; lowti&dtail; vnto hy&mtail;.
And whe&ntail; &thorn;ai at saw vnderstude not vnto whome he di&dtail;
it, &thorn;ai a&llbar; went afor&ntail; &thorn;e rude ilkone after
o&thorn;er.  And itt inclynyd vnto none of &thorn;aim bod vnto
hy&mtail;.  And &thorn;ai axked hy&mtail; what was &thorn;e cauce, and
he tolde &thorn;aim a&llbar; as is afor&ntail; sayd.







<PB N="338">

</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCXCVI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Misericordia dei omnibus est
aperta.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Maister Alexander, &thorn;e bisshop of Myla&ntail;, tellis how
so&mtail; tyme &thorn;er was a scoler off Bolay&ntail;.  And o&ntail;
a nyght as he lay in his bed, hy&mtail; &thorn;oght he was be his one
in a grete felde, &amp; &thorn;er he was war, as hy&mtail; &thorn;oght,
of a grete tempeste, &amp; a huge, of stor&mtail; &amp; evu&llbar;
weddur co&mtail; oute of &thorn;e nort&hbar;.  And he hy&mtail; selfe
was gretelie giffe&ntail; to sy&ntail; and wrichidnes.  So hy&mtail;
&thorn;oght he was fer&dtail; for &thorn;is stor&mtail; &amp; was nere
evy&ntail;, &amp; he ra&ntail; als faste as he myght &amp; gatt
hy&mtail; to &thorn;e tow&ntail;, and come vnto a howse &amp;
knokki&dtail; at &thorn;e dure &amp; prayed &thorn;aim latt hy&mtail;
co&mtail; in.  And a womma&ntail; within answere&dtail; hy&mtail;
&amp; sai&dtail;; "I a&mtail; Rightwusnes att dwellis here, and
&thorn;ou &thorn;at erte nott ri&yogh;twus may nott co&mtail; in
here."  And &thorn;a&ntail; he went vnto a noder dure &amp;
knokki&dtail;, &amp; praye&dtail; &thorn;aim latt hy&mtail; co&mtail;
in.  And one within ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp; sai&dtail;; "I
a&mtail; Trewth at dwellis <NOTE ID="P338.N1">MS. dwellid.</NOTE> here, &amp;
&thorn;ou &thorn;at luffis not trewt&hbar; sa&llbar; not co&mtail; in
here."  And &thorn;a&ntail; he went vnto &thorn;e iij dure, &amp;
knokki&dtail; &amp; praye&dtail; at he mott co&mtail; in, &amp; one
ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail; within &amp; sai&dtail;; "I am Pease
&thorn;att dwelles here, &amp; becauce &thorn;at peas is not to wykkyd
me&ntail;, &thorn;erfo&rtail; &thorn;ou sa&llbar; not co&mtail; in
here, ffor a&llbar; my thothtes er of peas, &amp; not of
affliccio&ntail; nor of dissese.  Bod I cownce&llbar; &thorn;e att
&thorn;ou go vnto my suster &thorn;at dwellis by me att &thorn;e next
howse, &thorn;at helpys a&llbar; &thorn;at er in dissese."  And he
went vnto &thorn;e iiij dure &amp; knokki&dtail;, and a womma&ntail;
ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail; with-in &amp; sai&dtail;; "I a&mtail; Mercye
&thorn;at dwellis here, and if &thorn;ou wi&llbar; hafe me &amp; be
savi&dtail; fro yone grete tempeste, &thorn;ou muste go vnto &thorn;e
howse of &thorn;e freer prechurs in Bolay&ntail; &amp; make &thorn;e a
freer, &amp; &thorn;er &thorn;ou sa&llbar; be savi&dtail;."  And
&thorn;is scoler with &thorn;is wakyn&dtail;, &amp; o&ntail; &thorn;e
mor&ntail; he rase &amp; went vnto &thorn;e freers &amp; tol&dtail;
&thorn;aim a&llbar; his vysio&ntail; &amp; asky&dtail; &thorn;aim
&thorn;e abbett &amp; reseyvi&dtail; it, &amp; liffi&dtail; &thorn;er
many a day &amp; was a gude ma&ntail; &amp; a holie.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCXCVII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Misericordia dei parata est eciam eum
negantibus.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Wee rede in 'Vitis Patrum' how o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;er was a
monke &thorn;at gretelie was tempid, &amp; he went into a strete of
Egip&ptail;; &amp; &thorn;er



<PB N="339">

hy&mtail; happend se &thorn;e doghter of a paynoms preste, &amp; he
axked to hafe hur vnto his wyfe.  And &thorn;is preste wente vnto his
<NOTE ID="P339.N1">MS. our; Harl. MS. deos suos.</NOTE> goddis in his temple, &amp; axki&dtail;
&thorn;aim cownce&llbar; &amp; sai&dtail; &thorn;e monk wol&dtail;
algatis hafe his doghter to wyfe, "whethur sa&llbar; I giff hur vnto
hy&mtail; or nay?"  And &thorn;e fend ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail;
agay&ntail; &amp; sai&dtail;; "Gyff hur not vnto hy&mtail; bod if he
furste forsake his Go&dtail; &amp; his bapty&mtail;."  And he went
&amp; tol&dtail; &thorn;e monk, &amp; he did a&llbar; as he bad
hy&mtail;.  And onone &thorn;er come oute of his mouthe a white duffe,
whilk &thorn;at flow vnto hevy&ntail;.  And &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;is
preste went agay&ntail; and axkid cownce&llbar; att &hbar;is
go&dtail;, and he ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail; agay&ntail; &amp;
sai&dtail;; "Gyff nott yitt &thorn;i doghter vnto hy&mtail;, for yitt
his God helpis hy&mtail;, &thorn;uf a&llbar; he hafe forsake&ntail;
Hy&mtail;."  And &thorn;is preste come agay&ntail; &amp; tolde
&thorn;e monke, and &thorn;is monke made grete sorow &amp; sai&dtail;;
"A, so wo is me!  Loo!  God duse me gude agay&ntail; i&llbar;."  And
be &thorn;e cownce&llbar; of a gude holie olde ma&ntail; he was
shrevy&ntail; and did penance, and adle&dtail; afterwar&dtail; for to
see &thorn;e duffe &thorn;at he had loste commyng agay&ntail; vnto
hy&mtail;, and entred in att his mouthe.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Misericordie dei possunt adaptari multa que dicuntur

supra de contricione et confessione, et alibi.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCXCVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Missa prodest viuis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Gregur tellis how o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;er was a
shi&ptail;-ma&ntail;, &amp; hy&mtail; happend be perisshid be &thorn;e
see.  And he had a gude fren&dtail;, a preste, &thorn;at sai&dtail; a
mes for hy&mtail; &amp; offre&dtail; &thorn;e sacrament for hy&mtail;.
And as &thorn;is preste was at &thorn;e sacryng of his mes, &thorn;is
ma&ntail; come al hole furthe of &thorn;e see, and come vnto &thorn;is
preste and tolde hy&mtail; &thorn;at whe&ntail; he was in &thorn;e se
and alsmoste defayli&dtail;, sodanlie &thorn;er come one vnto
hy&mtail; &amp; broght hy&mtail; a lafe.  &amp; whe&ntail; he had
ete&ntail; itt, onone he was comforthe&dtail; &amp; had strenthe,
&amp; was taky&ntail; vp into a shi&ptail;, &amp; so he was
savi&dtail;. And be his tellyng, &thorn;is preste knew &thorn;at
&thorn;e same how&rtail; at &thorn;e lafe was broght vnto hy&mtail; he
was att mess, &amp; offre&dtail; &thorn;e sacrament for hy&mtail;.



<PB N="340">

</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> CCCCXCIX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Missa iterum et alio modo valet viuis.</FOREIGN>
</HEAD>

<P> Petrus Clunacensis <NOTE ID="P340.N1">MS. Climacensis.</NOTE> tellis &thorn;at in
&thorn;e dioces of Polita&ntail;, in Grece <NOTE ID="P340.N2">Harl. MS. in diocesi Greciopolitana.</NOTE>, &thorn;er was a ma&ntail; <NOTE ID="P340.N3"><HI REND="i">For</HI> men, Latin viri.</NOTE>
&thorn;att wroght in a banke for syluer vre.  And sodanlie &thorn;e
banke fe&llbar; and kyllid a&llbar; &thorn;at was vnder-nethe.  So
&thorn;er was one of &thorn;aim ra&ntail; in-to a corner of &thorn;e
banke and was savi&dtail;, neuer-&thorn;e-les he mott nott gett oute.
And his wyfe, trowyng &thorn;at he was dea&dtail;, euerilk day garte
do a mes for hy&mtail;, and daylie at &thorn;at mes sho offer&dtail; a
cande&llbar; and a lofe of brea&dtail; and a litle pott fu&llbar; of
wyne.  And o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;e devu&llbar; had envy at hur dede,
&amp; daylie iij dayes to-gedur, in a mans liknes, he mett hur and
axki&dtail; hur whedur sho went, and evur sho tolde hy&mtail; &thorn;e
cauce of hur gate.  And he ansswer&dtail; hur agay&ntail; &amp;
sai&dtail;; "Labur not to &thorn;e kurk in vay&ntail;, for &thorn;e
preste hathe done mess."  And so &thorn;ies iij dayes to-gedur sho
ow&rtail;-hippi&dtail; &amp; offir&dtail; nott.  So afterwar&dtail;
&thorn;er happen&dtail; a ma&ntail; grafe in &thorn;e same banke.  And
sodanlie as he wroght, he har&dtail; one speke &amp; say; "Smyte
softelie, for &thorn;er is a grete stone bow&ntail; to fa&llbar;
o&ntail; me."  And &thorn;is ma&ntail; was fer&dtail; with &thorn;is
voyce, &amp; calli&dtail; dyvers folke to here it.  And he grofe
o&ntail;, and belife he harde &thorn;e same voyce.  And with &thorn;at
he wroght o&ntail; &amp; fon&dtail; &thorn;is ma&ntail; &amp; tuke
hy&mtail; oute quyk&ktee;, &amp; axkid hy&mtail; how he liffi&dtail;
&thorn;er so long.  And he tol&dtail; &thorn;aim &thorn;at euerilk
day, outtake&ntail; iij dayes to-gedur, se&ntail; &thorn;e banke
fe&llbar; o&ntail; hy&mtail; was broght vnto hy&mtail; a lofe of
brea&dtail; and a pygg with wyne &amp; a light candy&llbar;.  And
whe&ntail; his wyfe hard &thorn;is sho was passyng gla&dtail;, &amp;
knew verelie &thorn;at he was susteny&dtail; with hur offrand, and at
&thorn;e devu&llbar; begyli&dtail; hur &thorn;ies iij dayes &thorn;at
sho sulde nott gar mes be done, to thentent &thorn;at he wol&dtail;
nott &thorn;e meracle of &thorn;e mes had bene provi&dtail; nor of
&thorn;e sacrament nowther.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Missa prodest defunctis.  Infra de Oculis.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Missam pro defunctis celebrare est vtile.  Infra de

