<ITEM><FOREIGN>Missam omni die audire bonum est.  Supra de

Maria, i 
<NOTE ID="P341.N1">MS. v.</NOTE> , et de decepcione, ij.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> D.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Monachus debet se humiliter habere et neminem
iudicare.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Vitis Patrum' how one &thorn;at hight Iosep&hbar;
axke&dtail; abbott Pastor how he sulde make hy&mtail; selfe a monke.
And he ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail; agay&ntail; &amp; said; "And &thorn;ou
wi&llbar; fyn&dtail; riste bothe in &thorn;is werl&dtail; &amp; in
&thorn;e toder werl&dtail;, in euer-ilk cauce say vnto &thorn;i selfe,
'whatt a&mtail; I?'  And &thorn;a&ntail; sha&llbar; &thorn;ou nevur
dea&mtail; no ma&ntail;."


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Monachus in habitu suo debet mori.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how in an abbay of Ceustus ordur &thorn;er was a
mon&ktee; &thorn;at was gretelie vexi&dtail; with sekenes, &amp; he
doffi&dtail; his cowle &amp; did o&ntail; his skaplorie, and so he
dye&dtail;.  And he was bor&ntail; in-to &thorn;er oratorie, &amp;
&thorn;e monkis bega&ntail; att say &thorn;er psalters for hy&mtail;.
And sodanlie he rase v&ptail; &amp; calli&dtail; &thorn;e abbot vnto
hy&mtail;.  And his brethur war fer&dtail; &amp; ra&ntail; away, &amp;
&thorn;e abbott come vnto hy&mtail;.  And he sai&dtail; vnto &thorn;e
abbott; "Sur, I shryfe me vnto you &thorn;at I dye&dtail;
withowte&ntail; my cowle vppo&ntail; me.  And whe&ntail; I
trowe&dtail; frelie to hafe entre&dtail; into paradice, Saynt Bennett
come vnto me &amp; sai&dtail;; 'Whar is &thorn;ine abbett?  Here may
&thorn;ou nott ente&rtail; withoute&ntail; itt.'"  &amp; one, he
sai&dtail;, axke&dtail; hy&mtail; whatt he was, and he tolde hy&mtail;
&thorn;at he was a monke of Ceustus ordur.  And he sai&dtail;, "'&amp;
&thorn;ou be a monke,



<PB N="342">

wha&rtail; is &thorn;ine abbett?' and with &thorn;at o&thorn;er
&thorn;at was aboute praye&dtail; for me, and &thorn;us I was suffred
co&mtail; agay&ntail; vnto my bodye at I mott resayfe myne abbett of
&thorn;e, and at I mott so be wurthie to entre into paradice."


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Monachus passiones debet reprimere.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede ex 'Dictis Patrum' how &thorn;at abbott Pastor sai&dtail;
in his life; "He &thorn;at is evur compleynan&dtail; sulde nott be a
monke, and he &thorn;at duse i&llbar; for i&llbar; is no monke, and he
that is angrie is nott wurthie be calli&dtail; a monke."  et c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Monachus apostata penitens, et sic moriens, eciam

post mortem habitum recuperauit.  Infra de

voluntate, ij.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Monachus cibaria exquisita comedere non debet.

Supra de gula, v.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Monachus in gestis exterioribus debet omnes
edificare.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Iacobus de Vetriaco tellis how so&mtail; tyme &thorn;er was a
knyght &thorn;at happend in were to take a pure ma&ntail;.  And
&thorn;is pure ma&ntail; prayed hy&mtail; to latt hy&mtail; gone, and
gett his rawso&ntail;.  And &thorn;is knyg[ht] had petie off hy&mtail;
&amp; sai&dtail;; "Whatky&ntail; suertie sha&llbar; &thorn;ou lefe me
for &thorn;i commyng agay&ntail;?"  And he ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail;
&amp; sayd; "I sha&llbar; fynde you God to borg&hbar; &amp; a
cawso&ntail; be myne othe, for other &thorn;ing I may not fynd you."
And &thorn;us he went his ways and selde a&llbar; his lyfelo&dtail;,
and yit he mott nott co&mtail; agay&ntail; at &thorn;e day att he had
poynti&dtail;; and here-fo&rtail; &thorn;is knyght wex passyng
wrot&hbar;.  So o&ntail; a day, as he rode, he was wer of a monke
&thorn;at was passand fatt &amp; rea&dtail;, syttand prowdelie
vppo&ntail; a fayr palfray, and rydyng passand secularelie.  And
&thorn;is knyght ansswer&dtail; to his sweyers

<PB N="343">

&amp; say&dtail;; "Wu&llbar; ye se &thorn;is monke, &thorn;at be his
ordur sulde ride o&ntail; ane ass, hase a better hors &thorn;a&ntail;
I hafe."  And with &thorn;at he rade vnto hy&mtail; &amp; tuke
hy&mtail; be the brydy&llbar;, and aski&dtail; hy&mtail; whose
ma&ntail; he was.  &amp; he sai&dtail; he had no lor&dtail; bod
Almi&yogh;ti God.  And &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;e knyght sayd vnto
hy&mtail;; "Thi lorde is a suertie bo&ntail; vnto me, &amp; I
wi&llbar; att &thorn;ou for hi&mtail; make a sethe vnto me."  And with
&thorn;at he garte hy&mtail; light, and tuke &thorn;e hors fro&mtail;
hy&mtail;.  And with-in a while after come &thorn;is pure ma&ntail;
and broght &thorn;e knyght his rawnso&ntail;, &amp; prayed hy&mtail;
to forgiff hy&mtail; att he kepi&dtail; not his day.  And &thorn;e
knyght wolde nott take his money, bod bad hy&mtail; take it
agay&ntail;; for, he sai&dtail;, his borg&hbar; had payed hy&mtail; for
hy&mtail; &amp; delyver&dtail; hy&mtail;.  And whe&ntail; &thorn;e
pure ma&ntail; harde &thorn;is he was passand fay&ntail; &amp; tuke
his money v&ptail; agay&ntail;, and went home als merie as he mott be
&amp; thonki&dtail; Go&dtail;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Monachus eciam post mortem ab abbate suo est a

peccatis suis absolutus.  Supra de absolucione.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DIV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Monachus in se debet esse magne penitencie, et
leues et dissolutos reprehendere.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> In 'Libro Purgatorio Beati Patricij,' we rede how so&mtail; tyme
&thorn;er was a mon&ktee; &thorn;at entre&dtail; into &thorn;e
purgatorie of Saynt Patrykk, and evur after whils he liffi&dtail; he
had wowndis a&llbar; ffress&hbar; &amp; new, whilk he tuke &thorn;er.
And he was also evur in grete penaunce, and evur whe&ntail; he saw any
yong mon&ktee; lag&hbar; vnmesurable or otherwyse be lewidlie
governy&dtail;, he wold cry &amp; say; "O! wol&dtail; God &thorn;ou
wist whatky&ntail; byttyr pay&ntail; is giffe&ntail; for mysgovernans,
for &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;ou wol&dtail; nowder do nor say as
&thorn;ou dose."  et c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Monachus recuperauit de vacca quod potuit.  Infra

de simplicitate.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Monachus proprietarius in sterquilinio sepelitur.

Infra de proprietate, ij.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>

<PB N="344">

</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DV.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Monialis in omnibus debet esse paciens.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Ambros tellis how &thorn;er was som tyme a gude huswyfe,
&amp; sho besoght ane abbatice at sho wulde graunte hur a no&ntail;
for to dwe&llbar; with hur awhile for recreacion, &amp; sho grauntid
hur one whilk &thorn;at was a gude buxso&mtail;, and was as a servand
in &thorn;e howse, bothe vnto hur and all hur meneya.  &amp; sho
servid hur a&llbar; a yere &amp; grevi&dtail; no creatur in &thorn;e
howse.  So at &thorn;e yere en&dtail; &thorn;is abbatis come &amp;
visit &thorn;is huswyff &amp; &thorn;is no&ntail;.  And &thorn;is
huswyff prayed &thorn;is abbatis to take home hur no&ntail;
agay&ntail;, for, sho sai&dtail;, sho mot wy&ntail; no &thorn;ing by
hur, sho was so pacient and so buxso&mtail; &amp; so servisable in
a&llbar; &thorn;ingis, &amp; wi&llbar; nowder truble hur selfe nor
oder folk.  And sho prayed hur to send hur one at sho myght wy&ntail;
somwhatt bye.  And &thorn;an sho sent hur one &thorn;at was a
maydy&ntail; and vncorrupte, bod sho was debatus &amp; passyng angrie
&amp; euer chidan&dtail;, &amp; alway gruchand agayns hur huswyffe,
&amp; wolde flite with hur and with a&llbar; &thorn;e howse-meneya.
And whe&ntail; &thorn;e yere end was done, &thorn;is abbatice come
agay&ntail; &amp; visitt &thorn;is huswyffe, &amp; &thorn;a&ntail;
&thorn;is huswyfe spak vnto hur &amp; sai&dtail;; "Ye hafe now
giffe&ntail; me a gude no&ntail;, whilk I wol&dtail; &thorn;at neuer
sulde parte with me; ffor I hafe wo&ntail; als meku&llbar; mede be
suffryng of hur inpaciens &thorn;is yere as I loste be &thorn;e
mekenes of &thorn;e toder &thorn;e laste yere."  And so &thorn;is
no&ntail; was with hur a&llbar; hur lyfe.  et c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
