<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DVI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Mors aliquando ex gaudio causatur.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Valerius tellis how som tyme at Tracie &thorn;a&rtail; was a grete fray
with-oute &thorn;e tow&ntail;, and &thorn;er was a wedow had hur
so&ntail; &thorn;er, and a&llbar; was nerehand slay&ntail; &thorn;at
&thorn;er was.  &amp; whe&ntail; wurde come in-to &thorn;e tow&ntail;,
&thorn;is wedow went hur so&ntail; had bene slay&ntail;, &amp;
sodanlie hur happen&dtail; to mete hur so&ntail; in &thorn;e yate,
&thorn;at sho went had bene dea&dtail;.  And sho was passand
fay&ntail; &amp; hawsi&dtail; hy&mtail; aboute &thorn;e nekk, &amp;
kyssyd hy&mtail;, &amp; evy&ntail; furthwith for ioy sho swelte &amp;
was dea&dtail;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DVII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Mors citius prouenit ex gaudio quam ex tristicia.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Valerius tellis how after &thorn;e same fray &thorn;er was a
womma&ntail; in &thorn;e cetie, and message come vnto hur at hur
so&ntail; was dea&dtail;; and scho went home vnto hur howse &amp; was
passand hevye.  So at &thorn;e laste sho sett hur dow&ntail; to mete,
and sodanlie hur so&ntail; come in, and als tyte as sho saw hy&mtail;,
for ioy sho wex evy&ntail; oute of hur mynde.  And so it was mo&rtail;
suffrable vnto hur, &thorn;e sorow of dea&dtail;, &thorn;a&ntail; was
&thorn;e mirthe of life.

</P>
<P>
