<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCLI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Proprietas.  Proprium non debet habere
religiosus.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how som tyme in Pycardye, &thorn;er was ane abbay
of Ceustus ordur, &thorn;er was a lewid mon&ktee;, and hy&mtail;
happen&dtail; fa&llbar; seke







<PB N="435">

and lyke to dye.  And he was shrevy&ntail;, and &thorn;a&ntail;
&thorn;e sacrament was broght to hy&mtail; and he was howsel&dtail;;
and whe&ntail; it was in his mout&hbar; he myght nowder chew it nor
swelow it.  Neuer-&thorn;e-les &thorn;e same day, a little
befo&rtail;, he had ety&ntail; a he&ntail; be his ane.  So hy&mtail;
happend sone for to dye, and whe&ntail; he was dea&dtail; &thorn;er
was fo&ntail; with hy&mtail; v soldi, not of clene syluer bod of
coppur; and he&rtail;-fo&rtail; it was demyd &thorn;at he myght not
ressayfe his sacrament.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Proprium aliquando est causa confusionis religioso.

Infra de simonia, i.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCLII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Proprietarius in sterquilinio sepeliri
debet.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Grego&rtail; tellis how som tyme &thorn;er was a mon&ktee;
in ane abbay, and he was a leche, &amp; he had a noder bruther, monke
in &thorn;e same place.  So hy&mtail; happyn&dtail; fa&llbar; seke,
bow&ntail; to dye, &amp; &thorn;er was fo&ntail; emang his medcyns iij
nobles of gol&dtail;.  And whe&ntail; Saynt Gregur saw &thorn;aim he
made meku&llbar; sorow what he sulde do here-in, in clensyng of
hy&mtail; &thorn;at was bow&ntail; to dye, and in exsample also of
&thorn;aim at warr olyfe.  And herefo&rtail; he commawndi&dtail; at
none of his brethyr bod his fu&llbar; bruther sulde speke with
hy&mtail;, nor gyff hy&mtail; no wurd of comfurt&hbar;, bod at his
bruther sulde te&llbar; hy&mtail; &thorn;at his brethir vggid with
hy&mtail; becauce he kepy&dtail; golde privalie vnto hy&mtail; selfe.
And whe&ntail; he wiste &thorn;is he made myky&llbar; sorow, and in
&thorn;is sorow and wepyng he decesi&dtail;.  And whe&ntail; he was
dead, Saynt Grego&rtail; commandi&dtail; he sulde be bery&dtail; in a
myddyng, and at &thorn;e money sulde be caste&ntail; o&ntail;
hy&mtail;, and at &thorn;ai sulde say whe&ntail; &thorn;ai keste it; "
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">pecunia tua tecum sit in perdicionem.</FOREIGN>"
&thorn;urg&hbar; &thorn;e whilk &thorn;ing it sulde be bothe
punyssment to hy&mtail; &thorn;at dye&dtail;, &amp; ferdfulnes to
&thorn;aim &thorn;at liffi&dtail;, at &thorn;e bitternes of dead mott
do away his sy&ntail;, and at &thorn;is penance done vnto hy&mtail;
mot flay &thorn;aim att war o&ntail; lyfe.  And &thorn;us it was done.
So afterwar&dtail; &thorn;e monkis durste nevur prive to &thorn;er
selfe kepe no maner of &thorn;ing, and it was nevur so feble.  And
whe&ntail; xxx dayes war passy&dtail; he had compassio&ntail; of
&thorn;is mon&ktee;, and garte say mes for hy&mtail; xxx dayes.  And
whe&ntail; &thorn;ies war passi&dtail; he apperi&dtail; vnto his
bruther germa&ntail;, &amp; say&dtail; vnto

<PB N="436">

hy&mtail;; "Vnto now it was bod i&llbar; with me, bod now I thank God
it is wele, ffor &thorn;is day I reseyvi&dtail; my howsy&llbar;."

</P>
<P>
