<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCLXXVIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Relinquere.  Relinquendi sunt parentes a viris

perfectis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Abbot Abraham o&ntail; a tyme tolde in his 'Collasio&ntail;,' how
so&mtail; tyme &thorn;er come a yong ma&ntail; vnto Saynt Anto&ntail;
&thorn;e abbott, and reprovi&dtail; &thorn;e life of ancharis and
sai&dtail; at &thorn;ai war of more perfeccio&ntail; &thorn;at bade at
hame with &thorn;er fadurs &amp; &thorn;er moders, &amp; ordand for
&thorn;aim a&llbar; &thorn;ing att &thorn;aim myster&dtail; and wroght
beselie daylie, &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;ai war at went into wyldernes
and <NOTE ID="P454.N2">MS. <HI REND="i">repeats</HI>, and.</NOTE> abstenyd &thorn;aim fro daylie laburyng,
and gaff &thorn;aim vnto nothyng bod vnto redyng an&dtail; prayer.
And Saynt Anto&ntail; ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail; &amp; sai&dtail;;
"So&ntail;, &thorn;ou at duse &thorn;us, whethur was &thorn;ou not
hevie whe&ntail; &thorn;i fadur and &thorn;i moder happend any cace of
aduersitie?  And also was &thorn;ou not ioyfu&llbar; whe&ntail;
&thorn;ai war in prosperite?"  And he ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail; &amp;
sai&dtail; yis.  And &thorn;a&ntail; &thorn;is abbott sayd vnto
hy&mtail;; "&thorn;ou sa&llbar; vnderston&dtail; &thorn;at in &thorn;e
werl&dtail; &thorn;at is for to com &thorn;ou sal be demy&dtail; for
to be in &thorn;er companye, in whase company in &thorn;is lyfe
&thorn;ou was conuersan&dtail;, owder in wynnyng or in los, in ioy or
in sorow.  And &thorn;erfo&rtail; &thorn;uf a&llbar; we hafe bothe
ffadurs &amp; moders, yitt vs hase levur lefe &thorn;aim &amp; liff in
wyldrenes &amp; &thorn;er take syke fude as Go&dtail; sendis vs,
&thorn;a&ntail; for to be in &thorn;e warlde &amp; be sekur of fyndyng
of our fadurs &amp; moders."

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Relinquentes omnia propter deum deus remunerat.

Supra de peregrino, iij.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCLXXIX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Reliquie sanctorum sunt honorande.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how &thorn;at som tyme in ane abbay of &thorn;e
Ceustus ordur &thorn;er was ij bodis of &thorn;e xj m&lbar; virginys,
and in a were tyme &thorn;ai <NOTE ID="P454.N3">MS. &thorn;er.</NOTE> war sett aboue a
vowte in &thorn;e kur&ktee;, &amp; &thorn;er &thorn;ai stude long







<PB N="455">

&amp; was forgette&ntail;.  So o&ntail; a tyme at mydnyght &thorn;ai
made sike a dusshyng in &thorn;e cace at &thorn;ai lay in, att
a&llbar; har&dtail; in &thorn;e quere, and &thorn;us &thorn;ai
di&dtail; o&ntail; &thorn;e nyght ij or iij [sythis], vnto so
meku&llbar; at &thorn;e sacristanes sai&dtail; at &thorn;ai durste not
lygg in &thorn;e kur&ktee;.  And for a&llbar; &thorn;is &thorn;er was
no wurshu&ptail; done vnto &thorn;aim, bod a&llbar; way &thorn;ai war
nothyng lukid after.  So o&ntail; a nyght in maty&ntail; tyme,
whe&ntail; a&llbar; &thorn;e covent was i&ntail; &thorn;e where,
&thorn;ai a&llbar; saw befo&rtail; &thorn;e altar ij fayr virgyns in
maydy&ntail; clothyng, inclynand &thorn;aim, &amp; whe&ntail;
&thorn;ai had done, went furt&hbar; of &thorn;e kur&ktee; at a dure
at evur befo&rtail; was wunte to be sparri&dtail;.  So onone <NOTE ID="P455.N1">MS. o&ntail; one.</NOTE> &thorn;e monkis went vnto &thorn;e cace at
&thorn;ies ij virgynys lay i&ntail;, &amp; oppynd it, &amp; &thorn;er
was nothyng &thorn;erin.  And &thorn;ai had grete merve&llbar; hereof,
&amp; sent vnto Colay&ntail;, and &thorn;er &thorn;e same bodis was
fo&ntail; in &thorn;e same placis &thorn;er &thorn;ai lay whe&ntail;
&thorn;ai war furste giffe&ntail; vnto &thorn;e sayd abbay. et
c&curl;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Remigij Remensis.  Supra de familiaritate, ij.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCLXXX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Remissio.  Remissionis peccatorum ostendit deus

aliquando signum aliquod.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Petrus Damianus tellis of one &thorn;at hight Arnulphus, &thorn;at
was fadur of kyng Pypy&ntail;, an&dtail; grawnsur vnto great Charlis
&thorn;at was duke of Lothoringia.  So o&ntail; a tyme sodonlie he
lefte his wyfe and his childre, and went into wyldernes.  And o&ntail;
a tyme as he went ouer a grete bryg &thorn;at was ow&rtail; a depe
watir, whe&ntail; he was at &thorn;e myddest of &thorn;e brygg
&thorn;er &thorn;e watyr was depeste, &thorn;er he keste in his ryng
with &thorn;is condicio&ntail;, &amp; say&dtail;; "Whe&ntail; I hafe
&thorn;is ryng agay&ntail;, &thorn;a&ntail; with-oute&ntail; doute I
sa&llbar; truste at my synys is forgyffe&ntail; me, an&dtail; at I
a&mtail; fullie asoyli&dtail; of &thorn;aim."  And &thorn;er he abade
in wyldernes many day in gude life.  And in &thorn;e mene while
dye&dtail; &thorn;e bisshop&ptail; of Methensis, and he was
chosy&ntail; vnto bisshop&ptail;.  And he absteny&dtail; hy&mtail; fro
etyng of fless&hbar;.  So o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;er was a ffyssc&hbar;
broght hy&mtail; to a present, and he garte oppy&ntail; itt
befo&rtail; hy&mtail; and fan&dtail; hys ryng in &thorn;e cudpoke
&thorn;eroff, &amp; onone as he saw it he kend it.  And it was ij day
iorney fro &thorn;at bryg at he keste it dow[n]


<PB N="456">

att, vnto &thorn;at place &thorn;er &thorn;e fiss&hbar; was
ta&ktee;e&ntail; at it was fo&ntail; in &thorn;e bely off.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Remuneracio.  Remunerat deus dantes aliquid per

se.  Supra de elemosina, i, ij, et iij.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCLXXXI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Remunerat deus aliqua bona a peccatoribus
facta.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Cesarius tellis how som tyme &thorn;er was a knyght &thorn;at was
a grete robber and a thefe, and be commandmend of Emperour Frederyke
he was take&ntail; &amp; honge&dtail;.  And vpo&ntail; &thorn;e iij
day after he was hanged, a noder knyght come rydan&dtail; be &thorn;e
galows, and whe&ntail; he saw hy&mtail; hyng &thorn;er he say&dtail;
vnto his ma&ntail;; "O God! it was meku&llbar; petie at &thorn;is fayr
ma&ntail; was hanged!"  And his ma&ntail; ansswer&dtail; hy&mtail;
agay&ntail; &amp; say&dtail;; "Sur, &thorn;is was a noble knyght &amp;
your nere cussy&ntail;."  So &thorn;is knyght &amp; his ma&ntail; come
ner, and thoght to take hy&mtail; dow&ntail; &amp; beryy hy&mtail;;
and as he hang he spakk vnto &thorn;aim &amp; say&dtail;; "Take me
dow&ntail;, ffor I lyff yitt."  And whe&ntail; &thorn;ai had tane
hy&mtail; dow&ntail; he say&dtail; vnto &thorn;aim; "Thuff a&llbar; I
was a synner, yit I did a litle serves vnto almyghtie Go&dtail;, for
&thorn;e whilk He had mercie o&ntail; me; ffor I vsid euere day to say
iij pater noster, &amp; iij ave maria, in wurshu&ptail; of &thorn;e
holie trynytie, &amp; v pater noster &amp; v ave maria in
wurshu&ptail; of &thorn;e v wowndis of our Lorde, and a pater noster
in wurshu&ptail; of &thorn;e aunge&llbar; at I a&mtail; betaght too,
and also one vnto &thorn;e sacrament &thorn;at is daylie sacred
&thorn;urg&hbar; a&llbar; &thorn;is werlde, besekyng daylie almighti
Go&dtail;, at I myght be wurthi to reseyfe &thorn;e sacrament er I
dye&dtail;.  And &thorn;at God hase grawnti&dtail; me of His mercie,
and &thorn;erfo&rtail; I pray you ca&llbar; vnto me a preste."  And
whe&ntail; &thorn;e preste come he shrafe hy&mtail;, and
&thorn;a&ntail; he was howsle&dtail;.  And onone as &thorn;is was done
he yelde v&ptail; his gaste, and &thorn;ai tuke and beri&dtail;
hy&mtail; <NOTE ID="P456.N1"><HI REND="i">This tale is marked</HI> Nota [be]ne.</NOTE> .

</P>
<P>
