<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCLXXXII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Reuerencia.  Reuereri et honorari debent [se mutuo] 
<NOTE ID="P457.N5"><HI REND="i">From the</HI> Latin MS.</NOTE> 
homines eiusdem status.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Valerius tellis how &thorn;at in &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at &thorn;e
vij sagis florisshi&dtail; at Athenis, it happen&dtail; in &thorn;e
regio&ntail; of Niclase <NOTE ID="P457.N6">MS. <HI REND="i">repeats</HI>, it happened, <HI REND="i">here</HI>.</NOTE> at a ma&ntail; boght of
&thorn;e ffysshers a draght with &thorn;er nett, &amp; at &thorn;at
draght &thorn;ai &thorn;aim happend draw a grete burde a&llbar; of
golde of a grete weght.  And so &thorn;ai fe&llbar; at varyans for
&thorn;is burde, &thorn;e fisshers &amp; &thorn;ai &thorn;at boght
&thorn;e draght, for &thorn;ai say&dtail; &thorn;ai solde hy&mtail;
noght bod ffiss&hbar;, &amp; he sai&dtail; he boght what at fortun
wolde send hy&mtail;.  So &thorn;ai had it vnto &thorn;e cetie, and
broght it befo&rtail; Appollo, &amp; made &thorn;er prayers vnto
hy&mtail; to send &thorn;aim som take&ntail; to whame &thorn;is burde
sulde be demy&dtail;.  An&dtail; he ansswer&dtail; &thorn;aim &amp;
bad &thorn;aim giff it vnto hy&mtail; &thorn;at was &thorn;e wyseste
in a&llbar; &thorn;e cetie.  And so &thorn;ai gaff it vnto one
&thorn;at hight Talentus Millesius, &thorn;at emang &thorn;e vij sagis
was moste noble, and he sent it vnto Byantes Priemo.  And he wolde
none &thorn;eroff bod gaff it vnto a noder, and so it went
&thorn;urg&hbar; &thorn;aim a&llbar; vnto it come at &thorn;e laste.
And he gaff a iudgement at it sulde be halowi&dtail; in wurshu&ptail;
of Appollo &amp; gyffe&ntail; vnto hy&mtail;, and so it was.













<PB N="458">

</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCLXXXIII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Reuiuiscere vel resurgere.  Reuiuiscit aliquando

homo ex gratia spirituali.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Gregur tellis how &thorn;er was som tyme in Rome a noble
cetysy&ntail; &thorn;at hight Romanus <NOTE ID="P458.N1">Latin, civis romanus, Stephanus nomine.</NOTE> , and
hy&mtail; happen&dtail; for to dye at Constantynople.  &amp; o&ntail;
&thorn;e mor&ntail; whe&ntail; &thorn;ai wol&dtail; hafe opyn&dtail;
hy&mtail; &amp; seson&dtail; hy&mtail; with spycis at he myght hafe
bene curi&dtail; <NOTE ID="P458.N2">MS. cari&dtail;.</NOTE> , he rase vp&ptail; &amp; was
whik&ktee;.  And he tolde &thorn;aim meku&llbar; &thorn;ing at he had
sene in he&llbar;, and at he neuer trowi&dtail; befo&rtail;, &amp; he
tolde also &thorn;at &thorn;e juge at he was broght befo&rtail;,
&thorn;at he calli&dtail; hy&mtail; noght Romanus <NOTE ID="P458.N3">Harl. MS. non petierat, 'huncStephanum,' sed, 'Stephanum Ferarium,' mortuus est. Arund.  MS. sed 'Stephanum Ferrarium,' qui erat iuxta eum, quo dicto, ille Stephanus mortuus est.'</NOTE> , bod Romanus Ferarius &thorn;at was nere-han&dtail;
hy&mtail;.  And &thorn;us he &thorn;at ans was dea&dtail; was o&ntail;
lyfe agay&ntail; &amp; liffi&dtail; many yeris.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Rex aliquando gloriatur in vestibus.  Supra de

augurio et de ornatu.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Rex humiliter se habet ad subditos.  Supra de

iudicio vltimo.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
