<PB N="460">

</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCLXXXVI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Sacerdos debet frequenter pro mortuis
celebrare.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Petrus Clunacensis <NOTE ID="P460.N1">MS. Climacensis.</NOTE> tellis how &thorn;er was
som tyme a bisshop&ptail; &thorn;at suspent a certa&ntail; preste in
his dioces becauce he sang euerilk day for a&llbar; cryste&ntail;
sawlis.  So o&ntail; a tyme afterwar&dtail;, as &thorn;is
bisshop&ptail; walkid be his one in a kur&ktee;-gart&hbar;, hy&mtail;
&thorn;oght at a&llbar; &thorn;e dead folk at lay in &thorn;at
kur&ktee;-garthe rase agayns hy&mtail;, ilkone with a spade in
&thorn;er han&dtail;.  And &thorn;ai thrett hy&mtail; &amp;
sai&dtail;; "Beholde! &thorn;is is &thorn;e bisshop&ptail; &thorn;at
tuke fro vs our preste &amp; suspend hy&mtail;, at he may not say mes
for vs.  And &thorn;erfo&rtail; certanlie, bod if he amend it vnto vs,
he sa&llbar; dye."  And with &thorn;at he was so flaye&dtail; he was
like hafe dye&dtail;, &amp; fe&llbar; in a swown&dtail; <NOTE ID="P460.N2">MS. swownyd.</NOTE> .  And whe&ntail; he come vnto hy&mtail; selfe
agay&ntail;, he garte send after &thorn;e preste and asoyli&dtail;
hy&mtail;, &amp; bad hy&mtail; syng o&ntail; for al cryste&ntail;
sawlis as he did befo&rtail;.


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCLXXXVII.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Sacerdotis malicia non polluit
sacramentum.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Iacobus de Vetriaco tellis how &thorn;er was so&mtail; tyme a
ma&ntail;, whilk &thorn;at of ane vnwurthie prest &thorn;at he knew
wolde nowder here mes nor resayfe his sacramentis.  So o&ntail; a tyme
hy&mtail; thoght in his slepe &thorn;at hy&mtail; was passand
thrustie, and &thorn;at he stude be a pitt with watir &thorn;er a
leprus ma&ntail; drew vp watir in a passand fayr vesse&llbar; with a
corde a&llbar; of golde.  And &thorn;er come many one &amp;
axki&dtail; hy&mtail; a drynk of &thorn;at fayr watir, &amp; he gaff
&thorn;aim &amp; &thorn;ai dran&ktee; faste.  And at &thorn;e laste
&thorn;is ma&ntail; drew ner &amp; wolde hafe had a dryn&ktee;, &amp;
&thorn;e layser ma&ntail; drew bak his han&dtail; &amp; wolde not lat
hy&mtail; dryn&ktee;, &amp; say&dtail;; "How wi&llbar; &thorn;ou take
a drynke of a lepros ma&ntail; han&dtail;, &thorn;at wi&llbar; not
here mes nor take &thorn;e sacramentis of a preste at &thorn;ou knowis
is in sy&ntail;?  Do no mo&rtail; so, bod &thorn;in&ktee; of
&thorn;is vers; <FOREIGN LANG="LAT">'vim sacramenti non mutat vita
ministri.'</FOREIGN>" And with &thorn;at he wakyn&dtail;.





<PB N="461">

And fro thens furt&hbar; he neuer gruchi&dtail; after to here
&thorn;at prestis mes, nor for to take his sacramentis of holie
kur&ktee; of his hande.

</P>
<P>
