<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCCXLI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Suspicio diligenter examinata est falsa.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Ierom tellis &thorn;at it is wrete&ntail; in &thorn;e bukis
of Ypocratis how &thorn;er was a ma&ntail; &thorn;at &thorn;oght his
wyfe sulde be punysshi&dtail;, &amp; suspecte






<PB N="495">

hur becauce sho bare a fayr bar&ntail; at was not like nowder &thorn;e
fadur nor &thorn;e modir.  So &thorn;ai bathe agrei&dtail; at a leche
sulde essone &thorn;e questio&ntail;.  And a leche come, &amp; he
say&dtail; <NOTE ID="P495.N1">Latin MSS. Ne forte talis pictura esset in cubiculo.  Qua inuenta, mulier a suspicione liberata.</NOTE> it was like &thorn;e clothe at was
o&ntail; the bed whe&ntail; it was gette&ntail;, &amp; &thorn;us
&thorn;e womma&ntail; was delyver&dtail; fro&mtail; hur
suspecio&ntail;.

</P>
<P>
