<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCCXLII.  
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Tactus.  Tangi debet mulier nec a sanis nec ab

infirmis.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Gregur tellis how som tyme &thorn;er was a preste, &amp;
&thorn;er was giffe&ntail; hy&mtail; a kurk and he governy&dtail; it
with meku&llbar; drede, whilk <NOTE ID="P495.N3">Latin MSS. qui ex tempore ordinis suscepti presbiteram suam ut sororem diligens, sed ut pestem fugiens, &amp;c.</NOTE> &thorn;at fro he
had furste tane ordurs he luffi&dtail; passynglie presbiteram suam,
for in that contre evur-ilk a preste hath a wyfe, bod he fled hur as
he wol&dtail; hafe done pestelens, and wulde not suffre hur co&mtail;
nere hy&mtail;.  And whe&ntail; he had bene xl<HI REND="sup">ti</HI> yere preste, a grete
ffevurs tuke hy&mtail; so &thorn;at he was bow&ntail; to dye &amp;
tuke a passio&ntail; of dea&dtail;.  And whe&ntail; his wyfe saw that,
sho made grete sorow &amp; went he had dyed.  And sho leny&dtail;
dow&ntail; hur mowthe vnto his at luke if any brethe war in hy&mtail;,
and whe&ntail; he feli&dtail; hur he spak vnto hur &amp; sayd; "Go
away fro me, womma&ntail;, ffor yit &thorn;er is a sparke of lyfe in
me, &amp; &thorn;erfor remefe away &thorn;e caff at it bur&ntail;
not!"

</P>
<P>
