<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCCXLVI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Temptacio est magistra meriti.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Vitis Patrum' how o&ntail; a tyme &thorn;e disciple of
ane alde monke was gretelie tempi&dtail; with &thorn;e spirit of
fornicacio&ntail;, bod &thorn;urg&hbar; &thorn;e grace of God,
manlelie he withstude it.  And &thorn;is monke, when he saw hy&mtail;
so grete labur &thorn;ero&ntail;, he sayd vnto hy&mtail;; "So&ntail;,
and &thorn;ou wi&llbar;, I sa&llbar; pray God to do &thorn;is
temptacio&ntail; away fro the."  And he ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail;
&amp; sayd; "Thuf a&llbar; I hafe a grete labur in withstondyng
&thorn;erof, yitt I fele frute &thorn;erin, ffor it cawsis me to faste
&amp; for to wake and giff hede vnto my prayers.  And
&thorn;erfo&rtail; I pray &thorn;e pray Almyghtie God to gif me vertue
to sustene itt, and for to withstonde it manfullie."


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCCXLVII.
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">
<LB>Temptat demon religiosos per formas mulierum
ymaginatas 
<NOTE ID="P498.N2">MS. ymaginatinas.</NOTE> .</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in 'Vitis Patrum' how so&mtail; [tyme] &thorn;er was in a
monasterie a mon&ktee; &thorn;at had a so&ntail;.  And he was so long
nurisshi&dtail; &thorn;er &amp; come not oute, att he knew not
whatky&ntail; thyng womme&ntail; was.  So whe&ntail; he was
wexe&ntail; vnto mans state, &thorn;e devu&llbar; apperi&dtail; vnto
hy&mtail; in lyknes and clothyng of a womma&ntail;, and he tolde his





<PB N="499">

fadur whatt he had sene and axki&dtail; hy&mtail; whatt it was, &amp;
he wolde not te&llbar; hy&mtail;.  So o&ntail; a tyme he went with his
fadur into Egypte, and &thorn;er he saw womme&ntail;.  And
&thorn;a&ntail; he tolde his fadur at &thorn;ai war swilk at he saw in
his abbay in wyldernes, and his fadur had merve&llbar; here-of &amp;
trowi&dtail; at it was a disseyte of &thorn;e devu&llbar; and said
vnto hy&mtail;; "So&ntail;, thies er seculer monkes &thorn;at vsis a
noder maner of habett &thorn;a&ntail; monkis or hermettis duse."  And
onone &thorn;ai went home samen agay&ntail;, and he wolde nevur after
latt hy&mtail; co&mtail; furt&hbar; agay&ntail; oute of his abbay.

</P>
<P>
