</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCCXCIX.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Christianus.  Christiani mali magis puniuntur

in inferno quam infideles.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> We rede in &thorn;e 'Life of Saynt Macharie' how o&ntail; a day he
fand a dead ma&ntail; hea&dtail;, &amp; he spak &thorn;erto &amp;
aski&dtail; whose hede it was, &amp; it ansswer&dtail; agay&ntail;
&amp; say&dtail; it was &thorn;e hea&dtail; of a payno&mtail;.  And he








<PB N="531">

aski&dtail; whar &thorn;e saule &thorn;er-of was, &amp; it say&dtail;
in he&llbar;; &amp; he axki&dtail; how depe, and it sai&dtail;, als
depe as fro hevy&ntail; to erde.  And he axki&dtail; if &thorn;er was
any dipper &thorn;a&ntail; it, and it say&dtail; ya, a&llbar; fals
cryste&ntail; me&ntail;, &thorn;ai er depeste in he&llbar;.

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Christus.  Christi ymago.  Supra de ymagine.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCCC.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Ymago Christi miracula facit.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Eusebius tellis of &thorn;e womma&ntail; &thorn;at was
calli&dtail; Emorissa, &thorn;at was clensy&dtail; of hur sekenes be
&thorn;e tuching of ow&rtail; Lordis he&mtail;, sho garte make ane
ymage after Cryste with clothyng &amp; His he&mtail; as sho saw
Hy&mtail;, &amp; oft sithis sho wurshippi&dtail; it, &amp; sho sett it
in hur garte, &amp; a&llbar; &thorn;e herbys grew &thorn;er <NOTE ID="P531.N1">MS. vppon, erased.</NOTE> vnder-nethe &thorn;at befo&rtail; was of no vertue,
whe&ntail; &thorn;ai grew vp &amp; tuchy&dtail; &thorn;e he&mtail;
&thorn;eroff &thorn;ai war of suche vertue at &thorn;ai heli[d] many
folke &thorn;at war seke.  And as Iero&mtail; tellis, Iulianus had it
away &amp; sett &thorn;er[in] hys aw&ntail; ymage, and belyfe a blaste
of levenyng come &amp; smate it dow&ntail; &amp; burn[yd it].

</P>
<P>
<LIST LANG="LAT">
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Ymago crucifixi sanguinem emisit.  Supra de

crucifixo.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Ymago beate virginis infectionem 
<NOTE ID="P531.N2">MS. temptacionem.</NOTE>  mitigauit.  Supra

de Maria, x.</FOREIGN></ITEM>
<ITEM><FOREIGN>Ymago beate virginis anulum a puero suscepit.

Supra de puero.</FOREIGN></ITEM></LIST>


</P></DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD> DCCCI.
<LB>
<FOREIGN LANG="LAT">Ypocrisis.  Ypocrita a demone deuoratur.</FOREIGN></HEAD>

<P> Saynt Gregorie tellis how som tyme &thorn;er was a monke of grete
estimacio&ntail; in his gude thewis, &amp; passan&dtail; wele
nurtur&dtail; in a&llbar; his oder gude werkis; as it provi&dtail; at
en&dtail;, he was not so





<PB N="532">

inwar&dtail;, for he was o&thorn;erwas &thorn;a&ntail; he
apperi&dtail;.  So hy&mtail; happyn&dtail; a hevynes of his bodie
&amp; fe&llbar; seke, and he garte gadder to-gedur a&llbar; his bredur
vnto hy&mtail;, and &thorn;ai trowyng &thorn;at, &amp; he dye&dtail;,
at &thorn;ai sulde hafe so&mtail; grete thyng of hy&mtail;, or els
so&mtail; thyng &thorn;at was delectable for to here it of hy&mtail;.
And whe&ntail; &thorn;ai come afor&ntail; hy&mtail;, &thorn;uf
a&llbar; he war gretelie turment &amp; whakan&dtail;, [yit] he was
compelli&dtail; to vttyr.  And &thorn;a&ntail; he say&dtail; vnto
&thorn;aim; "Brethir, whe&ntail; ye trow[yd] at I fasti&dtail; with
you I had meate privalie &amp; eete, and &thorn;erfo&rtail; I a&mtail;
now giffe&ntail; vnt[o a] drago&ntail; to devow&rtail;, ffor with his
tayle he hase vmlappi&dtail; my kneis, &amp; he hase [put] his
hea&dtail; in my mouthe &amp; suppyd vp my sawle. &amp; with &thorn;at
he stude vp&ptail; o&ntail; his fete and onone he was dea&dtail;.

</P>
<P>
